title: party potato skins
directions: Scrub potatoes and rub skins with oil; prick each potato several times with a fork.
Bake in oven at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Allow potatoes to cool to touch; cut top third of each potato; discard tops.
Carefully scoop out pulp, leaving about 1/8-inch thick shells.
(Reserve pulp for later use.)
Fry potato skins in hot oil for 3 to 4 minutes and drain on paper towel.
Place potato skins, cut side up, on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and Cheddar cheese.
Broil 6 inches from heat for 30 seconds or until cheese melts.
Top potato skins with bacon and 1 tablespoon of chives. Press green chilies between paper towels to remove excess moisture. Combine chilies, sour cream and red pepper in a small bowl.
Top with remaining chives and serve with skins.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: Cream cheese, oleo and peanut butter together.
Melt together in large pan; add vanilla and sugar.
Knead it like bread dough until you can't see any white of sugar.
Can add chocolate chips, raisins, shredded coconut or your favorite trim.

title: eileen's top secret barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix well the first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: italian rice salad
directions: In large bowl blend dressing with mayonnaise; stir in veggies. Add rice and toss well.
Put in mold and chill well.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix and sift together all dry ingredients.
Add onions. Combine beaten egg with milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Drop by spoon into deep, hot grease where fish have been cooked.
When done, they will float.

title: chess pie
directions: Cook slightly all ingredients and put in unbaked pie shell; bake at 350° until done.

title: angel cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and Cool Whip together.

It will make a sticky batter. Drop spoonfuls into powdered sugar and roll dough into a ball. Place sugared dough balls onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool on racks.

title: sweet and sour salad dressing
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well with a whisk.
Bring to just barely boiling (do not boil).
Add oil when mixture is cool.
Mix well and refrigerate!
Very Good!!

title: crazy fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased, floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 275° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly. Put nuts in last. Preheat oven to 375°. Turn down to 300° when you put the bread in oven. Bake 1 1/2 hours or until a toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean. Makes 3 loaves.

title: dried bean-burger casserole
directions: Pour boiling water over string beans and let stand 5 minutes. Simmer unsalted until tender.
Add ground gluten or TVP to tomato soup.
Let stand to absorb flavor.
Put reconstituted green beans in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Pour gluten-soup mixture over beans.
Spoon mashed potatoes on top.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese melts well.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix and press into long pan the graham crackers and melted butter; let cool.
Whip powdered sugar, butter and eggs for 15 minutes and spread over cracker layer.
Drain pineapple and spread on top.
Slice the bananas over pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip on top.
Next, the cherries and sprinkle with the nuts.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in pineapple and bread.
Bake in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: magic french fudge
directions: In double boiler, melt chocolate chips.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
The peanut butter is optional, also the nuts.

title: tea cakes old fashioned
directions: Omit salt and baking powder if using self-rising flour.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients; add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to make a stiff dough.
Roll thin, cut and bake.
May be used as drop cookies.

title: zucchini au gratin
directions: Pour oil into baking dish and add 1/3 squash, parsley and cheese.
Salt to taste.
Make layers until all ingredients are used.
Cover with crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake uncovered in 350 degree oven until golden brown, about 45-50 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together and put into a loaf pan; set aside.

title: punch
directions: Chill juice in cans.
Dissolve sugar in water and chill.
Mix Kool-Aid with chilled water and sugar.
Mix with the chilled juice.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.

title: black bottom cakes miniatures
directions: Combine cream cheese, egg, 1/3 cup sugar, 1/8 teaspoon salt; beat well.
Add chips and set aside.
Sift together flour, cocoa, baking soda, 1 teaspoon salt and 1 cup sugar.
Add water, vinegar, oil and vanilla.
Beat well.
Use miniature cupcake tins and liners.
Fill liners with cocoa mixture 3/4 full.
Drop 1/2 teaspoon of cream cheese mixture on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at preheated 350°.
Yields 48.
Can be frozen.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and butter.
Add the 1/4 cup sugar and cornstarch and cream.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Place flour, 2 cups sugar, salt, baking powder, baking soda, butter/oleo and milk in a bowl.
Blend, then beat 1/2 minute at low speed.

title: sugar-free meringue fluff
directions: Mix well.
Yields 2 to 3 cups.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop small stems and tops of broccoli.
Also chop red onion. Fry bacon; drain and crumble.
Grate sharp cheese.
Mix all this together.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Just before serving, pour dressing over salad and toss.

title: tilikum-broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli and peeled stems into bite size pieces. Mix with cooked bacon, onion and raisins.
In separate bowl, mix mayonnaise, sugar and raisins.
Mix into broccoli mixture.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Makes 28 to 32 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: homemade banana ice cream(without the churn)
directions: Whip milk until firmly stiff.
Add mashed bananas.
Sweeten with sugar to taste.
Add lemon juice to taste to cut sweetness. Put in freezer cartons and let freeze.
After frozen, take out, break up in large bowl, then whip until soft and smooth.
Return to cartons and freeze.
(Makes a little more than 1 quart.)

title: banana nut ice cream
directions: Lightly beat eggs; add sugar.
Gradually continue to beat until thick.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Freeze according to your freezer directions.

title: chicken gourmet
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Combine other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with sweet paprika. Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
(Can be prepared in advance.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt
the
oleo and mix the crushed crackers and grated cheese into it.
Season to taste.
Mix the squash, eggs, onion and
milk and add 1/2 the cracker mixture to it.
Pour into a greased casserole and top with the remaining cracker mixture. Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 8.

title: ham and noodle casserole(for microwave)
directions: Cook egg noodles.
In a 1 1/2-quart microproof casserole dish combine ham, onion, tarragon and butter.
Cook, covered, on High (maximum power) for 3 minutes.
Add chicken soup, egg moodles, green beans and water.
Stir.
Cook, covered, on High (maximum power) 5 minutes, or until hot, stirring once during cooking time. Top with bread crumbs.
Let stand, covered, 2 to 3 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: three cheese manicotti
directions: In small saucepan, blend water, tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce mix; simmer uncovered for 10 to 12 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine 1 cup Mozzarella, Ricotta and Parmesan cheese.
Add eggs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix lightly; stuff shells with cheese mixture using about 1/2 cup of mixture for each.
Pour half of spaghetti sauce into 2-quart or 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish; arrange stuffed manicotti in dish.
Pour remaining sauce over top.
Sprinkle remaining 1 cup cheese and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: corn flake macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Gradually beat in sugar, continuing to beat until very stiff.
Fold in vanilla, coconut, corn flakes and nuts.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter.
Fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate.
Let set overnight.

title: mock zucchini pie
directions: Peel zucchini and remove seeds and lose pulp.
Slice like apples for pie.
Cook until tender in lemon juice; add sugar and spices.
Let cool.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Cream egg and butter.
Add marshmallow cream.
Add strawberries with juice, pineapple and nuts.
Add whipped cream.
Mix together. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs, then pour mixture over crumbs. Freeze until ready to serve.
Remove 30 minutes before serving.

title: groten hans(steamed dumpling)
directions: Combine sugar, egg yolks and melted butter.
Stir together the dry ingredients and add alternately to the egg yolks with the milk.
Add vanilla and raisins.
Fold in the beaten egg whites. Turn into a cloth, place in a steamer and steam 2 to 3 hours, until firm like a heavy bread.

title: four layered delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, 1/4
cup sugar, and melted butter.
Press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in large bowl of mixer.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla. Sift flour, soda and cream of tartar. Add flour mixtures in four different times, beating well after the first 3 times.
This is a soft dough, so chill in the refrigerator overnight before cooking.

title: pea-ham casserole
directions: Combine in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vinegar spice mixture
directions: In a large saucepan, pour apple cider vinegar, water, sugar and pickling spice that has been tied in a small piece of cheesecloth. Bring to a rolling boil; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes. Pour hot vinegar into jars to 1-inch from top, over cucumbers. Use a clean damp towel to wipe mouth of each jar. Place lids on jars snug, not tight. Place jars in water bath and boil 5 minutes. Remove from water bath, tighten lids and allow to air cool before storage.

title: diabetic pound cake
directions: Mix flour and soda; add oil and sugar and mix.
Beat eggs; add with remaining ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Serve with cream cheese. Soften cheese and beat until smooth.
Spread on slices of cake.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender.
Combine cooked carrots, pepper, celery and onion.
Make a sauce with the remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover tightly and store overnight.
Keeps for several weeks in refrigerator.

title: apricot pear tart
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter in a small bowl. Press crumb mixture onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan. Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, measure 3/4 cup Jell-O; set aside.
Chill remaining Jell-O until slightly thickened.
Fold in whipped topping and ginger.
Spoon over crust.
Chill measured gelatin until slightly thickened.
Slice pears lengthwise, cutting almost through stem ends.
Arrange on whipped topping mixture, fanning each pear slightly.
Place mint leaf and cinnamon stick at stem of each.
Carefully spoon remaining Jell-O over pears. Chill 3 hours.
Run hot knife around edges of pan before removing.

title: cheese straws
directions: Use hands to mix oleo and cheese.
Mix flour, onion salt, dry mustard and pepper together.
Add to cheese and mix well.
Press out strips from cookie press onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Cut into desired lengths.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 or 9 dozen.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Trim crusts.
Flatten slices with rolling pin.
Blend cheese and egg.
Spread evenly on bread slices.
Place asparagus spears on each slice of bread.
Roll into log shape.
Dip into melted butter, coating well.
Place each log on a cookie sheet and freeze.
When firm, slice into 3 pieces.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Place chicken in a large kettle and add about 2 quarts of cold water.
Bring to a boil, then reduce and simmer until chicken is tender.
Take chicken from broth; reserve the broth.
Cut chicken into small (bite-size) pieces and set aside.
Cook spaghetti in the reserved broth until tender; drain well.
Blend soup and milk in saucepan; add chicken and mushrooms.
Blend well and heat through.
Layer spaghetti, chicken mixture and Cheddar cheese in casserole dish, sprinkling each layer with salt and pepper.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy sesame chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken in chunks (bite size), then dip chunks in egg, flour, water and sesame batter; season with salt and pepper and fry in about 1-inch hot oil.
Better double recipe as they go fast.
May serve with assorted dips (honey mustard, barbecue or Ranch).

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Follow directions on spaghetti box (use tomato paste, not tomato sauce).
Boil spaghetti in both boxes and extra package as well.
When sauce and spaghetti are both done, fry hamburger; mix it together with sauce.
Drain spaghetti.
In large baking dish, pour one layer of sauce mixture on bottom, follow with a layer of boiled spaghetti, another layer of sauce and finish with last of spaghetti.
Place cheese over all.
Put in 350° oven for 3 to 4 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: cold cucumber soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in Cuisinart and puree until smooth. Check seasoning; serve.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Boil hollowed out whole peppers for 3 minutes in saltwater; drain.
Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add tomatoes to hamburger mixture and spices, uncooked rice and water, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until rice is tender (about 20 minutes).
Fill peppers with mixture and any remaining mixture; spoon around outside of peppers in 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake 2 minutes more; let stand 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Then serve.
These can be made up to the baking part and frozen.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in butter until slightly brown.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/4 cups sauce.

title: baby ruth cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Beat in egg.
Stir in other ingredients.
Chill and drop by 1/2 teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 50 to 75 cookies.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix brown sugar, white sugar, milk and salt in pan; bring to boil over medium heat.
Boil to soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter, vanilla and nuts. May use crunchy peanut butter and not add nuts.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: pennsylvania dutch chicken corn soup
directions: In Dutch oven, combine chicken, water, parsley, onions, bay leaf, salt, pepper and thyme.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Remove meat from bones and return to broth.
Bring to a boil and cook lima beans 5 to 10 minutes.
Add corn and noodles.
Simmer 7 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Discard bay leaf.
Stir in eggs and parsley.
Adjust seasonings.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Put raw hamburger in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Layer sliced onion over hamburger.
Season to taste.
Layer Tater Tots over seasonings.
Mix soup with milk, then pour over top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: pastie pie
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Add all of mixture to pastry lined pie pan.
Sprinkle with 3 tablespoons butter.
Cover with top pastry. Crimp edges and slit top.
Place in preheated oven at 400° for 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Slice bananas and beat until well mashed.
Add remaining ingredients (do not add ingredients listed on cake box).
Blend them.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
(Can may be baked in 13 x 9-inch pan for to 50 to 55 minutes, if preferred.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Lay chicken breasts in pan.
Cover chicken with frozen broccoli.
Combine soup and Cheez Whiz and pour over broccoli. Bake at 400°, uncovered, for 1 hour.
For easy clean-up, line pan with foil.

title: white bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast with 3 cups of lukewarm water and let dissolve for 5 minutes; stir.
Add rest of ingredients and knead for 10 minutes.
Rise to double size.
Beat down and place in pans.
Rise 1 hour and bake.
Preheat oven to 375° and bake for 45 minutes. Remove from pans and place on cooling racks quickly.

title: everyday meat loaf
directions: In bowl combine first 8 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add meat and mix well.
In 9-inch glass pie plate, shape meat mixture into a ring about 1-inch high around a small juice glass.
Cover and microcook until meat is done, about 12 to 13 minutes.
Remove juice glass.
Let meat loaf stand about 5 minutes before removing to serving plate.

title: campfire coffee
directions: Heat 2 quarts cold water to boiling.
Mix coffee, 3 tablespoons water and egg.
Pour water over coffee mix in coffee pot.
Heat just to boiling.
Cover.
Let stand 12 minutes at grill's edge.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Put celery and onion in 1 tablespoon butter and 1/4 cup water. Cover and cook to boiling stage.
Add soup and tuna and 2 slices cheese.
Salt and pepper.
Put cooked noodles and peas in casserole dish.
Pour mixture over noodles and peas; mix.
Put more cheese on top.
Garnish with olives.
Bake at 350° until begins to bubble.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in a little butter until tender. Mix together with all other ingredients and pour into ungreased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat eggs.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika and dot with butter before baking.
Bake in oiled casserole 40 minutes at 350°.

title: butternut fingers
directions: Mix all with hands and roll into small fingers; curve.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar (or shake in a bag).

title: walnut coffee cake
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: potato patties
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter.
Heat 2 tablespoons butter in a skillet.
Make small balls of potato mixture and pat out into patties.
Brown in butter and serve hot.
This is really a great use for leftover mashed potatoes.

title: chop sewey cake
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Pour into large cake pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 375° until toothpick comes out clean.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: mocked apple pie
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to a rolling boil, making sure butter and sugar are completely dissolved.
Add all at one time to soda crackers; stir while it cooks for 3 minutes.
Add lemon juice and sprinkle of spice for flavor.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle top with sugar and a little spice.
Bake at 350° until crust turns a golden brown.

title: fruit muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add egg and liquids.
Bake in large greased muffin pan for 20 minutes at 400°.
If blueberries are frozen, do not defrost.
You may substitute any other fruit.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Stir in other ingredients.
Let jell overnight.

title: jambalaya
directions: Heat oil and saute onion until tender.
Add sausage and ham. Let cook on medium for about 15 minutes.
Keep covered.
Add tomatoes.
Cook about 15 minutes longer.
(Chop tomatoes.)
Add shrimp and drained oysters, but set oyster water aside.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add rice and cook on low, stirring often.
Cook until rice is tender.
If rice is too dry but not done, add oyster water.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain and dry fruit.
Melt butter and stir in brown sugar and curry powder.
Place mixed fruit in a long baking dish.
Pour brown sugar mixture over fruit.
Dot top with a few maraschino cherries for added color.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: basic roux(basis for all stews and gumbos)
directions: Heat oil in a heavy pot or Dutch oven.
When oil is hot, gradually add flour, stirring continuously until well mixed.
Lower flame and continue stirring until chocolate brown.
When roux is chocolate brown, remove from pot and set aside.
If roux remains in the pot, it will continue to cook and get too dark.
Always use warm water to dissolve the roux.
While you're at it, make more than enough as it keeps well in or out of the refrigerator.

title: easy mexican rice
directions: Brown rice slightly in butter.
Add broth and salsa and bring to boil.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook 15 to 20 minutes, or until moisture is absorbed.

title: new york spaghetti pie
directions: Break spaghetti in half and cook in boiling salted water just until tender; drain. In medium bowl beat eggs and cheese; add warm spaghetti and toss to mix. Line a buttered 10-inch pie plate with spaghetti mixture; set aside. In large skillet; over medium heat; saut pepper and onion in butter for about 5 minutes or until onion is tender but not brown; stir in sour cream. Spoon over spaghetti. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. In a 3 qt. Saucepan over medium heat cook sausage, breaking up meat until no longer pink. Drain off fat. In a small bowl; mix water and tomato paste; Stir in sausage. Simmer over low heat for 10 min. or until slightly thickened. Spoon over sour cream mixture. Cover with foil and bake for 25 min. in 350-degree oven. Remove foil and arrange cheese over top and bake for an additional 3 to 5 min. or until cheese is melted. Cut into wedges and serve.

title: dolly bars
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt 1 stick margarine at 350°.
Mix in graham cracker crumbs and press into bottom of pan.
Pour can of milk on top.
Sprinkle with coconut and then chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: walnut kipfel
directions: Make the yeast mixture and let stand a short while.
With a fork, work margarine.
The dough can be chilled overnight.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken and parsley in greased 8 x 11-inch pan.
Place chicken on top of mixture.
Sprinkle parsley on top.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°. Then uncover and bake 30 minutes more.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Prepare long grain and wild rice according to package while rice is cooking.
Saute mushrooms, onions and celery in butter until tender, 5 to 7 minutes.
When rice is done, stir in condensed mushroom soup, diced chicken, broccoli and pepper.
Add sauteed vegetables and pour into greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash peppers, remove seeds and stems from the tops.
Cook in boiling salted water for 5 minutes.
Combine rice, meat, tomatoes, onion, salt and pepper.
Stuff preboiled peppers.
Mix crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle on top of peppers.
Put peppers in casserole with tomato juice.
Bake at 375° about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mawmaw's moist cornbread dressing
directions: Cook cornbread.
Crumble to make 4 cups.
Boil and debone 1 large hen.
Add 1 large box Stove Top dressing according to directions, using broth instead of water and add to other dressing mix. Be sure it is very moist.
Bake at 350° until all vegetables are well done.
If dry before done, add extra broth.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine dry cake mix, melted butter and one egg.
Beat until combined.
Reserve 1 cup mixture.
Spread remaining mix in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, pressing to form even crust. Filling:
Beat 2 eggs, pumpkin, evaporated milk, brown sugar and spices.
Pour over prepared crust.
Combine reserved 1 cup mixture, 2 tablespoons sugar, 2 tablespoons butter and cinnamon. Dot evenly over pumpkin filling.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack; cut into squares and serve with whipped cream if desired.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Arrange hash browns in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Melt ingredients in microwave.
Pour over hash browns.
Gently mix. Cover and refrigerate 1 hour or more.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken curry
directions: Layer broccoli and chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix other ingredients together, except bread crumbs and Cheddar cheese. Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: winter strawberries
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape in balls and roll in colored sugar.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Mix and bake until hot.
Serve with crackers.

title: pork chops for four
directions: Brown pork chops in olive oil in skillet, then take out.
Saute sliced potatoes, onions, green peppers and mushrooms.
Dissolve 2 chicken bouillon cubes in 2 cups of water and pour over vegetables. Put pork chops back in skillet with vegetables and simmer about 30 minutes until tender.

title: irma's peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg.
Beat just until blended.

title: quick candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips and almond bark in top of a double boiler.
Add nuts.
Stir.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: dough for pizza
directions: Make a well (circle
with
opening
in center) with the flour. Add oil, water/yeast, salt and eggs in center of well. Add 1 cup warm
water
to
center
liquid
ingredients.
Start mixing flour into center ingredients by hand slowly.
Mix with hands until you form
a
ball.
Use
additional
flour
if too sticky.
Knead and form
ball.
Cover	with
blanket or towels and let stand until dough
rises.
Punch
once	and
let
rise again.
Dough is ready to be deep fried for small pizzelles or can be spread into pizza pan
and
covered with your favorite toppings.

title: apple taffy dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla together.
Pour mixture into bowl and top with peanuts.
This is great for a dip served with sliced apples.

title: easy chicken and rice dish
directions: Wash chicken pieces; set aside.
Place rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Spread evenly to cover bottom of pan.) Mix French onion soup with 1/2 can of water if using 1 1/2 cups rice.
Mix soup with 3/4 can of water if using 2 cups rice.
Pour evenly over rice.
Place chicken pieces on top of rice and onion soup.
Mix cream of mushroom and cream of chicken soups with 3/4 can of milk. Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.

title: cabbage and beef soup(very much like shoney's cabbage soup)
directions: Brown beef. Combine all the other ingredients, except parsley. Bring soup to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for about an hour. Garnish with parsley if desired.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Mix sugar, citric acid, water and pineapple juice.
Freeze. Just before serving, pour in the ginger ale.

title: lemon bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In dry bowl, mix cake mix and pie filling together until creamy. Pour into a 9 x 13 pan and bake 20 minutes. Cool on rack. When still warm, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake and pudding using directions on box.
Layer cool, sliced cake in a punch bowl with pudding, sliced bananas, drained pineapple, pie filling, Cool Whip and nuts.
Refrigerate.
(Best when done in 2 complete layerings, using 1/2 the ingredients in each layering).
Sprinkle top with nuts before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; drain.
Cook carrots and onions until tender; drain.
Add soup to squash, carrots and onions.
Add sour cream. Add melted margarine to the herbed stuffing mix.
Put 2/3 of stuffing mix in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add squash mixture and top with rest of stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Saute onion and garlic until tender.
Stir in bacon, sauerkraut, potatoes and parsley.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper lined baking sheet and form into a ball.
Cover with waxed paper and refrigerate until firm.
Mix cereal and caraway seed.
Dip balls in egg mixture and roll in seeds and cereal.
Deep fry.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Melt butter in a medium saucepan.
Blend flour into melted butter.
Add broth and milk gradually stirring until smooth.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add seasonings, chicken, peas and pimento to sauce.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Stir cheese into chicken mixture.
Serve over toast or biscuits or in patty shells.
Yields about 6 servings.

title: eleanor's brandy slush
directions: Combine ice tea mix and sugar with hot water to dissolve; add remaining ingredients.
Put in freezer at least 1 to 2 days before serving.
Stir several times during freezing.

title: hamburger spinach quiche(good!  makes 2 pies.)
directions: Layer the following in a 9 or 10-inch greased pie pan or plate:

title: meat pizza pie
directions: Place ground beef, milk, bread crumbs and garlic salt into a 9-inch pie pan.
Mix throughly with fork and press into shape of pie pan.
Spread sauce over meat.
Next place sliced mushrooms, pepperoni, green pepper, onions, etc.
Then top with the cheeses and lightly sprinkle with oregano.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 355°.
Cook dough 8 to 10 minutes.
After it is done, chill dough in refrigerator.
Put mixture of cream cheese and Ranch dressing on dough.
Put lettuce on first then chopped vegetables.
Includes tomatoes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let stand 1/2 to 1 hour before cooking. Drop by teaspoons into hot grease.

title: demcko's official speidies sauce
directions: Speidies are meat cubes which are marinated in this sauce, then grilled on skewers.

title: fruit salad
directions: Add 1 c. water; boil until thick.

title: slimming strawberry pudding
directions: *I have added other fruit:
bananas, peaches, etc., to blender and have added chunks of fruit before setting.

title: corn soup
directions: Combine corn, butter, onion, salt, pepper and 1 cup milk in a skillet.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Pour into blender and mix until smooth.
Stir remaining 1 cup milk into flour.
Pour into saucepan.
Add corn mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Add cream; heat thoroughly.
Serve garnished with chopped parsley or crumbled bacon.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef, taco mix and chili powder; drain.
Mix beef mixture with refried beans.
Put into a bowl, leaving a hole in the center.
Mix together sour cream and green chili sauce; pour in hole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Serve with corn chips.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Mix the flour, 1 cup sugar, milk and butter.
Pour into greased pan.
Add fruit.
On top of this, sprinkle 1 cup sugar, then pour 1 cup cold water over this. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, stirring only once after 15 minutes baking time.

title: baked rice
directions: Melt butter over rice.
Chop water chestnuts and mushrooms. Mix all ingredients and bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese bread
directions: Lightly grease 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan with "Baker's Joy".
Unroll 1 can of crescent rolls and pat them flat, covering the pan. Cream 2 packages of cream cheese with sugar and vanilla.
Spread mixture over crescent rolls.
Unroll the second can of crescent rolls and spread over cream cheese mixture and pat lightly. (Pinch dough together where it separates.)
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown.
Let cool before cutting into squares.

title: askansas hash
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in a large baking dish at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.
Uncover and add onion rings and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: european flan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small nonstick pan on medium heat, melt the 1/2 cup of sugar.
Mix sugar as it begins to melt. Cook until sugar turns colored and is completely melted.
Pour syrup all at once into a 1-quart baking dish, tilting and covering the bottom and sides of baking dish.
Put dish in a 9-inch square baking pan.
Set aside.

title: irish potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until just tender, then let get cold.
Cut potatoes into slices.
Pour oil over potatoes just enough to coat them.
Pour small amount of white vinegar over them.
Stir.
Add chopped celery and chopped onion.
Also add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix in mayonnaise as you desire.
Tastes best if left overnight.

title: mrs. james rhodes' creamed artichokes and crab(state of ohio governor's wife)
directions: Place artichoke bottoms in a square or oblong, buttered baking dish.
On each, place crabmeat and cover with rich sherry cream sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Boil carrots in salt water until tender.
Drain.
Heat, but do not boil, soup, oil, vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Chop onion, bell peppers and celery.
Add to drained carrots.
Pour soup mixture over vegetables and add black pepper to taste.
Let marinate at least 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: hamburger balls
directions: Combine salt, pepper and hamburger.
Roll into balls.
Brown balls in pan.
Put in crock-pot.
Brown flour and onion and add water and beef stew mix.
Simmer in crock-pot for 3 hours on low.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Spread pineapple in bottom of baking dish.
In small bowl, mix flour and sugar.
Sprinkle over pineapple.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Crumble Ritz crackers over cheese and pour melted butter over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry-o-cream pie
directions: Soften cheese to room temperature.
Whip until fluffy. Gradually add Eagle Brand milk, while continuing to beat until well blended.
Add lemon juice and vanilla; blend well.
Pour into crust; chill 2 to 3 hours.
Before serving, top with cherry pie filling.

title: gourmet seafood salad
directions: Mix
the
first
ingredients
in a large bowl.
Stir vinegar,
mayonnaise, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour over crab
and vegetables.
Stir until well mixed.
Chill;
garnish with chopped parsley and serve on lettuce leaves.
Great for a summer night's dinner, too.

title: blueberry pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 12-inch pizza pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, 1 cup oats and 6 tablespoons margarine.
Mix at low speed until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping.
To remaining crumbs, add egg.
Press into pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
In bowl with remaining crumbs, add 1/2 cup oats, 2 tablespoons margarine, sugar, cinnamon and chopped nuts; mix well.
Remove pan from oven.
Spread pie filling on top evenly all over.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Return to oven. Cook 15 to 20 minutes longer until lightly brown.
Cut into wedges or squares.
Enjoy.

title: parmesan puffs
directions: Mix and put on Pepperidge Farm dinner rolls.
Broil until brown on top.

title: clam casino casserole
directions: Drain clams; reserve liquid.
Chop very fine the celery, onion and pepper.
Cook bacon until crisp; put on paper towel to cool, then crumble.
Crush Ritz crackers.
Mix clams with 1/2 liquid and remaining ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole and bake until light brown and bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: In a medium bowl combine 2/3 cup sugar, butter and buttermilk.
Beat until creamy.
Add peanut butter, egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
In a medium bowl combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir into the peanut butter mixture.
Drop the dough by full teaspoons onto ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten the dough with fork dipped in the remaining sugar. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Mix together shortening, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar. Add 1 unbeaten egg, milk and vanilla.
Blend flour, soda and salt and then add to peanut butter mixture.
Shape into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 8 minutes. Remove cookies from oven and press kiss into each cookie making it look cracked.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender and not sticking together.
In a casserole dish, place the first layer of noodles on bottom.

Then spread pizza sauce on noodles (you can put pizza sauce on bottom of dish to keep them from sticking and drying out), then cheese sauce, then sprinkle meat and cheese. Do the same for approximately 3 layers.
You may want extra cheese on top.
Cook at 375° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: kiwi-strawberry spinach salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine spinach, strawberries and kiwi. In a blender combine the sugar, oil, vinegar, paprika and Worcestershire sauce. Process for 30 seconds. Add onion and seeds. Pour over salad and toss to coat. Yield 12 servings.

title: my mother-in-law's baked oatmeal(prep. time: 35 minutes)
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and press into 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with milk. Serves 4.

title: t's oyster soup
directions: Heat oyster liquor to boiling.
Add oysters and simmer until edges curl.
Scald milk.
Add butter and seasonings.
Serve hot.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture of flour, milk and sugar over butter.
Distribute the fruit and its juice evenly over the batter.
Bake 35 minutes until browned.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix all and chill (can be molded into a ball for hors d'oeuvres or on buttered bread for shrimp sandwiches).

title: mrs. shinn's cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Mix good and add sour milk.
Add rest of dry ingredients except flour and beat good. Add flour to make soft dough.
Refrigerate dough.
Roll out dough and cut cookies.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake at 400° until light brown.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Combine pineapple and coconut.
Add eggs and sugar; mix well. Sift flour with soda and salt and add to pineapple mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into 2 greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chinese cabbage salad
directions: Mix and serve.
Sunflowers may be added.
This may be made early so it can marinate.
Will keep for a week.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Use baking dish or pudding pan.
Line bottom of dish with a layer of toast cubes, then a layer of tomatoes.
Sprinkle with sugar and dot with butter.
Alternate layers until all is used. Add four drops of vanilla on top.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: sweet 'n' sour cocktail wieners
directions: Heat first two ingredients until jelly melts.
Add relish and stir well.
Add wieners.
Keep warm in crock-pot or fondue pot turned on low.

title: easy baked chicken & potato dinner
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray large baking pan with cooking spray.
Place 1 half breast in each corner.
Place potatoes, peppers and onion in center of pan. Pour melted butter over chicken and vegetables.
Sprinkle with mixture of cheese, garlic powder and paprika.
Bake for 35 - 40 minutes.
Stir vegetables halfway through cooking.

title: clam chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook for about 1 hour, if not thick enough, combine 2 Tbsp. corn starch with 1/2 cup water and add to soup, cook until it is thick enough.

title: whole wheat scones with anise
directions: In a small mixing bowl, pour enough hot water over currants to cover.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: low-fat crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate for 1 hour or until vegetables are
moistened. Serve with wheat crackers.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks and stir in condensed milk.
Add ReaLemon juice and lemon rind.
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake 8 minutes.
Chill and top with whipped cream. Garnish with a slice of lemon if desired.

title: sausage and vegetable skillet
directions: In a skillet, brown sausage, drain meat, add onion and peppers; saute until vegetables are tender.
Add potatoes and water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Yield: 2 servings.

title: tangy broiled potato slices
directions: Preheat broiler.
Slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Toss with 2 tablespoons dressing.
Place on rack in broiling pan.
Broil at closest position to heat.
Broil 15 minutes or until tender, turning once and brushing with remaining dressing.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 4.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Simmer ribs in water to cover in a large kettle for 30 minutes. Drain and arrange in a shallow nonmetal dish.
Combine sugar, mustard, salt, pepper, ginger, tomato sauce, orange juice, onion, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce in a bowl.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Pour over ribs, turning ribs to coat.
Marinate in refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Grill 6-inches from coals, 10 to 15 minutes, basting occasionally with sauce.
Turn ribs.
Baste and cook 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Bring chicken broth to boil and add onion.
Add broccoli and potato.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Puree soup in blender; add cream.
Check seasonings.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: dump it in cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in a 2 or 3-quart casserole dish.
In a bowl, mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour over oleo.
(Do not mix.) Dump in pie filling.
(Do not mix.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green pepper deer bake
directions: Place venison in baking dish; add salt and pepper.
Cover venison with green peppers, celery and onion.
Cover this with chili sauce and water.
Bake covered for 2 1/2 hours at 325°. Serve on a bed of rice.
Serves 4.

title: green chili burritos
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain, leaving a little grease in pan. Add flour to meat and brown a little more.
Add water to thicken. Add salt, pepper, garlic powder, beans, cumin, oregano and chilies.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve on flour tortillas.
Top with cheese and salsa.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Bake pie shell 15 minutes at 350°.
Spread peach pie filling in baked crust, saving 2 to 3 slices for later use.
Mix first 4 ingredients and pour over peach layer.
Add 2 to 3 peach slices and slivered almonds on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion in a 400° oven for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally; drain well.
Add celery, soy sauce, soup, water and rice; mix well.
Bake, uncovered, in a 9 x 13-inch pan or small roasting pan for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Five minutes before removing casserole from oven, top with rice noodles (and, if desired, cashew nuts and mandarin orange slices).

title: meat balls
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, egg, milk, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Make it into balls.
Mix catsup, chopped onions and vinegar.
Place meat balls in this mixture and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: dutch meat loaf
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Peel and chop onion fine.
Beat egg until bubbly.
Add all ingredients to ground beef.
Mix lightly, but thoroughly, with a fork.
Pack mixture into 9 x 5 x3-inch loaf pan.
Pour 1/2 of sauce (recipe follows) over meat loaf.
Bake 1 1/2 hours, then add remaining sauce and cook 5 more minutes.

title: one-pan macaroni and cheese
directions: Leave drained macaroni in cooking pan.
Mix water and dry milk.
Add to macaroni.
Add cheese.
Cook over low heat, and stir gently, until cheese melts.
Let stand a few minutes after cooking for a thicker sauce, if desired.
For thinner sauce, add a little water.
Makes 2 servings, 1/2 cup each.

title: old-fashioned cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, soda, baking powder and salt; stir in eggs and buttermilk.
Heat bacon drippings in an 8-inch cast-iron skillet until very hot.
Add drippings to batter and mix well. Pour batter into hot skillet and bake at 450° for about 25 minutes.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings, cut into pie shaped pieces.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Blend softened cream cheese, milk, lemon juice and vanilla with beater.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill 4 hours.
Just before serving, top with fruit.

title: mom's beef stew
directions: Cut meat into 1 inch pieces.
Roll in blended salt, pepper, paprika, and flour to coat each piece.
Then brown the meat in the fat in a large pot.
This browning gives rich, brown gravy and extra flavor to the meat.
Add water and seasonings.
Cover tightly and simmer about 2 hours.
(DO NOT BOIL) Add the vegetables.
Cover and cook another 30 mintes or until the vegetables are tender.
Add peas the last 15 minutes of cooking. If the broth is too thin, thicken it with 1 tablespoon of flour, mixed with 1/4 cup cold water.
Boil, stir, and taste.

title: mickey mouse pancakes
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk and beat well.
Melt butter and add to egg/milk mixture while stirring.
Stir together other ingredients except flour.
Add to egg/milk mixture.
Gradually add flour to desired thickness.
Spoon 2 tablespoons of batter for ears (1 tablespoon each) onto moderately heated griddle.
Let cook for about 15 seconds, then connect the ears with a big circle of batter for the face.
Bake on the griddle until the cakes are full of bubbles on the top.
Turn with a spatula and brown the other sides.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together eggs and oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake on center rack for 45 minutes.

title: pimientos cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer.

title: cheezy hamburger dip
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet until done, then drain.
Put hamburger into crock-pot.
Add cheese and tomato sauce, stirring occasionally.
When cheese has completely melted, dip is ready.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil, take off stove; add next 4 ingredients, then add nuts.
Mix well and drop on wax paper. Let cool.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Grease baking pan or spray with cooking spray; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; beat well.
Remove 1 1/2 cups batter; reserve for cupcakes.
Pour remaining cake batter into prepared baking pan.

title: sausage and apple quiche
directions: Separate crescent rolls.
Place points to center in a 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Press roll dough to cover pie plate; crimp edges.
Bake shell at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: butter browned potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut each into 6 slices; dry.
Coat in butter on cookie sheet.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake covered at 350° in single layer 20 minutes.
Uncover, baste and bake 30 minutes more.

title: german apple cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel apples.
Core and slice thinly.
In bowl, toss apple slices with 5 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Set aside (best if it sets overnight).
In large mixing bowl, mix flour, sugar, salt, eggs, oil, vanilla, orange juice, baking soda and baking powder.
With electric mixer, blend together at low speed for 1 minute.
Clean side of bowl with rubber spatula. Increase speed to medium and blend for 3 minutes.
You will have a very thick dough.
Fill prepared pan with alternating layers of batter apples, making a total of 3 batter and 2 apple layers. Start and finish with batter.
Bake 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours at 350°. Insert cake tester to make sure cake is done.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes, then invert cake and remove pan.

title: nightcap peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well and bake at 325° on ungreased cookie sheet for 13 minutes.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together. Cut in shortening. Mix milk, egg and vinegar together. Add all at once and stir until moistened. Roll out. Makes 2 crusts.

title: oreo pudding cake
directions: In 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan:

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into slices.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Pour milk in dish.
Place cut potatoes on bottom, then dice ham.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour or until potatoes are soft.

title: taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease square baking dish.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion in skillet; drain.
Stir in seasoning and spoon into a plate.
Beat Bisquick, milk and eggs with a wire whisk or hand beater until almost smooth, about 1 minute.
Pour onto plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Garnish with lettuce and tomatoes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: southwest taco pie
directions: Bake pie shell at 400° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350°. Cool pie shell.
In frying pan, brown meat and onion, then drain off grease.
In a small pan, heat beans and 1/2 jar of taco sauce. Mix taco seasoning and 3/4 cup of water together; pour into pan with meat mixture and simmer.
Place meat mixture in pie shell, then top with refried bean mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top until pie is covered.
Place in oven and cook until cheese is melted. Serve with lettuce, tomato and sour cream.

title: raisin pecan pie
directions: Combine butter and sugar in saucepan.
Cover over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Cool 5 minutes.
Stir in eggs and next 5 ingredients.
Pour into prepared pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until pie is set.
Top with whipped cream, if desired, and serve.

title: tara's orange juice coffee cake
directions: Crumble flour, sugar and margarine until mixture is like cornmeal.
Set aside 1 cup of this mixture along with the cinnamon for the topping.
Add baking powder to rest of mixture and blend well.
Beat eggs, blend with orange juice and mix lightly into crumb mixture.
Pour into greased 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle the 1 cup of crumb mixture over batter.
Sprinkle cinnamon over crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pineapple coconut balls
directions: Combine sugar and shortening in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until blended well.
Beat in egg.
Mix in pineapple.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add gradually to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in coconut and nuts with spoon.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart onto greased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack and enjoy.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: cream of swiss cheese and onion soup
directions: Saute the onion and the dried herbs for 2 minutes.
Add potatoes, carrot, celery or broccoli stems, garlic and bay leaf. Continue to saute for 2 to 3 minutes more.
Add enough water to vegetables and cook until the vegetables are tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Take out the bay leaf and puree the mixture in a blender or food processor until smooth.
Return to the pot.
Add milk, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup sliced vegetables and cook for 10 more minutes or until the vegetables are tender.
If the mixture is too thick, adjust with addition of milk or water.
Serve with fresh chopped herb.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in a greased casserole.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions and butter, then add remainder of ingredients and simmer.
Toast French bread with garlic salt.
When simmered and ready to eat, pour soup in bowl.
Top with toasted bread and layer 2 slices or more of sliced Swiss cheese.
Put under broiler and melt cheese.
Enjoy!

title: baked cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower just until tender in lightly salted water. Heat can of soup (undiluted).
Drain water off of cauliflower; pour soup over cauliflower.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Toast bread and crumble over top.
Cut up margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream 2 sticks butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla in bowl.
Add sugar, 1/3 cup at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in next 2 ingredients, mixing well.
Add flour, 1/3 cup at a time, alternately with buttermilk, beating well after each addition, beginning and ending with flour.
Combine soda and vinegar.
Add to batter, mixing well.
Pour into 3 prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Melt marshmallows in condensed milk over very low heat until melted.
Add the remaining ingredients. Mix well and place in one large or two small cake tins lined with waxed paper.
Wet hands with warm water and pack well.
Place pecan halves on top if desired.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine the mayonnaise, curry powder, soy sauce, lemon juice and pineapple tidbits.
Mix all ingredients and chill several hours before serving.
(Better made a day ahead.)

title: chocolate brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Melt chocolate and butter over hot water bath (not on direct heat).
Beat eggs, sugar, chocolate mixture and corn syrup together.
Mix in pecans and pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until set.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Boil chicken until tender and remove from bone.
Add chopped bell pepper, onion and celery.
Mix in remaining ingredients and cook for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Cut and clean peppers.
Wear rubber gloves.
Leave in a few seeds.
Chop in food processor.
Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: corn souffle
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Mix in eggs, butter, milk and corn.
Fold in spices.
Pour into greased 3-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes, until top is golden brown and center is firm.
Serve as either main course or side dish.

title: simple pot roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with garlic powder to taste.
In a Dutch oven kettle, brown roast on all sides in a little oil.
Add beef stock. Mix dry onion soup mix with soup and pour over roast.
Cover and cook on low heat until tender.
You may have to add a little water or beef stock as it cooks.
You may add whole onions, carrots and mushrooms while the meat is cooking.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour half of batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: layered jello salad
directions: Dissolve 1 package of Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Take out 1/2 cup. Stir into 1/3 cup sour cream.

title: albondigas soup
directions: Mix pork, beef, salt and pepper together.
Shape into as many 2-inch balls as it will make.
Fry these in a skillet until browned on all sides.
In a large pot, add carrots, celery, onion, cabbage wedges, garlic, meatballs, tomatoes, corn, broth and water.
Simmer until done.
You may vary the vegetables to suit your taste.

title: dried beef cream cheese ball
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften.
Finely chop green onions.
Use scissors and cut dried beef in small pieces.
Mix together well; use your hands.
Form a ball; wrap in Saran Wrap.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Serve with crackers or bagels.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Drain pineapple.
Put pineapple in bottom of dish.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 5 teaspoons flour together and put on top of pineapple, then put grated cheese on top of that. Crush Ritz crackers and put 3/4 cup on top of cheese.
Melt butter and pour over Ritz crackers.
Pour pineapple juice on top of this. Sprinkle rest of Ritz crackers on top.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: family-style meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except tomato sauce; mix well.
Shape mixture into loaf and place in baking pan.
Cover with tomato sauce.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for about 1 hour.
The tomato sauce makes a tasty gravy for the meat loaf.

title: simon's favorite guacamole dip
directions: Peel ripe avocado (ripe when slightly soft, indents to touch!) Smash avocado thoroughly with a fork or in food processor.
Grate 1 clove garlic and add to avocado.
Squeeze 1/2 lemon into mixture; add 1/2 cup plain yogurt and salsa if desired.
Mix thoroughly.
Serve with corn chips and your favorite Mexican dish!

title: baked hash browns
directions: Place potatoes in 9 x 13-inch greased dish.
Mix soup and sour cream; cover potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Mix butter and corn flakes, pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cottage pudding
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and eggs until light. Add milk and flour.
Bake in two layers, putting together with whipped cream and shredded orange.

title: vivian's appetizer
directions: Fix ahead of time.
Brown sausage and ground beef; drain.
Add Velveeta.
Stir until cheese is blended well.
Put about 1 teaspoon of mixture on a slice of bread; place on cookie sheet (freeze).
Broil until bread is toasted; serve hot.

title: gourmet casserole
directions: Cook the noodles.
Brown onions in margarine, then saute ground beef.
Make 1 layer of noodles, then the meat, parsley, almonds, cheese and repeat the layers again.
Cover top with chow mein noodles.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12. Especially good for church.

title: grandma's cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and oatmeal; set aside.
Cream butter, white sugar and brown sugar together.
Add to creamed ingredients eggs and vanilla.
Add the dry ingredients to creamed ingredients and mix.
Add chocolate chips.
Make golf ball sized cookies.
Do not press.
Bake at 375°.
Makes 75 cookies.

title: pickled corn
directions: Mix above ingredients in pan (as many times as you need to cover corn). Put on stove and stir well; bring to a boil. Cook corn as if for eating approximately 10 minutes after it starts to boil. Put in a crock and put vinegar mixture over top. Cover with a cloth and tie with a string. Take scum off as it develops.

title: yellow summer squash with cheese
directions: Preheat broiler to high.
Rinse the squash and pat dry.
Trim off the ends of the squash.
Cut the squash into thin rounds. Heat the oil in a large heavy skillet and add the squash, shaking the skillet to distribute the squash evenly.
Add the salt and pepper to taste and cook over high heat 4 minutes.
Sprinkle with oregano and toss to blend well.
Remove the garlic and discard. Transfer the squash to a flameproof serving dish, piling it up and smoothing the surface to make it flat.
Sprinkle with the cheese. Place the dish under the broiler and cook briefly until the cheese is lightly browned.

title: chicken with broccoli and cheese
directions: Over medium heat in hot margarine, cook chicken for 10 minutes, or until brown on both sides.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Add broccoli; reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer for 10 to 15 minutes, until chicken is tender and broccoli is done.

title: sumi salad
directions: Toast almonds in 400° oven.
Brown sesame seed in butter.
Add almonds to coat with butter.

title: almond-chicken casserole
directions: Mix together.
Put into a shallow style baking dish.
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot-apple cider sipper
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil in a Dutch oven; reduce heat, and simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove cinnamon sticks.
Serve hot. Makes about 21 cups.

title: cocoa drop cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add cottage cheese and vanilla; beat thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each is added.
Sift together flour, cocoa, soda, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before taking off cookie sheet.
When cool, frost with icing, if desired.

title: heart warming tea mix
directions: Combine ingredients; blend well. Store in a container. To make 1 serving, use 1 rounded tablespoon Heart Warming Tea Mix with 3/4 cup boiling water. Stir until mix is dissolved.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: May be easily multiplied.

title: congo squares
directions: Stir dry ingredients.
Mix sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, beating one minute after each.
Add dry ingredients, nuts and chocolate bits.
Turn mixture into 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: best sugar cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar with a spoon.
Beat in egg, oil and vanilla.
Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt; stir into butter mixture.
Chill dough 1 hour, or until easy to handle.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet; flatten to 1/4 inch with tines of fork.
Dip fork in sugar.
Bake in a 375° oven for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes about 40.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
When brown on all sides, remove.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Serve over rice or spaghetti.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Combine margarine, brown sugar and corn syrup; melt in microwave for 4 minutes.
Mix lightly with cereal.
Pat mixture into buttered pie pan and freeze.
Combine chocolate syrup, peanut butter and corn syrup.
Spread onto crust.
Freeze until firm. Soften ice cream a bit, then spoon into crust.
Drizzle syrup over top.
Makes 1 pie.

title: colorado chocolate cake
directions: *To sour milk, add 1 tablespoon of vinegar to sweet milk.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix ingredients together; add cinnamon and pats of butter on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in 1-quart ovenproof bowl. Delicious with ham dinner.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine
and beat to spreading consistency.
Will frost two 9-inch layers or tube cake.

title: wynn's breakfast casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray.
Sprinkle bread cubes on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle bacon over bread.
Next, sprinkle cheese on.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper. Pour over other ingredients.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in the morning for 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan 35 to 45 minutes. Add chopped nuts, if desired.

title: no bake brownies
directions: Use 3-quart saucepan.
Put milk, marshmallows, chocolate pieces, sugar and salt into pan and cook over medium heat to full all over boil.
Boil and stir 5 minutes more.
Take off heat and stir in butter, vanilla, graham crumbs and nuts.
Press mixture into buttered 9-inch square pan.
Chill 1 hour or until set. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 24 squares.

title: unbaked fudge cookies(24 to 30)
directions: Boil sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes.
Start timing after the mixture reaches a full rolling boil.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, oatmeal, vanilla and nuts, if used.
Beat until blended, then drop on wax paper by teaspoonful.
Coconut or dates may be added, if desired.

title: rhonda's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except ketchup, brown sugar and prepared mustard.
Spread in ungreased loaf pan.
Mix ketchup, brown sugar and prepared mustard.
Spread over meat loaf mixture.
Cook in a 350° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.
Delicious!!

title: fresh banana cooler
directions: Place banana, honey and a small amount of the milk in a blender container; cover and puree until almost smooth.
Add remaining milk and ice cream.
Blend about 1 minute or until smooth and frothy.
This makes 2 servings.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine the dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat; do not use mixer.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool; remove from pans.
Cool completely.
Frost between layers, on top and sides with frosting.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine crumbs, 2 tablespoons of Parmesan cheese, oregano, garlic and pepper.
Roll chicken in mixture.
Arrange in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Turn chicken; bake 20 minutes more.
Blend soup and milk and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with paprika and remaining cheese.
Bake 20 minutes more or until done.

title: pumpkin or sweet potato cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Combine sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin or potatoes.
Add dry ingredients to mixture.
Bake in 350° oven in 1 pound coffee cans.
It will make 3 loaves.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Grease casserole.
Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole.
Top with buttery cracker crumbs.
Bake in a 400° oven for 25 minutes.

title: crescent roll chicken
directions: Chop chicken; toss with poultry seasoning.
Spread chicken on each roll of dough.
Roll up and place in ungreased casserole pan. Mix milk with soup; pour over rolls.
Cook for 25 minutes at 350°.
When rolls are brown, take out of oven and cover with grated cheese.
Serve hot.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain juice off crushed pineapple.
Add enough water to make 2 cups; put in medium saucepan.
Add marshmallows and cream cheese. Cook over medium heat until cheese and marshmallows melt, using a whisk to blend.
Remove from heat.
Stir in jello, blending with the whisk.
Cool on counter for 15 to 20 minutes.
In a mixing bowl, blend jello mixture, crushed pineapple, oranges (keep about 8 out to decorate the top) and Cool Whip.
Pour into a pretty glass bowl; place the 8 oranges for top.
Refrigerate; serve when set.

title: tenderloin biscuits
directions: Take tenderloin and slice into 1/4 to 1/2-inch pieces. Preheat pan with olive oil and butter.
Dip tenderloin slices into flour.
Place in pan.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until brown on both sides.
Slice open cooked biscuits.
Place a slice of tenderloin on each biscuit.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes whole with skins and cool.
While potatoes are cooking, clean and cook carrots and cool.
Cook eggs and cool. Chop potatoes with egg slicer.
Chop eggs, carrots, onion and green onion.
Grate celery, radishes and pickles.
Put in very large bowl.
In separate bowl, mix sauce ingredients.
Then add sauce ingredients to potatoes and mix thoroughly.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except sour cream.
Fold in the sour cream.
Use as dip for raw vegetables, such as cucumbers, green pepper strips, cauliflower, celery, carrots and green onions.

title: a different punch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Then add sherbet one scoop at a time. Wait tell it dissolves and stir well.

title: crunchy salad
directions: Mix slaw, chopped onion and chicken in large bowl.
Mix together salad dressing and seasoning mix out of Ramen noodles. Pour over slaw.
Before serving, crunch noodles and sprinkle over the top, then top with sunflower seeds.

title: apple squares
directions: Mix together.
Batter will be thick.
Spread on greased jelly roll pan with 1/2-inch edge.
Glaze with confectioners sugar while warm.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Before measuring sweet potatoes, mash through sieve to remove strings.
In large bowl mix potatoes, sugar, eggs, butter, milk and nutmeg.
Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients well.
Add vanilla and lemon extract last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 425° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup milk over low heat.
Combine cake mix, margarine and remaining 1/3 cup milk.
Pat half the dough into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Pour the melted caramel mixture over the baked dough.
Sprinkle the walnuts over the caramel mixture and then sprinkle the chocolate chips. Drop by spoonfuls the remaining dough to cover mixture.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream together cocoa, sugar and shortening.
Add and mix eggs. Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk and vanilla.
Add boiling water last.
Pour batter into three 8 x 1 1/2-inch pans or loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press firmly into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Chop onion & ham in small pieces. Mix with cream cheese and Worcestershire sauce; mix well. Place in refrigerator overnight or for several hours. Roll into ball and cover with chopped pecans. Serve with Club Crackers.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening/butter.
Add eggs.
Mix 1 1/2 cups flour with baking powder.
Add rest of flour alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Use Bundt or angel food cake pans which you have greased and lightly floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not preheat oven - start with cold oven.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water over heat.
Fold in nuts, strawberries and pineapple.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until set.
Can be served with a dollop of sour cream.

title: mex dip(appetizer or supper dish)
directions: Chop up onion and brown with hamburger and drain.
Cut up cheese into chunks and put in crock-pot.
Add everything else to crock-pot and cook on high for 1 hour or until cheese is melted. Cook on low for 2 more hours.
Serve with corn chips.

title: cold pea salad
directions: Cook and drain peas.
Allow to cool.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Chill before serving.
Season to taste.

title: nutty cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Drain pineapple.
Mix cream cheese, pineapple, pepper, onion, salt and 1/2 of the pecans.
Chill overnight.
Make into a ball and cover with remaining pecans.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cool, then rip apart.
Mix broth with cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Layer chicken with sauce mix.
On top, spread mixture of Ritz crumbs, melted butter and poppy seed.

title: brode's spaghetti dish
directions: Melt a pound of Velveeta cheese and add a can of Rotel, mild or hot.
Boil and cube chicken breasts, mix together.
Cook spaghetti as directed on package. Add all of the ingredients together.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Pour in casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Allow to cool slightly.
Mix together with remaining ingredients until well moistened (don't beat).
Pour into a greased square pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Drop by tablespoons.
Sprinkle top with sugar.
Bake about 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.
Bake one to test for time and texture.

title: maryland salad
directions: Layer in a large bowl:
lettuce, bacon, onion, cauliflower, mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese.
Cover and chill overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Saute onion and butter.
Boil giblets until done.
Add onions, salt, pepper, parsley and one bay leaf.
Save juice from giblets and drippings from turkey.
Also, add celery, chopped fine.

title: pineapple gelatin salad
directions: Heat and stir pineapple, lemon juice, and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Soak Knox gelatin in water for 10 minutes.
Add to hot mixture above.
Cool and add cheese and Cool Whip.
Stir together and pour into an 8 x 12 inch pyrex dish or gelatin mold.

title: tuna pie
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Cover loosely.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Uncover; let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix everything, except coconut, together in mixer or blender. Add coconut.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan (greased).
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes a 350°.

title: no knead bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
In saucepan, add the water, milk and oil and heat until very warm; do not boil.
Mix with dry ingredients and add 1 beaten egg.
Mix with mixer for 2 minutes. Stir in flour by hand.
Cover and let rise (about 1 hour).
Punch down and put in greased loaf pan.
Wet fingertips and smooth down. Bake at 375° for about 50 minutes.

title: auntie sherri's pork chop casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir to wet rice.
Push in pork chops.
Cook, covered, for one hour.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt together in bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add water, a little at a time, until mixture is moist and pulls together easily.
Cover with damp cloth or plastic wrap and let stand for a few minutes.
Flour and roll out pastry to 1/8-inch thick or less.
Place in 9-inch pie pan and trim 1-inch larger than pan.
Flute edge or fold under.
Chill in the freezer for 30 minutes.
Fill crust and bake.

title: pudding bars
directions: Prepare box of pudding according to box.
Add 1 box dry cake mix; mix well.
Add chips or nuts or whatever; mix.
Place on a cookie sheet or in a pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; refrigerate.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten egg yolks.
Alternately add 2 cups flour and extract.
Dredge fruit, nuts and raisins in remaining flour. Add to batter.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 250° for about 5 hours in large tube pan.
Place a pan of water on the bottom of oven rack.
Remove from pan when completely cool.
Wrap tightly with foil and store in the refrigerator.

title: shrimp scampie
directions: If small shrimp, saute in sauce of listed ingredients.
If jumbo shrimp, cook 2/3 done before adding them to the sauce.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients to make marinade.
Add chicken. Refrigerate for 3 to 6 hours.
Cook on grill to desired doneness.

title: mexican skillet dinner
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water.
Brown hamburger and onions together.
Drain fat.
Add macaroni, bell pepper, tomatoes, sugar, salt and chili powder.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add sour cream and simmer 5 minutes.
Do not boil after adding sour cream.

title: hamburger dish
directions: Brown onion and meat.
Drain.
Add beans and soup.
Put in casserole and put balls of mashed potatoes on top.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Cut stew meat up and brown. Cover with stock. Add chopped carrots, celery and onion.
Cook until almost done and add cabbage.
Add the undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, garbanzos, pork and beans and macaroni. Add Parmesan cheese, parsley, oregano to taste, salt, pepper and frozen spinach, thawed.
Makes a lot of soup.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger; add onion, garlic, bay leaves, salt, pepper and red pepper while meat is browning.
Add tomato paste and tomato juice.
Use juice to desired consistency.
Simmer.

title: "cream cheese pound cake"
directions: Blend butter and cream cheese. Add sugar. Add flour and salt. Add flavorings separately. Add eggs last. Do not preheat oven. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or bake at 320° for 1 1/2 hours. Baking time is not precise; depends on your oven. "Good Eating."

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put all casserole ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: daddy's oil and vinegar dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Do not beat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir.
Place in casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pig in a blanket
directions: Take 2 biscuits, wrap around hot dog.
Lay in ungreased pan and bake at 350° until biscuit is brown.

title: sam's fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together well in a large bowl.
Pour into 12 cup tube pan, well-greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let sit in pan for 20 minutes, then remove.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend milk and cream cheese.
Add cool whip and nuts.
Use for: whole strawberries, apple slices, celery sticks, banana slices, vanilla wafers, graham crackers, etc....

title: lemon berry pie
directions: With wire whisk, beat cream cheese and 1 tablespoon milk with sugar until smooth.
Stir in lemon peel and juice.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of Cool Whip.
Spread evenly into crust.
Press berries into cream cheese mixture, but reserve some for garnish.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Chill milk.
Whip milk with electric mixer; add lemon juice and mix with spoon.
Fold in Cool Whip, then add pineapple.
Pour into cool pie shell.
Chill 2 hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: hot chili dip
directions: Blend lightly, using all the juices.
Good with chips, eggs or hamburgers.

title: black magic cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. (Batter will be thin.)
Scrape sides of bowl, beat 2 more minutes.

title: southern hush puppies
directions: Scald cornmeal, salt and shortening.
Blend in onion, parsley and Tabasco sauce.
Shape into football shapes.
Fry in deep, hot fat until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: rolls
directions: Combine hot water, salt and sugar; mix well.
Add egg; cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and flour; mix well.
Put in a greased bowl and place in refrigerator or allow to rise and shape rolls.
Bake.

title: antipasto roll-ups
directions: Mash together tuna, egg,
mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Set aside.

title: homemade kolaches
directions: Boil sausage 10 minutes; drain.
Roll out or pat each biscuit to twice the original size.
Cut biscuit in half.
Wrap a sausage in each half biscuit.
Place on greased baking pan.
Melt butter or oleo and brush on top of each one.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat peanut butter and butter with electric mixer.
Add eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in flour.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating good after each egg.
Sift flour; measure.
Add baking powder; sift 3 times.
Add flour and milk alternately beating well after each addition; add vanilla.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: strawberry-banana salad
directions: Add boiling water to Jell-O and dissolve well. Add frozen strawberries and stir until separated.
Add mashed bananas and pineapple.
Mix well and refrigerate until thick, but not set. Pour half of the mixture into mold. Spread sour cream over. Add remaining Jell-O
on top. Refrigerate overnight or several hours.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook until onions are tender.
Remove onions and set aside.
Add more oil if needed; brown chicken for 15 minutes.
Return onions; add rest of ingredients except rice and cook for 30 minutes, covered. Chicken is done when easily pierced with a fork.
Remove bay leaves and serve over hot rice.

title: red leaf lettuce salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except lettuce, bacon and cottage cheese.
Chill 2 hours or overnight.
Tear lettuce.
Pour on dressing and spread cottage cheese and bacon throughout.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Cook beef in skillet until lightly browned; drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in catsup and tomato sauce.
Heat thoroughly.

title: pumpkin squares
