directions: Mix all ingredients except pumpkin until blended.
Add pumpkin.
Cook in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan for 30 minutes or less.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook whole chicken on top of stove simmering until done.
Also add the onion and celery.
After chicken is cooked and cooled, bone and cut into small pieces.
Place in bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Then heat in pot 1 cup of the chicken broth, 1 can cream of chicken soup and 1 can cream of celery or cream of mushroom soup. When hot, pour over chicken.
Prepare Stove Top stuffing, according to directions.
Then sprinkle over casserole.
Bake in oven for approximately 1/2 hour at 350°, uncovered.
This can be served over rice, noodles or plain.

title: pie crust cookies
directions: Roll out dough to thickness of pie crust.
Cut out shapes with small cookie cutters.
Poke holes in cookies with a fork.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 375 degrees for 8 - 10 minutes.

title: congo bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put margarine into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan and put in oven to melt.
Remove pan from oven and stir in graham cracker crumbs.
Press crumbs into an even layer with rubber spatula.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumb layer.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Press down with fingertips.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until golden.
Let cool on wire rack.
Cut into 24 squares.
Makes 12 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and onion, seasoned with salt and pepper. Drain.
Mix with chicken and mushroom soups, evaporated milk, green chilies and enchilada sauce.
Layer all ingredients, beginning with meat mixture and ending with Doritos and cheese. Place in a large greased casserole dish or 2 small dishes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, cinnamon, allspice and cloves.
Alternating sour cream and combined dry ingredients, add to creamed mixture.
Add jam.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: stuffed shells
directions: In a medium bowl, combine egg, cheeses, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cook and drain pasta according to package directions. Rinse and drain.
Spoon cheese mixture into pasta shells.
Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Cover pasta shells with sauce.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: mustardy fried chicken breasts
directions: Cut up the chicken breast in wedge style, like hot dogs.
Wipe chicken breast with damp paper towel.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In a bowl, beat together the egg and mustard.
In another separate bowl, combine the Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then roll in cheese mixture until evenly coated.
Let this set for about 10 minutes.
Saute chicken on both sides in heated oil or margarine for 10 to 20 minutes until tender.

title: native succotash soup
directions: Cover beans and hominy 8 hours or overnight.
Drain.
Discard liquid.

In 6 to 8-quart Dutch oven, combine beans, hominy (if using canned hominy, add last 30 minutes of cooking), chicken broth, garlic, carrots, onion, artichokes, ham, sausage, parsley, sage and rosemary.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 2 hours until beans are tender.
Add canned hominy, if using.
Remove ham and sausage.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Return to soup. Season to taste.

title: sangria
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, add slices of lime, orange and lemon.

title: no cook salsa
directions: Stir together and chill.

title: creamy pecan pie
directions: Combine crumbs, butter and 1/3 cup chopped pecans in small bowl.
Mix. Reserve 2 tablespoons of mixture of topping.
Press crumbs in bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan.
Chill for 20 minutes.

title: quick caramel rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease casserole dish.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag.
Cut biscuits into quarters and place in bag and shake well.
Arrange in casserole.
Melt butter and brown sugar and pour over biscuits.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in baking dish.
After 10 minutes, turn upside down onto platter.
Serve warm.

title: apple salad
directions: Peel and dice apples into pieces.
Mix all ingredients. Chill.

title: cheese stuffed pasta shells
directions: In 2-quart casserole, crumble ground beef.
Cook in microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes until meat is no longer pink, stirring after half the cooking time.
Drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on High 4 to 6 minutes, stirring after half the cooking time.
In a medium bowl, combine Ricotta and Parmesan cheeses, eggs, pepper, 1 1/2 cups Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Stuff manicotti with cheese filling.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, arrange manicotti in single layer; add meat sauce to completely cover. Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella.
Cover dish with plastic wrap. Cook on Medium-high for 30 to 35 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn during cooking.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: date-nut cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat butter to soften.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in flour mixture. Stir in dates and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons into corn flakes and roll until covered.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten slightly and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: sausage stars
directions: Spray miniature cupcake tins with Pam.
Push wontons in cups and spray again lightly.
Bake wontons at 350° for about 4 to 7 minutes.
Watch.

title: grandma olga's applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a bowl, cream together sugar and butter.
In second bowl, mix soda with water.
Add applesauce. Add this to the butter mixture. Stir. Add dry ingredients, including spices.
Blend together well.
Mix in raisins.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of cake. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Blend together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers or chips.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar, flour, cornstarch and dash of salt.
Gradually stir in 1 1/2 cups water.
Stir over medium-high heat until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce and cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Separate egg yolks and set the whites aside for meringue.
Add yolks to mixture and bring to a gentle boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add butter, lemon peel and lemon juice.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large tub pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crunchy jumble cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Measure butter or margarine and sugar into large mixing bowl.
Beat until well blended and smooth.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients; mix until combined.
Stir in Rice Krispies, chocolate morsels and raisins.
Drop by level measuring teaspoonful onto lightly greased baking pans.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 12 minutes or lightly brown.
Remove immediately from baking sheets.
Cool on wire racks.

title: filet de boeuf roti(roast filet of beef)
directions: Rub a trimmed filet of beef with butter and with pepper to taste.
Roast it in a moderately hot oven (375°) for 25 to 35 minutes, depending on the size of the filet.
Baste frequently with hot beef stock for the first 15 minutes, then with the juices from the pan for the remaining roasting time, being careful not to let juices burn.
(Medium is 160° on meat thermometer.)

title: swedish love knots
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together; cut in butter.
Add vanilla to the eggs and beat until light and frothy.
Mix thoroughly into flour mixture (if eggs are large, add just enough flour so dough can be handled).
Knead on lightly floured board for 3 minutes.
Roll dough about 1/8-inch thick and cut with floured knife into strips 1 1/2-inches wide and 4-inches long. Make a slash 1-inch long in center of each piece.
Lift and carefully slip one end through the slit.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs in large bowl.
Add apples and stir.
Add nuts, flour, salt, soda and spices.
Stir well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan which has been greased and the bottom lined with waxed paper.
Put cake into cold oven. Turn temperature to 325°.
Turn oven on and bake 1 hour or until done.
Ice with Penuche Icing.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix juice, rice, pepper, shrimp and onion.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs (mixed with melted margarine).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Shred chicken. Butter a 13 x 9 casserole dish. Crush Doritos and layer bottom of dish. Layer shredded chicken on top of Doritos. Mix Ro-Tel, soups, and milk. Spread soup mixture over chicken. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nubbins cheese dip
directions: Put 1/2 of corned beef into cheese mixture.
Use the rest to roll the cheese ball in.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Prepare carrots; cool slightly. Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over carrots. Refrigerate 24 hours before serving. Use as relish with meats.

title: flavored popcorn snack variations
directions: Melt butter and salt in a small saucepan before adding one of the following:

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Mix all 5 ingredients and chill 30 minutes before serving.

title: jello cake
directions: Bake yellow cake.
Cool.
Punch holes with fork.
Spoon Jell-O mixture over cake (Jell-O and water).
For topping, mix Cool Whip, vanilla pudding, cold milk and vanilla.
Refrigerate.

title: szechwan spareribs
directions: Trim and discard excess fat from ribs; cut between bones into individual pieces.
Heat 2 tablespoons of the oil in a wide frying pan over high heat.
Add ribs and cook, stirring often, until browned (about 4 minutes).
Remove from pan from heat and let cool briefly.
Add water and soy and return pan to low heat; cover and simmer until ribs are fork-tender (about 30 minutes).
Meanwhile, prepare cooking sauce and set aside.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes or until firm in a 350° oven.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add milk and continue beating until well mixed.
Add 2 cups of water and flavor.
Put into pot and heat until hot, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add favorite fruits or nuts and freeze.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cream butter or margarine with sugar until fluffy in a large bowl.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on rack.
Wrap and store overnight for easier slicing.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon pie filling on top.
Dump in cake mix; dot top with butter. Sprinkle with chopped nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Soften the cream cheese and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan, preferably glass.
Mix all remaining ingredients and spread on top of cream cheese.
Top with Monterey Jack and Cheddar cheeses. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour; warm in microwave if necessary.

title: bacon vegetable soup
directions: Fry bacon until fully cooked and crisp.
Get medium-size pot. Put all vegetables in pot.
Heat for 15 minutes on medium-high. Then put in bacon with bacon oil.
Mix all together in the pot and serve.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Cook eggs, milk, sugar, oleo and vanilla until thick like pudding, about 12 to 15 minutes. Add coconut and pecans. Cool and spread.

title: calico pickles
directions: Combine vegetables in a large bowl. Dissolve salt in water and pour over vegetables. Soak for 15 to 18 hours in a cool place; drain. In a large kettle, mix sugar, spices and vinegar. Bring to a boil; boil for 3 to 4 minutes. Add vegetables and simmer 5 to 7 minutes. Pack hot into 8 hot pint jars, leaving 1/4 inch headspace. Remove air bubbles.
Adjust caps and process 15 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: perfect cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in cornmeal. Add eggs, milk and shortening. Beat just until smooth. Pour into a greased pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes until lightly brown or toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: claudia's divinity
directions: Place the sugar, corn syrup and water in saucepan over low heat.
Stir until sugar is dissolved, then cook to 225° (a little dropped into cold water forms a hard ball).
Remove from heat; pour, beating constantly, in a fine stream into 3 egg whites. Continue beating until mixture holds its shape and loses its gloss.
Add the vanilla and broken nuts.
Drop quickly from tip of buttered spoon onto waxed paper in individual peaks.

title: no cook cucumber pickles
directions: Mix sugar, salt, celery seed, turmeric and vinegar, then pour over cucumbers, green peppers and onions.
Put in quart jars and refrigerate.
Makes approximately three quarts.
Keeps all winter.

title: evelyn's low-fat bran muffins
directions: Mix together dry ingredients. Mix buttermilk, egg and oil together and add to dry ingredients. Let sit in refrigerator overnight. May be stored in fridge up to 6 weeks. Take out what you want and leave the rest in the refrigerator. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour filling in pie shell. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Filling will become firm as it cools.
Allow pie to cool before cutting.

title: shrimp with cream cheese
directions: Layer on crackers:
2 packages cream cheese mixed with milk to cream it, onion, shrimp and egg.
Salt and pepper between layers.

title: cookie brittle
directions: Combine margarine, vanilla and salt; blend well.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in flour.
Add chocolate chips and 3/4 cup nuts; mix well.
Press evenly into ungreased 15 x 10-inch pan. Spread remaining 1/4 cup nuts over top and press lightly.
Bake at 375° about 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool, then break into irregular pieces.
Makes about 2 pounds of crisp cookies.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken and remove from broth when done. Debone chicken. Cook broccoli and drain. Cook spaghetti in chicken broth (do not drain). Add cooked broccoli, chicken, green onions, pimento, mushroom & celery soup, milk and cheese in spaghetti and chicken broth. Pour in large casserole and
bake at 325 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice according to directions.

title: chicken breasts with lemon butter
directions: Wash,
then
pat chicken dry with paper towels.
Season on both
sides
with salt and pepper.
Dust very lightly with flour, shaking off any excess.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix sugar syrup, Kool-Aid and juices.
Pour over ice in a punch bowl.
Add ginger ale or Sprite.
Serves 50.
A ring of frozen sweetened cherry Kool-Aid is nice to put in punch bowl.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Add cake mix 1/3 at a time; mix well.
Chill dough for 1/2 hour.
Heat oven to 375°.
Drop by scant teaspoonful on ungreased baking sheet or before chilling, roll between wax paper and slice to bake.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.

title: chili con carne
directions: Sprinkle the salt in the frying pan so meat won't spatter. Then put the ground beef, the onion, green pepper and pepper in pan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring and breaking meat into small pieces.
Cook until the meat is light brown and the onion and green pepper are tender.
Spoon extra fat off meat and then add beans, tomatoes and chili powder.
Bring to a slow bubble, then stir.
Reduce the heat, cover with a lid and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes or more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cinnamon apples
directions: Mix with the boiling water and dissolve the cinnamon candy and pour over apples and bake.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Mix jello according to directions and cool.
Then add strawberries to jello and let slightly jell.
Prepare pudding mix. Crumble one cake in a pan.
Pour strawberry mixture over first layer, then crumble other cake over berries.
Pour pudding on top of this.
Top with Cool Whip; refrigerate.

title: walnut turtles
directions: Cover baking sheet with waxed paper.
Cut walnut halves into large pieces and arrange into 28 to 30 clusters, spaced 1-inch apart.
Put caramels and butter in top of double boiler.
Set over hot water until caramels are melted, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and stir until butter, vanilla and caramels are thoroughly mixed.
Drop by teaspoons onto walnut clusters, making sure caramel touches all walnut pieces.
Cool.
Melt chocolate with shortening over hot (not boiling) water.
Spread over caramel and nut clusters and allow to set before removing from waxed paper.
Store in tight container in cool place.
Makes 28 to 30 turtles.

title: fruit salad(club member: amanda speed)
directions: Drain juice from cocktail and pineapple. Slice bananas into juices. Add instant pudding and mix. Add fruit and mix well, then refrigerate.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add bananas and milk. Mix well with mixer; add eggs and blend.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder, salt and nutmeg together.
Stir into cream mixture.
Fold in 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, then 325° for 25 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and pepper in a 1-quart casserole.
Stir in vinegar and beet liquid.
Add beets.
Cover. Microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes until slightly thickened.
Let stand 3 minutes before serving.

title: black bean vegetable chili
directions: Place eggplant in colander.
Toss with salt and let sit for 1 hour to remove moisture.
Pat dry.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Beat cream cheese and egg well. Blend in sugar and flour, gradually beating until well blended. Stir in cherries. Set aside.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Combine Seven-Up and marshmallows in saucepan. Cook until melted.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Cream the cheese in mixing bowl.
Add hot mixture to cheese and beat until smooth. Add pineapple and nuts. Chill until almost set. Fold in Cool Whip and mayonnaise.
Pour into oblong dish or mold. Refrigerate until set.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and celery until tender.
Drain almost all.
Dissolve bouillon in boiled water and add honey or sugar.
Mix rest of ingredients into a large Dutch oven or casserole dish.
Bake at 375° uncovered for 1 to 1 1/4 hours. Excellent on hot dogs, corn chips or as a side dish.

title: chocolate chips champs
directions: Beat butter and sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add flour.
Stir in candy and nuts.
On greased cookie sheet, drop by tablespoons 3 inches apart.
Press 3 to 4 additional candies in each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Grate lemon rind.
Cook first 5 ingredients and egg yolks until the mixture thickens, stirring occasionally. Cool before putting into 9-inch pie shell.

title: overnight buns
directions: Mix yeast with 1/2 cup water and 1 teaspoon sugar and let stand 5 minutes.
Mix together all ingredients in the late afternoon. Let rise; punch down and before going to bed, make into buns or cinnamon rolls.
Let rise all night on countertop covered with a towel.
Bake in morning at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: company chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with a slice of dried beef, then a slice of bacon.
Place in foil-lined pan.
Mix cream of chicken soup, mushroom soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 3 hours.
Last 10 to 15 minutes, uncover and let bacon brown.

title: giant chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into chunks.
Dip in beaten eggs.
Place in bread crumbs until covered.
Drop in hot deep fryer.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes, until golden brown.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients and coat chicken.
Place in baking pan or dish and bake at 425° for about 45 minutes.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: Melt
butter in a
heavy
pot
over
medium
heat.
Add onion, garlic, celery and pepper.
Cook until limp and tender, but not brown.
Add
all
remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and
cover;
simmer
for
hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and allow to cool.
Remove bay leaves, then blend in blender, food processor or force through a sieve.
Keep refrigerated.

title: overnight tuna casserole
directions: Grease 3 quart casserole.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Spoon into greased casserole.
Cover; refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 375°.
Allow casserole to stand at room temperature for 15 minutes.
Bake uncovered for 60 to 70 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 7 (1 cup) servings.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Pour mixture into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.

title: chinese salad
directions: Mix cabbage and onions.
Dissolve sugar in vinegar.
Add oil and soy sauce.
Mix with cabbage.
Melt butter in skillet over low heat.
Carefully brown seeds, almonds and noodles (this browns quickly).
Add to cabbage mixture just before serving so noodles will be crunchy.
Serves 20 to 25 people.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix Ricotta cheese, sugar and cream cheese.
After mixing, add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla, flour and sour cream.
Beat well. Bake in a buttered spring-form pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool for 1 hour and refrigerate.

title: oven barbecued wieners
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in cast iron skillet.
Warm in 325° oven.
Add boiled, drained wieners.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes.
Spoon sauce over wieners after 15 minutes.

title: onion dip
directions: Place sour cream in bowl.
Sprinkle dry soup mix over sour cream; mix well.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving.

title: quick ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add enough milk until you fill churn. Freeze.
You can make this recipe anyway you like.
You can add fruit or nuts.

title: nut goodie bars
directions: Melt together first 3 ingredients.
Stir in marshmallows and peanuts.
Spread in well-buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Store in refrigerator to set.
Cut into squares.

title: spinach salad(congealed salad)
directions: Thaw spinach.
Put in colander to drain.
Use paper towel to get all moisture out.
Dissolve gelatin in the 3/4 cup hot water. Let cool.
Add
lemon juice.
Mix onion, celery, cottage cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix everything together with spinach and gelatin. Place in a large mold and chill.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Set overnight in refrigerator.

title: spanish roast pork
directions: Place pork in large Ziploc plastic bag.
Add barbecue sauce and Recaito Criello.
Marinate for several hours (overnight is best). Season with salt and pepper.
Place in large pan and add melta and bake in 350° oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Wonderful served with black beans and rice.

title: strawberry minute pie
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add frozen berries.
Break up berries with a fork.
As berries thaw, gelatin thickens.
When partially set, pour into cooled pie shell.
Chill until completely set.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: Wash and drain mushrooms.
Put in skillet.
Add onion.
Mix other ingredients; pour over mushrooms.
Cover; bring to boiling point, then reduce heat and simmer for about 5 to 6 minutes.

title: wintery day bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain.
Add 2 quarts water, ham or sausage.
Simmer for 2 1/2 hours.
Add onions, garlic, chili powder, tomatoes and lemon juice.
Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: mustard salmon
directions: Mix mayonnaise and mustard.
Spread over salmon fillet (can use sole, flounder) and broil 10 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 275° in a stem pan.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into small chunks.
Place in a large pan.
Cover with water; bring to a boil, uncovered, until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain and cool.
When potatoes are cool, stir in sour cream, bacon, green onions, cheese, salt and pepper. Makes 16 servings.

title: manicotti with cheese
directions: Heat spaghetti sauce and water in saucepan to boiling; reduce heat and keep warm.
Mix together Ricotta, Mozzarella, Parmesan, parsley, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into cooked manicotti. Pour 1 cup sauce on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Arrange filled manicotti in a single layer over sauce.
Pour remaining sauce over manicotti.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix water and yeast.
Add sugar, salt and egg.
Mix with 2 cups flour with a rotary mixer.
Add remaining flour by hand.
This makes two cookie sheet pizzas or 3 round pizzas.
It's a good dough to put in a couple of iron skillets for deep dish pizza.
Brush pan and top of crust lightly with olive oil.
Bake with all ingredients for 15 to 20 minutes at 450°.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour and cocoa.
Blend in milk, melted butter and vanilla.
Put in pie shell and bake at 325° until firm.

title: soup (mom's style)
directions: Brown meat in skillet and drain off all drippings.
Put in stew pot or pressure cooker the browned meat, diced potatoes, dry onion, frozen vegetables and seasonings.
Add tomato sauce and at least 2 cans of water.
Cook 30 minutes at 15 pounds pressure if using a pressure cooker.
If using stew pot, it will need to cook longer and you will need more water.
Great served with cornbread.

title: chocolate date torte
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and let cool.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, date mixture, flour and soda.
Mix and pour into cake pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips, nuts and then sugar on top and bake in not too hot an oven.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Add 3 eggs at a time and 1 cup flour.
Pour in milk and flavoring.
Place in a cool oven at 325°. Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together in a large bowl.
Mix the remaining ingredients, except cheese, together and add to the dry ingredients.
Pour half of the batter into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle the grated cheese over the batter and cover with the remaining batter.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: dirt cake
directions: Put half of crushed cookies in bottom of a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer prepared pudding, cream cheese and the Cool Whip.
Cover with remainder of crushed cookies.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar; beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda; add to mixture alternating with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla. Add coconut and pecans.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in greased and floured pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: easy squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients, except for margarine and stuffing. Mix stuffing with melted butter.
Add 1/2 of mixture to rest of ingredients.
Pour into medium casserole dish.
Put rest of stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: peanut cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder onto paper plate. In mixing bowl, blend together sugar, shortening, egg and milk. Add sifted dry ingredients and mix.
Add peanuts and lemon juice. Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw
potatoes.
Mix
all
ingredients together, except corn flakes
and
butter.
Pour
mixture
into
greased baking dish. Top with crushed corn flakes, mixed with 1/4 cup melted butter. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Cook to a boil; add cornstarch to thicken.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Combine eggs and milk. Stir into cornmeal mixture (do not overbeat).
Lightly stir in butter or margarine.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until tests done.

title: wassail
directions: Tie spices in bag.
Mix all ingredients in pot and boil 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
May be prepared ahead and refrigerated. Serve hot!

title: carrot pecan crunch pie
directions: Cook carrots, covered in 1 cup of water, for 30 to 40 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Puree or mash carrots.
Should yield 2 cups.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat well by hand the shortening, sugar, egg, vanilla and milk.
Then add to the dry ingredients. Add nuts.

title: quick trail stew
directions: Pour oil into Dutch oven or large boiler.
Chop onion fine and place in pot.
Fry onions until brown.
Salt and pepper ground beef evenly and put in pot until beef browns.
Stir to mix with onions.
To browned beef, pour 2 cans of soup and 2 cans of water. Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Take pot off fire and put on tight lid.
Let set for 20 minutes.
Serve over Fritos and enjoy. Feeds 4.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, melted oleo, syrup, vanilla and salt. Add pecans and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Place whole pecans on top.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 35 more minutes.

title: chili for a crowd(serves 16)
directions: Brown ground beef, sausage and onion in very large soup kettle over medium-high heat.
Spoon off excess fat.
Over low heat, stir in pepper, tomato paste, garlic, cumin, chili powder, mustard, salt, basil and oregano.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes, breaking up with your hands or the back of a spoon.
Add wine, wine vinegar and beans.
Stir well and simmer uncovered for about 30 minutes.
Serve with bowls of sour cream, chopped onions and grated Cheddar cheese for garnish.
Goes great with East Coast Grilled Cornbread.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate until melted.
Add cream, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: chili for 100
directions: Melt suet.
Add meat a little at a time; cook until done. Chop garlic and onions; add to meat and cook until done.
Add tomato puree, cook about 30 minutes.
Season with chili powder, paprika, red pepper and salt.
Cook for 1 hour.

title: german skillet dinner
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Layer in skillet kraut, uncooked rice, cooked and drained hamburger, salt, pepper, tomato sauce, sliced onion and sliced green pepper.
Cook low-medium on stove for 30 minutes.
Do not stir.

title: old harwich hermits
directions: *Add 1/2 teaspoon vinegar to make sour.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Stew chicken with 3 or 4 bay leaves, bone it and dice.
Brown onion in butter.
Add tomato soup, tomato sauce, mushrooms, garlic powder and olives.
Cook package of spaghetti and chicken with sauce.
Put in casserole and top with grated cheese.
Heat in oven until hot throughout and cheese is melted.
Freezes well.

title: tiger cookies
directions: Stir together flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour mixture, mixing until well combined.
Stir in crushed Kellogg's Sugar-Frosted Flakes cereal.
Drizzle melted chocolate over dough.

title: ravioli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put half of the canned ravioli in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Stir together the eggs, spinach, cheeses and spices.
Spoon mixture over ravioli and layer again with ravioli.
Cover with foil and bake for 50 minutes.
Kids will eat spinach fixed this way!

title: michelle's blue ribbon peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla in large bowl. Stir in peanut butter.
When thoroughly blended, add flour, soda and salt.
Spoon onto cookie sheets and crisscross with a floured fork (I use a potato masher).
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: fish batter
directions: Mix well.
Dip fish, shrimp, etc., into batter.
Coat well and deep fry until golden brown.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450° (must be hot).
Combine all ingredients; knead dough until smooth.
Flour hands, pat out dough flat to 3/4 inches thick on floured board with biscuit cutter.
Bake on greased sheet for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes approximately 18 biscuits.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Then add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix lightly but well.
Combine flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to egg and zucchini mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pans (2) and sprinkle top with cinnamon, sugar and nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: danish apple pastry
directions: Sprinkle crust with cornflakes.
Put sliced apples on top. Sprinkle with cinnamon mixed with sugar.
Roll out other 1/2 of dough.
Place on top; pinch edges.
Beat egg white until stiff; brush on crust.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.
While warm, drizzle with frosting.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add flour in several parts. Add vanilla and nuts.
Shape into fingers.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; bake at 275° for about 30 minutes.
When done, roll each "finger" in powdered sugar.

title: crock-pot sloppy joes
directions: Beat meat in microwave in a colander, rinse and put in crock-pot. Add onions, green pepper, tomato sauce, water and seasonings. Stir thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or High for 3 to 4 hours. Serve with buns, chips and carrot stick.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and salt.
Melt butter in skillet. Pour in egg mixture.
(Stir once or twice around pan so egg does not start cooking.)
Add dates and stir until mixture thickens and turns brown (3 to 5 minutes) after mixture boils.
Add vanilla. Remove from heat; add cereal and nuts.
Cool slightly.
Make into small balls or into long rolls like refrigerator cookies.
Roll in coconut, nuts or powdered sugar.
(I like to use powdered sugar.) Put in refrigerator to harden.
These keep indefinitely in long rolls and can be sliced as needed.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Coat chicken with salt, pepper and flour. Fry in 1/3 cup of oil. Brown, then put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: vanity fair coconut custard pie
directions: Combine eggs, salt and sugar.
Add milk gradually, then add coconut and mix thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 15 minutes, then decrease heat to moderate 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Cool.

title: tuna and noodles
directions: Prepare noodles as directed on box.
Add drained tuna.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Cook 5 minutes on medium heat.
Serve over toast.

title: layered taco surprise
directions: Layer in order in 9 x 13 1/2-inch dish.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together; chill and serve.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: potato casserole
directions: Make first layer melted butter, second layer hash browns, third layer onions, fourth layer soup, fifth layer cheese and sixth layer corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: inexpensive sponge cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Beat in sugar, salt and flavoring.
Bring to a boil the milk and butter.
Add to the egg mixture and mix, then add the flour and baking powder quickly; beat until thoroughly mixed. Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Check at 25 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Bring jello, sugar and water to boil and boil 30 minutes.
Add juice and chill overnight.

title: apricot omelet for two
directions: Blend the kummel and apricot preserves; set them aside (but not too far away).

title: red beans and rice
directions: In large pot, brown sausage and onion.
Simmer until onion is tender, about 30 minutes.
Add rice and simmer about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cranberry-pretzel salad
directions: Mix cranberries, 1 cup sugar, pineapple and marshmallows; refrigerate overnight.
The following day, mix 2 cups pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine; pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Cool thoroughly.
Whip the whipping cream (or use Cool Whip), fold in the cranberry mix and spread over crust. Top with remaining 1 cup of crushed pretzels.
Chill and serve as salad or dessert.

title: stuffed crabs
directions: Saute celery and onions in oleo until soft.
Add cream of celery soup, prepared mustard and Worcestershire sauce.

Cook until warm. Mix crabmeat in separate bowl with bread crumbs, salt and pepper. After onions and celery cool, add to crabmeat mixture and mix well. Stuff crab shells and sprinkle bread crumbs on top and bake.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over the melted butter.
Do not stir.
Pour pie filling in middle of mixture but do not stir. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: easy casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package.
Using an ovenproof pan, mix all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° until bubbling.

title: friendship cake
directions: To make starter:
Warm 1 cup fruit juice.
Add yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar; let sit for 3 days at room temperature.
(Use starter within 3 days, or it will go flat, or keep adding 1 teaspoon of sugar daily to hold.)

title: pastor eddie's granny grace's dill pickles
directions: Put cucumbers in can. Boil water and vinegar mixture. Pour over cucumbers. Put cans in hot water bath for 7 minutes to seal cans.

title: karen's beans
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until thickened to desired consistency.

title: chocolate fudge sauce(for ice cream)
directions: In top of double boiler, melt chocolate and butter over simmering water.
Add confectioners sugar and milk alternately, 1/2 cup at a time, blending with a whisk.
Cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes, whisking often.
Remove from heat.
Transfer to mixing bowl and beat 5 minutes.
Do not miss this step.

title: fiesta pork chops
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Arrange meat in it. Top with soup mix, then rice.
Spread ketchup; sprinkle on Worcestershire sauce.
Pour boiling water over all.
Cover; bake for 55 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Add additional 1/2 cup boiling water if mixture dries out.
Remove from oven.
Top with cheese; allow to stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: *Chicken can be substituted for pork.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli; drain well.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs and onion; add to broccoli and put in casserole.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Melt butter or margarine and add to stuffing. Sprinkle on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot mexican dip(appetizer)
directions: Soften cream cheese by hand or in microwave.
Mix in chili and some chopped jalapeno peppers.
Put grated cheese on top and cook in microwave on Medium until hot all the way through and cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: *Note:
For best results, use a hot air corn popper to pop corn.

title: hungarian pastry
directions: Mix together flour, salt and yeast.
Crumble together with pastry blender, then cut in butter.
Add egg yolks, sour cream and 1 teaspoon vanilla as liquid.
Work together, using hands if necessary, into one ball.
Cut carefully into 6 balls.
Let stand while mixing filling.

title: super spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef in oil and garlic, crain fat.
Blend tomatoes into a puree.
In a crock pot, add beef and tomato puree.
Simmer uncovered 1 hour.
Add tomato paste, water, bay leaves, sweet basil, salt, pepper, sugar, parsley, Worchestershire sauce and oregano.
Cook covered for 1 hour.
Brown Italian sausage links. Cook until done.
Add to sauce 10 - 15 minutes before serving. Serve over spaghetti noodles.

title: broccoli and cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in a small crock-pot.
Combine all other ingredients.
Serve hot with chips.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together (mix with spoon not mixer) sugar, oil and eggs. Add to the mixture flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, vanilla, nuts and apples.
Spread dough into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 6 ounce package butterscotch chips on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
This is a moist cake.

title: lemon-filled yellow cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions for two 8 or 9-inch cake layers.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan.
Stir in water gradually.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute; remove from heat.
Stir in margarine and lemon peel until margarine is melted.
Gradually stir in lemon
juice and food color.
Press plastic wrap onto filling.
Refrigerate until set, at least two hours.
Fill layer and top with filling.
Frost sides with vanilla frosting.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In bowl,
beat	eggs
until frothy.
Beat in sugar, oil and vanilla
until
it	is
thick
and lemon colored.
Stir in loosely grated zucchini.
Stir in flour (sifted with cinnamon, soda, salt and
baking
powder).
Fold in chopped nuts.
Pour mixture into three oiled and floured loaf pans.	Bake at 350° for approximately one hour.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, pudding, butter, egg and milk and pour into a greased 10-inch square pan.
Mix together peaches, sugar, cream cheese and peach juice.
Put over batter.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spinach lasagne roll-ups
directions: *Set aside about 1/4 cup to use as topping on casserole before baking.

title: white salad
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add the baking soda and sugar. Fold in crackers and nuts.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Prepare one envelope Dream Whip as package directs.
Beat in the cream cheese (softened), then add the crushed pineapple.
Spread onto crust; refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: texas salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute margarine, onion (chopped) and celery (chopped).
Stir in cream of mushroom soup, evaporated milk and garlic cheese.
Add chunk chicken and frozen broccoli (cooked).
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake in medium oven until brown.
Makes 1 large casserole or 2 small ones.
Can be frozen.

title: chocolate scotcharoos
directions: Bring corn syrup and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Press into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt in a double boiler, chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Spread on the top of the pressed Krispies. Cut in squares.

title: peaches and cream("brings men to their knees")
directions: Combine flour, pudding mix and baking powder.
In another bowl, mix egg, milk and butter.
Combine the wet and dry mixtures and spread in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chop peach slices and arrange on top of batter.
Combine the cream cheese, sugar and peach juice; pour over peaches.
Sprinkle a cinnamon and sugar mixture over the top.
Bake for 45 minutes to an hour at 350°. Serve hot or cold.

title: cornish hens with special sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add sherry.
Bring to a boil.
Blend in jelly, lemon juice, salt, mustard and paprika; boil for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Brush hens with sauce; place in roasting pan. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes, basting often with remaining sauce.

title: seggetto salad
directions: Stir together ingredients.
Pour western dressing over all. Make a few days ahead and stir each day.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Make up and let stand for a while.
Roll thin as possible and cut in squares.
Use large container for chicken broth.
Drop layers of dumpling squares in boiling broth and allow to boil over each layer before adding another layer.
Cover and cook 12 minutes.
Season with milk and butter, if desired.

title: potato casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: company chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken pieces and roll in flour.
Brown lightly in margarine.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Add soups to skillet used for browning chicken; heat and stir until smooth. Pour sauce over chicken and bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: wita's mole
directions: Brown round steak in oil.
Add salt, garlic and comino.
Mix flour and chili powder in a cup; add mixture to skillet and brown, stirring constantly.
Stir in water and peanut butter.
Cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes, until sauce is gravy consistency. Serve with Arroz and mashed potatoes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, corn syrup, vanilla and melted butter.
Add pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: hot potato salad with bacon
directions: Boil the potatoes until soft; do not overcook.
Drain, then peel and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Set aside potatoes ina bowl covered with aluminum foil.

title: german apple cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Beat eggs in sugar. Combine oil and orange juice.
Add alternately with dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Mix until smooth; add vanilla and beat well.
Pour 1/2 batter in greased and floured tube pan. Arrange 1/2 apples over batter.
Combine cinnamon and sugar. Sprinkle over 1/2 of apples.
Top with remaining butter, apples and sugar.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: Make a brown sauce of fat, flour and stock.
Season and add mushrooms.
Cook 4 minutes for canned and 5 or 6 minutes for fresh ones.

title: rhubarb up-side down cake
directions: Put rhubarb in greased 9 x 13 inch pan. Sprinkle with sugar, then the jello. Then put the marshmallows on top of the jello layer. Mix the cake mix as directed of the box. And pour it over the rhubarb, sugar, jello and marshmallow. Bake 350 degrees until the cake is dark.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat 1 1/2 cups sugar, eggs and the fruit well.
Add reserved juice and mix.
Sift in the flour, soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Bake in an 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan for 45 minutes at 300°.
Bring to a rolling boil the brown sugar, pecans, 1/2 cup sugar, milk, vanilla and oleo.
Pour on top of cake and return to oven for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: sourdough bread("starter" from scratch and "bread")
directions: Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Pat top with corn oil.
Then cover lightly with foil paper and let rise for 10 to 12 hours.
Knead a little while in bowl, then divide into 3 or 4 equal parts and knead each part 12 to 15 times on floured board.
Put into greased loaf pans.
(Spray with Pam or Mazola corn oil spray.) Brush tops with corn oil.
Cover with waxed paper and 2 dish towels.
Let rise in pans 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from pans, brush tops with melted butter or margarine.
Cool on racks.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients, except last two.
Toss lightly and place in casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and chips.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat egg, shortening, butter, vanilla and 1/2 cake mix (dry) until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix. Divide dough into 4 equal parts.
Roll each part into rectangle 10 x 6-inch on lightly floured cloth-covered board with floured stockinet-covered rolling pin.
Cut rectangles 3 x 2 1/2-inch each.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until edges look set (centers of cookies will be slightly puffed). Prick surface of cookies lightly with fork.
Cool; remove from baking sheet.
Cut ice cream into rectangles about 3/4-inch thick. Place ice cream rectangle between 2 cooled cookies.
Gently press together to spread ice cream to edges of cookies.
Wrap in foil or plastic wrap and freeze at least 24 hours.
Makes 16 sandwiches.

title: thanksgiving cider
directions: Empty the cranberry juice into a punch bowl.
Stir in the frozen lemonade until melted.
When you are ready to serve, pour in the ginger ale.

title: white chocolate macadamia nut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly grease cookie sheets. Beat butter and shortening until soft and creamy. Gradually add the sugars and beat well. Add egg and vanilla and beat well. Combine flour, soda, and salt; gradually add to butter mixture beating well after each addition. Stir in chips and nuts. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets. Bake for 10-12 minutes or until done. Remove to wire racks to cool.

title: pete's savory beef casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet; drain excess fat.
Stir in seasonings and tomato sauce.
Add green pepper and onion.
Cook macaroni twists according to package directions; drain.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Mix all ingredients together and roll into small balls.
Make a cinnamon and sugar mixture, roll balls into mixture.
Place on cookie sheet, bake until slightly brown.
Cookie will not look done but they cook after taken out.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Put oven on 350°.
Blend sugar and flour and sprinkle about 1/3 of the mixture in bottom of pie shell.
Smooth evenly across pie shell.
Toss peaches with almond extract.
Add peaches to pie shell, keeping slices level rather than heaping.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar and flour.
Pour the cream slowly over the top of peaches.
Use a fork to move peaches around so they are all covered with cream.
Bake for 45 minutes.
The filling should be firm and lightly browned in spots.
Cool before serving.

title: fish kids will love!
directions: Layer fish in a lightly buttered 9x9 baking pan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Layer sour cream over fish, about 1\4-inch thick. Sprinkle with crushed cheese nips.
Bake at 350° for about 45 min. until fish flakes.

title: italian mashed potato pie
directions: After making the instant mashed potatoes, remove from heat. Add one egg and mix, then add the cheese (you can add more if you like the pie thicker).
Spread in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate-peanut butter chippers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the first 7 ingredients together. Mix flour, soda and salt together, then add slowly to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Add chips and pecan pieces.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for about 8 minutes. Do not let cookies brown.

title: sweetheart fudge pie
directions: Cream butter; gradually add brown sugar, beating at medium speed with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add melted chocolate, coffee granules, and yum extract; mix well.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Pour mixture into pastry shell.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes; cool completely.
Shill.
Garnish with whipped cream, if desired.

title: earthquake cake
directions: In a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan, spread pecans and coconut. Mix the cake mix as directed on package.
Pour over pecans and coconut.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add enough milk to make mixture pour over cake mix.
Bake for 55 minutes at 350°.

title: fried cabbage with tomatoes
directions: Cut cabbage into 1 1/2 to 2-inch chunks.
In a large, nonstick skillet, stir-fry cabbage and onion with wine for about 10 minutes or until cabbage becomes limp.
Season with garlic powder, oregano, parsley, salt and red pepper.
Combine tomatoes and sugar; add to cabbage, mixing thoroughly.
Cover and simmer until cabbage is tender (about 30 minutes).
Stir occasionally and, if necessary, add a little water to prevent sticking.

title: holiday turkey casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread and margarine.
Mix until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate all day.
Before placing in 350° oven, cube the bread and coat with margarine.
Scatter over turkey mixture.
Bake, uncovered, about 1 hour.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In large greased casserole dish layer chicken, onions and eggs. Mix soups, broth and canned drained vegetables, pour evenly over chicken mixture.
Mix milk, mayonnaise and flour to form crust when poured over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: in the bag turkey breast
directions: You will need 1 large (14 x 20-inch) oven cooking bag.

title: crunchy fudge sandwiches
directions: Cut crusts off about1 1/2 loaves bread.
Roll slices of bread flat with rolling pin.
Spread each piece with about 1 teaspoon cream cheese mixture; roll up.
Dip in melted butter, then sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake 400° for 10 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and save 3 cups of juice and cook puddings with juice until thick.
Let cool and pour over fruit.
Use any fruit you like as long as you have 3 cups of juice to add to your pudding.

title: old-fashioned turnip greens
directions: Pick and wash turnip greens.
Tear into bite-size pieces. Peel the turnip roots and slice.
Rinse salt pork and cut into 2-inch pieces.
Combine salt pork and water in a large Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Add turnip greens; cover and cook 10 minutes.
Add turnip roots and bacon drippings.
Cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes or until greens and roots are tender.
Serve with green onions.

title: applesauce bars
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add egg and applesauce.
Sift flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add to first mixture.
Add vanilla, nuts and dates.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in a 12 x 18-inch pan.

title: baker's icing
directions: Cream together sugar, water, shortening and vanilla.

title: tara's fair winning lemon delight pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Generously grease and flour 12-cup fluted tube pan.
In large bowl, combine cake ingredients.
Blend on low speed until ingredients are moistened.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Remove cake from oven.
Prick deeply every inch with a fork.
In small bowl, blend glaze ingredients until smooth.
Spoon half the glaze over hot cake in pan.
Let stand 10 minutes; invert onto serving plate.
Spoon remaining glaze over cake.

title: quick lasagne
directions: Saute onion in small amount oil or butter.
Add beef.
Drain when cooked.
Prepare pasta and begin layering ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish as follows: pasta, Ricotta, Prego, beef, Cheddar and Mozzarella.
Continue layering until pasta is gone. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese and bacon ball
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and form a ball.
Chill until firm, then roll in nuts.
Cover and refrigerate.
Allow to reach room temperature before serving with crackers.

title: brown sauce
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt together.
Add water and stir until smooth, add butter, boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Pour over pudding and serve hot.
Yields 6-8 servings.

title: broccoli chowder
directions: Chop vegetables and add to 1 can of chicken broth (2 to 3 cups).
May use bouillon.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes.
Add 1 quart of milk and bring to a boil.
Thicken with 2 to 4 tablespoons of cornstarch.
Add cheese.
Beat with spoon until melted.
Do not boil.

title: green bean supreme
directions: Saute onion and margarine.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add sour cream, stirring constantly.
Cook until smooth and thickened.
Add beans.
Put into deep casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain peaches and strawberries.
Add together in a large bowl. Add pineapple with juice.
Next, add pudding and Tang together and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, add bananas.
This will keep in refrigerator for 7 to 10 days.

title: hershey chocolate pie
directions: Melt hershey bars on low in microwave, stirring constantly. Stir in cool whip and marshmallow creme.
Spoon into crust.
Chill and serve.

title: quickie luscious lasagna
directions: Add lasagna noodles to boiling water one at a time so you do not stop the water from boiling.
Boil 15 minutes or until tender. Drain, rinse with cold water and drain thoroughly again.
Blend Ricotta cheese, egg whites, spinach and parsley.
Add minced garlic to spaghetti sauce.

title: pie crust
directions: In a large bowl, blend the flour, salt and Crisco.
Make a paste of 2/3 cup flour and 1/2 cup warm water.
Stir the paste into flour mixture until you can gather it into a ball.
Kneading the ball will not be a problem.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter, add eggs.
Stir in bananas (the riper the bananas the better the flavor) and lemon juice.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix quickly.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: end of garden pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers, peppers, cabbage, onions and tomatoes overnight in salt water (1/2 cup salt to 2 quarts water).
Drain. cook carrots and green beans until tender.
Mix all ingredients and boil 10 minutes.
Pack in sterilized jars and seal.

title: orange-pineapple ice cream
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients in freezer and finish filling with drinks to freezer line for 1 gallon freezer.
Freeze and serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix and bake in greased and floured Bundt pan or loaf pans. Bake at 350°.

title: plume-moos
directions: Cover dried fruit with water and cook until done. Cool slightly and add cream. Combine sugar, cinnamon and flour and stir in enough water to make a thin paste. Add to fruit and cook until thick, stirring constantly. Serve either hot or cold.

title: surprise sweet potato balls
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water until done.
Peel and mash real fine, add slightly beaten eggs to mixture and mix well. Form into balls around marshmallow, then roll in crushed corn flakes.
Place into baking dish being careful not to crowd.
Set aside while topping is being prepared.

title: steak sticks sandwiches
directions: Cut steak into 6 to 8 strips (1-inch thick).
Sprinkle with tenderizer.
Wrap each with bacon; fasten with wooden picks.
Stir together the mustard, juice and brown sugar; brush over steak sticks.
Grill over hot coals about 10 minutes, turning frequently and brushing with additional mustard mixture.
Remove wooden picks; serve on toasted buns.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: 24 hour coconut cake
directions: Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
As soon as you take cake from oven, make holes in top with fork.
Combine the icing and pour over cake.

title: everyday stir-fry
directions: All ingredients must be cut.
Heat wok with oil.
Add 2 or 3 tablespoons ginger root and garlic cloves.
Brown.
Add cut-up meat; broil real good.
Add vegetables and 2 or 3 tablespoons soy sauce.
Stir constantly.
Vegetables should be crisp (not overcooked).
Add cheese (if using it) after veggies have cooked 2 or 3 minutes.
Serve over rice or just plain.

title: blueberry syrup
directions: In a blender container or food processor bowl, combine berries and apple juice; blend or process until pureed.
Transfer to saucepan.
Stir in cornstarch.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat. Stir in Equal, lemon peel, lemon juice and margarine.
Serve over pancakes, waffles or French toast.
Makes 1 cup.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli.
Cut florets and tender stems below.
Wash and cut red onions into rings.
Place in salad bowl.
Shred 4 ounces of Swiss cheese on top.
Sprinkle bacon bits on top.

title: no cheese cheese pie(low calorie)
directions: Put ingredients in blender in order. Blend 2 to 3 minutes on high.
Pour into a 9-inch pie plate sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg. Chill at least 2 hours.

title: squirrel and dumplins
directions: Put
squirrel into a pressure cooker; cover with water. Cook at	10
pounds pressure for 30 minutes.
Let pressure go down slowly.
Lift
meat
out;
set aside.
Season broth with butter, salt and pepper.

title: baked mushroom rice
directions: Place rice in a greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Cook onions, stirring constantly, in skillet until tender.
Add broth and remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil and pour over rice. Cover and bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Stir before serving.
Yields 8 servings.

title: great new way to bake the turkey(takes courage but it works)
directions: Salt and pepper inside and out.
Place in roaster or turkey pan with 6 cups of water.
Tightly cover with lid or heavy-duty foil. Bake the bird in a 500° preheated oven for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and do not open the door for 12 hours.
It does work and your turkey will be moist and tender.

title: honey dijon salad dressing
directions: Blend everything well.
Refrigerate.
Will keep for 21 days. Discard when oil starts to separate.
Makes 1 quart.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown beef lightly in fat.
Stir with fork to break up meat. Add onion, cook a few minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and simmer 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: grandma mag's peanut butter no-bake cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Beat well.
Spoon onto waxed paper and cool.

title: aztec chicken casserole
directions: Saute butter, green onion, bell pepper and celery.
Add chicken to saute mixture.
Add chicken broth.
Melt cheese.
Add to mixture, corn, tomatoes, mushroom soup and celery soup.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Cover with crushed chips on the bottom of the dish. Top with mixture, then on top of mixture add second layer of crushed chips and top with rat trap cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until hot and bubbly.

title: turkey turnovers
directions: Dice meat or run through grinder.
Heat meat, onion and part of broth.
Make thickening with flour.
Add to heated meat.
Place a 16 dipper of meat mixture over crust.
Fold over and seal edges with fork.
Perforate with fork.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Pour gravy over, eat and enjoy!

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.
Keeps well.

title: rice and broccoli
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Slice water chestnuts. When onions are done, add rice, broccoli, soup, evaporated milk and water chestnuts.
Mix in one third of the cheese.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Beat milk, sour cream and pudding mix until smooth.
Place a third of the banana slices into pastry shell.
Top with half of the pudding mixture.
Repeat layers.
Arrange the remaining bananas on top.
Cover with whipped topping.
Chill for at least 2 hours.

title: sausage spaghetti
directions: Brown sausage over medium heat with diced onions and green peppers.
Drain fat.
Add mushrooms and Ragu sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over cooked spaghetti noodles.
This is quick, easy and delicious!

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Place in 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Drain off grease as necessary.

title: farm journal custard pie
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar and flavoring.
Mix together.
Stir slowly into beaten eggs.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: shredded wheat bread
directions: Pour boiling water over Shredded Wheat. Add molasses, shortening and salt. When cool, add eggs and yeast (dissolved according to directions).
Add enough flour to make a good dough. Knead well, at least 5 minutes; the more, the better.
Let rise double in bulk.
Punch down and let rise again.
Put in pans.
Let rise. Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: tomato sauce cake
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sift the first 3 ingredients; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine the next 3 ingredients; set aside.

title: neapolitan
directions: Melt margarine; add flour, 1 tablespoon powdered sugar and nuts and mix together.
Pat down into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Set aside to cool.

title: salado select almond marble fudge
directions: Line two 9-inch square pans with foil; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine chocolate chips and 4 tablespoons butter with sweetened condensed milk and vanilla.
Microwave on High, stirring after each minute, until mixture is smooth.
Stir in 2 cups nuts. Spread evenly into pan.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Place uncooked noodles in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add browned chops.
In same pan, saute onion and celery until tender.
Pour over pork chops.
Add tomatoes.
Mix tomato soup and water.
Stir well, then pour over pork chop mixture.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy russian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Skin chicken parts.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In separate bowl, mix preserves, Russian dressing and onion soup mix.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: chicken vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate.
Mix chicken, zucchini, tomato, onion and cheese.
Spoon evenly into pie plate.
Beat the remaining ingredients for 15 seconds on high speed or until smooth.
Pour evenly over chicken mixture.
Bake 35 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Let cool 5 minutes before cutting.

title: pineapple chiffon cake
directions: Sift together cake flour, sugar, baking powder and dash of salt.
Make well in center and add in this order:
salad oil, yolks and pineapple juice.
Beat until smooth.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and margarine.
Add eggs one at a time and beat.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add flavorings and mix. Pour into large, greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Small tube pan is not big enough.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cook and drain ground beef. Layer tater tots in casserole dish. Pour ground beef over tater tots. Mix cream of chicken and cream of mushroom together pour over ground beef. Top with shredded cheese. Put in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot ring
directions: Wash, peel or scrape carrots and grate.
Mix with bread crumbs.
Beat
eggs.
Add
milk,
salt
and
melted butter and combine
with
carrots
and bread crumbs.
Fill a well-greased ring mold and set mold in pan of hot water.
Bake in slow oven (325°) until
firm.
Turn
mold
onto hot dish and fill center with creamed fish of creamed eggs.

title: strawberry pretzel torte
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, sugar and margarine together.
Press 3/4 of mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Reserve 1/4 of mixture for topping.)
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cool.

title: bacon-wrapped little loaves
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except bacon.
Shape mixture into 6 little loaves.
Crisscross 2 half slices bacon on each loaf, tucking ends under loaves.
Place loaves on rack in shallow baking pan; bake uncovered 50 minutes.

title: christmas cut out cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg and vanilla.
Mix flour and salt and add to creamed mixture.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Roll out on floured surface to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut out and bake at 325° approximately 10 minutes.
Do not let cookies get brown.

title: delightful dessert
directions: Mix flour and melted butter.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Beat powdered sugar and cheese.
Fold in 1 (8 ounce) Cool Whip. Spread on crust.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, flour and margarine; add milk and vanilla. Beat well and pour mixture into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: curry rice
directions: Mix rice,
curry
powder,
salt and onions with oil and vinegar.
Marinate	overnight and then mix with other ingredients.

title: peachy bran muffins
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Mix eggs, peaches, oil and cereal with milk.
Let stand.
Add flour mixture.
Stir. Place in muffin pans and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend the ingredients together and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: minestrone(a meal in a pot)
directions: In a large pot, saute carrots, celery, onions, garlic and cabbage in butter until brown (about 20 minutes).
Add tomatoes with fluid and next nine ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 30 minutes or until rice and vegetables are tender.
Add beans and spinach (cook before adding) and bring entire soup to a simmer.
Add water if needed.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Makes about 18 cups (4 1/2 quarts).

title: cajun rubbed fish nuggets
directions: Brush BBQ grill with oil.
Turn to medium high.
Place Cajun Rub and 1 pound of fish nuggets in a paper bag.
Shake until pieces are well coated.
Thread onto pre-soaked skewers.
Cook on hot grill for 3 - 5 minutes each side.
Serve with lemon wedges, as an appetizer for 4 or as a main dish for 2.

title: striped delight
directions: Crush cookies and mix with softened margarine, press firmly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate 15 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and 2 tablespoons milk in a medium bowl until smooth. Gently stir in 3 cups of whipped topping.
Spread over crust, pour milk in a large bowl.
Add pudding mix, beat, spread over cream cheese mixture and refrigerate until set.
Use rest of Cool Whip to top.
Sprinkle with nuts (optional).
Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight. Cut into squares.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Arrange chips in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Cook ground beef and onion together; drain.
Put on top of chips layers of soup, beans and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Top with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: dirt
directions: Cream together the margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Mix in milk, instant pudding and Cool Whip.
Crush large bag of Oreo cookies into crumbs.
In a large clean flowerpot, alternate layers of cookies and pudding. Begin and end with cookies.
Use the plastic Cool Whip lid in bottom of
flowerpot to prevent leaking. Decorate with plastic flowers and serve with a garden spade.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Cream the sugar and melted butter.
Add other ingredients. Mix with mixer.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 4 minutes.
Needs no refrigeration.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Fry together the hamburger, onion, peppers and celery. Combine remaining ingredients and add the hamburger mixture. Simmer all together for at least 30 minutes. Serve hot on buttered round rolls. Serves 12-15.

title: nut squares
directions: Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in medium oven.
Let cool and cut in squares.
Do not overcook.
Will be soft until cool.
Use greased cookie sheet to bake.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cheese.
Whip with electric mixer.
Set in refrigerator.
Whip milk.
Fold in jello mixture. Pour in pan lined with graham cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs on top and chill.

title: spring punch
directions: Combine drink mix, grape juice and apple juice in large pitcher.
Stir to dissolve and chill well.
Just before serving add soda and fruit.
Serve over ice.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit together.
Save juice from pears, peaches and pineapple. Pour dry pudding mix over fruit.
Pour juice over pudding, then mix.
Do not use juice from cherries.

title: copper pennies
directions: Clean carrots, slice and cook until tender. When cool, add cleaned, sliced onions and pepper rings.
Combine tomato soup, vinegar, salad oil, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and sugar.
Mix well and pour over vegetables.
(Cauliflower may be added.) Refrigerate several days.

title: pumpkin supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in custard cups or in 1 1/2-quart casserole 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream.

title: lisa's zucchini bread
directions: Grease bottom of 2 loaf pans.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Stir in sugar, zucchini, oil and vanilla.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup.
Stir in flour and remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour into greased casserole dish. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until brown around edges.
Serve immediately.

title: bacon-pineapple slaw
directions: In saucepan, cook bacon until crisp; remove with slotted spoon and set aside.
In bacon fat, saute onion until light brown.

title: peachy keen salad
directions: Combine dry gelatin, vanilla pudding mix and marshmallows; stir in boiling water.
Cook over low heat until all ingredients are dissolved.
In a 9 x 13-inch dish, pour peaches and all but 1/2 cup of the liquid.
Pour hot jello mixture over peaches; stir to blend.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serves 8.

title: ham-cheese oven omelet
directions: Beat eggs, milk and seasoning salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased oblong baking dish (12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inches) or square baking dish (8 x 8 x 2-inches).
Cook uncovered in 325° oven until omelet is set and top is golden brown, 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, cornstarch and flour.
Add eggs (beaten), vanilla and coconut flavoring.
Add squash and coconut.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: oven beef stew
directions: In order, place meat and vegetables into large casserole in layers.
Do not stir it, layer it.
Pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with tapioca.
Pour 2 cans golden mushroom soup and 2 cans French onion soup over vegetables and meat.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 4 hours.
Do not lift the lid while baking.
Stew will have a thick brown gravy and meat will be brown.
Enjoy!

title: red jello punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add sugar and additional water.
Add juice; mix well.
Freeze, stirring occasionally.
Add 1 quart ginger ale just before serving.

title: rikki's soup stew
directions: Place all ingredients into a 6-quart pan.
Do not drain juice! Cook on stove on medium temperature for about 1/2 hour.
Serves 6 people.

title: almost my mama's pumpkin pie
directions: Place half the ingredients in blender in the order given.
Mix with first half in blender. Add rest. Blend well.
Pour into a 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Makes its own crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: philly cream cheese dip
directions: Beat all ingredients in small mixing bowl at medium speed until well blended.
Refrigerate.
Serve with vegetables, crackers or baked potato topper.
Makes 2 cups.

title: hot cider
directions: Combine and simmer for 30 minutes.
(Put allspice and cloves in tea ball.)

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Mix sifted flour, milk and oil together with spoon.
Place extra flour in larger pan or cutting board to roll out biscuits on. Roll dough out in hands to make biscuits or place ball of dough on cutting board and roll to desired thickness.
Cut biscuits out with biscuit cutter and place in lightly greased pan to bake.
Bake at 400 degrees till golden brown on top and bottom.
This recipe should make about 8 to 10 biscuits.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and put in bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle onion over hamburger and then vegetables.
Cover top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate sour cream sheet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat for 2 minutes.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a sheet cake pan.
Cool and frost with chocolate or white frosting.

title: surprise-filled cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a medium bowl combine flour and baking powder.
Mix well with a wire whisk.
Set aside.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook
raisins,	sugar,	water,	salt,
butter and lemon juice for
minutes.
(In
microwave, just cook until boils really well.) Dissolve cornstarch in 3 tablespoons cold water and	add to	raisin mixture.
Cook about 5 minutes (in microwave,
until thick)
until nice and thick;
remove from heat. Add
lemon extract.
Pour
into unbaked 10-inch pie shell and add
top crust.
Bake about 25 minutes at 425° or until crust is
nice
and brown.
Juice will bubble out top of pie through slits in top crust.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in square cake pan in a 350° oven.
Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Pour into melted butter.
Add peaches.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: ambrosia fruit dip
directions: In small bowl, combine yogurt and cream of coconut; mix well. Stir in nuts.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: easy oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine all dry ingredients and mix.
Add oil, egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Press together in balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: dried beef spread
directions: Chop beef and mix all ingredients together. Serve with crackers.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Place undrained, thawed strawberries into a large bowl; add eggs and oil.
Beat with fork to mix.
Stir in 2 1/2 cups flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar.
Mix pecans with remaining 1/2 cup flour.
Stir into strawberry mixture and beat to mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture into 2 greased, floured 9 x 5-inch or 3 (8 x 4-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
If top starts to overbrown before bread is done, loosely cover top with a piece of foil.

title: potato skins
directions: Bake potatoes until tender.
Cut into quarters.
Scoop out the insides, leaving 1/2-inch thick shells.
Brush both sides of potato skins with butter.
Place, cut side up, on a large baking sheet.
Bake in oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until crisp at 425°. Sprinkle with cheese and salt (optional).
Bake 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Top with salsa, green onions or sour cream.

title: sweet onion pizza on crispy rice crust
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine rice, egg whites and 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese in a bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Coat 12-inch metallic pizza pan or 9 x 13-inch rectangular baking pan lightly with nonstick cooking spray.
Press the rice mixture firmly into the pan.
Bake 18 minutes or until surface is crispy and lightly browned around the edges.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Combine egg and corn.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir well.
Drop by tablespoons into hot oil.
Cook until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Blend cake mix, applesauce and eggs until moistened. Beat as directed on package.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups batter.
Pour remaining batter into pan. Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over cake batter and top with reserved batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until it tests done.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes, then loosen and turn out onto wire rack.

title: ho bo bread
