directions: Soak the raisins, boiling water and soda overnight.
Next morning, add oil, sugar, flour, eggs, salt and nuts.
Mix well. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Beat egg whites with 1/4 cup sugar until stiff.
Set aside. Cream butter; add salt, vanilla and remaining sugar.
Add flour, baking soda and milk; mix until light and creamy.
Fold in egg whites.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon flour over blueberries and add to mixture.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while hot.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, vanilla and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well. Stir in peanut butter, then sifted dry ingredients.
Form into balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Press down with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and can of milk, then blend in Cool Whip.
Add nuts and pineapple; pour into cooled pie shells and sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: cherry walnut cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Blend in flour, salt and soda.
Stir in cherries and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° 8 - 12 minutes, until golden.

title: cottage cheese bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let rise until doubled in a greased bowl.
Bake in a greased pan 40 minutes at 300° to 350°. When done, spread on butter and sprinkle on salt.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar thoroughly. Blend in bananas, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to banana mixture alternately with buttermilk, mixing thoroughly after each addition.
Add nuts, if desired, and mix.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
If top becomes brown before bread is done, lower oven temperature to 300° and bake until done.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: lemonade pie
directions: In mixing bowl, combine all 3 ingredients and mix together until smooth.
(Can use spoon or mixer.)
Pour into graham cracker crust.
(To make it look yellow you can add a couple of drops of lemon food coloring.)
Put in freezer.
Ready in 1 hour.
Can garnish with lemon slices.
Great for hot summer days; takes minutes to make.
Let the kids do this one!

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and milk.
Add pudding and whipped cream and mix.
Alternate layers of crushed cookies (bottom) and pudding mixture for 5 layers, ending with crushed cookies.
Chill and enjoy.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, tomato sauce, eggs and onion. Form into balls.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes on cookie sheet.
Mix ketchup, chili sauce and grape jelly.
Heat until jelly melts.
Add meat balls and simmer.

title: luncheon salad
directions: Fold in one cup whipped cream.
Pour into molds and set.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Season to taste in water, enough to equal vegetable level. Bake in 250° oven for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with biscuits or French bread.

title: golden glow cake
directions: Mix sugar and shortening, then egg yolks.
Add milk and flour. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Stir in vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: chipped beef ball
directions: Combine 1/4 cup dried beef with softened cream cheese.
Add sour cream, Parmesan cheese and horseradish.
Blend thoroughly. Refrigerate mixture 15 minutes.
Form into ball and roll in remaining dried beef.
Chill thoroughly.
Enjoy!

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Mix cherries, pineapple, oranges and marshmallows; toss with Old-Fashioned Pineapple Dressing.
Cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours but no longer than 24 hours.
Spoon into lettuce-lined salad bowl or lettuce cups and if desired, garnish with orange sections.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; set aside.
Beat eggs lightly in large bowl.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla and beat until creamy.
Drain pineapple and stir in along with zucchini.
Add dry ingredients, stirring only until moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's directions.

title: applesauce
directions: Cut apples into small pieces (leave peelings on) and put them in an electric frying pan.
Add little sugar and lemon juice to taste.
Cover apples with water.
Simmer until completely disintegrated.
Mash mixture with wooden spoon.
Add dash of cinnamon.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash strawberries; cap and drain.
Bring to a boil and boil, stirring constantly for 2 minutes the sugar, cornstarch and water. Add jello.
Let cool.
Put a small amount of glaze in pie crust, then strawberries and remaining glaze.
Chill.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together with electric mixer.
(You may use less of the evaporated milk if it is too thin a consistency.)
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add crushed wafers and milk.
Mix in coconut and pecans.
Bake in well-greased tube pan at 275° for 2 hours.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together sugar and water.
Bring to boil; let boil 4 minutes.
Add marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well and spread into buttered dish.
Let cool.

title: icebox pie
directions: Mix
all ingredients and put in refrigerator.
Bake pie shells.
When
pie	shells	are cool fill with mixture and put pies in refrigerator to set.
Makes 2 pies.

title: waffles
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk and well beaten egg yolks.
Add melted butter, but not too hot. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in hot waffle iron.

title: cream cheese vegetable soup
directions: Prepare vegetables as indicated; add water.
Cook until tender.
Combine cream cheese, butter and soup.
Add to cooked vegetables.
Add bacon bits, pepper and milk.
Heat and serve.

title: apple pan pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and baking powder.
Add other ingredients.
Put mixture in greased pie pan(s). Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Top with whipped cream.

title: dream cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until thick. Slowly add sugar, salt and vanilla. Beat mixture on high speed until stiff. Fold in chips and drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet. Put into oven and turn oven off. "Forget" cookies until morning (or at least 5 hours). Yield: About 1 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: broccoli ham roll-ups
directions: Blanch broccoli in boiling, salted water; put in colander. Run cold water over broccoli for several minutes.
Let drain.
Put on paper towels and pat as dry as possible.
Put 2 broccoli spears on each slice of ham, flower ends opposite.
Roll up.
Put in baking dish, seam side down.
Melt oleo over medium heat in heavy saucepan.
Add flour, salt and mustard.
Stir until smooth.
Add milk, stirring over constantly.
Slowly add milk; stir until thickened.
Remove from heat; add cheese.
Mix well.
Pour over rolls and bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until hot.
Can be doubled or make as many as you like.
Just use 2 broccoli spears for each slice of ham.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening, then add eggs and beat thoroughly. Add milk, flour, vanilla and butter flavoring.
Mix thoroughly. Cook in Bundt pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place pie crust on a cookie sheet.
In small bowl, beat together water and egg white.
Brush on the pie crust and bake for about 5 minutes or until light golden.
Cool thoroughly.
Meanwhile, in a large bowl, place the pudding, nutmeg, cinnamon, milk and softened ice cream; mix for about 1 minute in an electric mixer until mixture is smooth.
Pour mixture into cooled pie crust and freeze a few hours until firm.
Remove from freezer about 15 minutes before serving.
Garnish with whipped topping and crushed chocolate.
Store leftover pie in freezer.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Cut top 1/3 from potato.
Scoop out the insides and place into large mixing bowl; save the shells.
Add warm milk, butter, salt, pepper and mix until creamy.
Add Parmesan cheese, mixing with a spoon.
Place mixture into reserved shells.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Place in baking dish and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve.
Will serve 4.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef, then add chopped onion, kidney beans, taco seasoning. Cook until onions are tender. Set aside to cool a little bit. Mix together lettuce, tomato, chips and cheese in a large bowl.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Combine water, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and looks transparent. Put in refrigerator to cool slightly, then add butter, cocoa, vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir until well blended.
Put into pie shell and let cool.
Top with Cool Whip or meringue.

title: gingered fruit dip
directions: In a blender or food processor combine cottage cheese, banana and ginger.
Cover and process until smooth.
Add enough milk (about 1 Tbsp.) to make the dip of desired consistency.
Transfer to an airtight container, cover.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve with fruit dippers.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Mix cider and spices and heat thoroughly.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
Serve hot with additional cinnamon sticks as stirrers. Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: potato casserole
directions: Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve juice.
Combine juice, sugar, and flour.
Combine pineapple, cheese, and juice mixture.
Pour in casserole dish.
Crush crackers and mix with butter and top with pineapple slices.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cold water chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl with a whisk or fork. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes and frost with your favorite fudge frosting.

title: six-spice cake(recipe dated 1936)
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in moderate oven.

title: crepes creme de cacao
directions: Whip the cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in confectioners sugar.
Stir in creme de cacao.
Whip the cream; fold into cream cheese mixture.
Fill crepes with about 3 tablespoons of the filling.
Roll crepes; serve.
Makes 6 servings of 2 crepes each.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: To make sauce, combine butter, flour, milk, nutmeg, American cheese, and Old English cheese.
When cooked, add onion, petter, pimento, and mushrooms.
Use two 8x12 Pyrex dishes, or one large pan.
Grease pan, and layer cooked spaghetti, cooked and diced chicken, and sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This may be frozen.
Serves 20.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix jello and boiling water.
When it starts to jell, add strawberries.
Let set until it is completely jelled.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Add sugar. Mix and spread on top of pretzels.
Add jello to the top.
Your dessert is ready to eat!
(Refrigerate it for a few hours before serving.)

title: cheesy enchilada casserole
directions: Put chicken and chips in an oblong pan.
Heat soups and melt cheese.
Pour this over the chicken and chips;
then bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Yum Yum!

title: alpine casserole
directions: Using a 9 x 13-inch pan, put in pieces of chicken, mushrooms and celery.
In a measuring cup (2-cup size), mix together soup, wine and milk mixing well.
Pour over chicken mixture thoroughly coating ingredients.
Gently stir in almonds and cheese.
Top casserole with a generous sprinkling of Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: hopscotch
directions: In double boiler melt peanut butter and butterscotch morsels. Add noodles and marshmallows; stir until well blended.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Chill.
Keep refrigerated.

title: carly's ice cream sandwich
directions: Warm cookies in microwave. Place ice cream between the cookies. Eat real fast!

title: sour cream baked haddock
directions: Mix maple syrup, sour cream and lemon juice.
Place haddock in baking dish and pour sour cream mix over.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Salt and pepper, if desired.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes, until fish is flaky.

title: chocolate war cake
directions: Use a glass 9 x 12-inch loaf pan.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add flour and cocoa mixture and milk alternately.
Add salt and vanilla.
Mix soda in hot water and blend well.
Add boiling water and mix well.
Mixture will be thin.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: gopher sandwich
directions: Spread peanut butter in pita, covering both inside surfaces. Spread honey on top of peanut butter and sprinkle with sunflower seeds.
Kids really "go-pher" this sandwich.

title: pecan chewy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray or grease two 6 x 10 baking pans or one 9 x 12 baking pan.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; add cocoa and red food coloring together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Grease and flour cake pans; spread batter evenly in pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tests done.
Bake in two 9-inch pans. Serves 8.

title: foiled hamwiches
directions: Combine ham, green pepper, onion, celery, mayonnaise, horseradish and pepper.
Spoon about 1/2 cup ham mixture on each bun and top with grated cheese.
Wrap each sandwich in foil. Chill.
To serve, heat in oven about 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot. Makes 12 sandwiches.

title: apple torte dinner dish
directions: Mix apples and nutmeats in a large bowl.
Sift flour, sugar, soda, baking powder and salt together.
Add dry ingredients to apples and nuts and mix well.
Combine egg, vanilla and oil.
Pour over dry mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Batter will be stiff.
Spread in a sprayed or buttered 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold with whipped cream.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Break up chicken and layer in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan with the broccoli over top of chicken.
Make sauce of mayo, curry powder and soup.
Mix together and pour sauce over chicken and broccoli.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl. Mix well. Serve with vegetables, crackers or corn chips.

title: tangy almond glazed ham
directions: Heat ham according to label instructions.
Combine remaining ingredients for glaze.
Generously spoon glaze over ham during last 20 minutes of baking.
Warm remaining glaze and serve over sliced ham.

title: ann's punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions and place in refrigerator to firm.
Make 2 layers from box cake.
Take one layer and break into pieces, into large punch bowl.
Place 1/2 of the following ingredients on top of cake in order: instant pudding, cherry pie filling, fruit cocktail, pineapple, nuts, coconut and Cool Whip.
Now add second layer in the same order using the remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.
Serves 20 to 25.

title: texas taters
directions: Mix together and put in a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Top with 1 1/2 cups crushed cornflakes mixed with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May use bread crumbs instead of cornflakes.

title: pear bread
directions: Add each ingredient in order in a big mixing bowl.
Pour into individual loaf pans or several regular cake pans that have been sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°. Cool upside down.
Serve hot or freeze for later.

title: eggplant, italian style
directions: Remove & discard stems.
Peel & slice approx. 1/8th inch think.
Layer into a colander or pot.
Add a lot of salt between each layer.
This will take all of the natural liquids from them and act as a preservative.
Put a heavy object on top of them to help squeeze the liquid from them.
Let set for at least 12 hours. Remove from colander/pot and squeeze any excess liquid if necessary.
Be careful not to break them apart.
Mix 1 part white vinegar with 2 parts water in large pot and bring to a boil.
Add sliced eggplants and boil about 2 mins.
Remove and drain.
Pat dry.
In largest bowl you can find, put eggplant, chopped garlic, oregano, red pepper seeds and oil.
Mix thoroughly making sure all of the eggplants have been absorbed and oiled.
Layer into jars while adding more oil a little at a time until oil reaches the very rim of jar.
Insert a long knife length ways along the inside edge of jars.
This is so all air bubbles can escape.
Wipe top rim clean so that the lids will seal properly.
Put lids on and tighten well.
Put in cool place and wait 1-2 weeks before eating. The longer the better.
Enjoy in a sandwich or as a side dish.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; add onion and saute until clear. Drain. Place in crock-pot or large boiler (I use crock-pot).

Add salt, pepper, garlic juice, bay leaves, tomato paste and water. Cook on low (2 to 3 hours in pot) or all night or all day in crock-pot. Cook noodles in salted water with oil until done. Pat dry after cooking. Remove bay leaves. Stir in cottage cheese. In greased 9 x 13 pan, spoon a little sauce over bottom. Cover bottom with noodles. Spoon sauce completely over noodles; cover with Mozzarella. Continue layering until gone, last layer being sauce. Top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.

title: trawler crab dip
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Chill before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: oyster snack crackers
directions: Warm oil and add seasonings.
Mix well.
Put crackers into large plastic bag.
Pour mixture over crackers and shake well. Seal bag tightly to keep.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Mix all the
ingredients
in large salad bowl and serve on lettuce leaves or other greens.

title: fried squash patties
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix well. Drop by tablespoon into hot oil. Fry on both sides until golden brown. Serve with fried seafood. Delicious!

title: prize cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir together dry ingredients; gradually add to shortening mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in mincemeat.

title: pork and hot slaw
directions: In large skillet, brown chops in hot Crisco; season with salt and pepper.
Drain off excess fat.
Add the 3 tablespoons water; cover immediately and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove chops; keep warm.
Blend the 1/4 cup water with the vinegar, flour, sugar, mustard, the 1 teaspoon salt, Worcestershire and celery seed. Stir into pan drippings.
Add cabbage.
Slice carrots into blender container.
Cut up onion; place in blender container.
Cover with cold water.
Blend until coarsely chopped.
Drain thoroughly. (Or, coarsely chop carrots and onion with knife.)
Add vegetables to skillet.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Return chops to skillet.
Simmer, covered, 5 minutes more.
(Cabbage will remain crunchy.)
Makes 5 servings.

title: wine cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in large bowl and beat at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for about 45 to 55 minutes or until center springs back when touched lightly.
Cool right side up for about 25 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt margarine in 9 x 13 baking dish. Mix dry ingredients. Pour melted margarine over dry ingredients. Add eggs and vanilla. Stir with spoon until mixed (do not beat). Add nuts. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Do not overbake. Brownies will be fudgy.

title: loyd's better peanut brittle
directions: Mix the sugar, water and Karo in a pot and cook to 270°, then add the peanuts and continue to cook to 290°.
Add the oleo and continue to cook to 300°.
Now add the heaping tablespoonful of baking soda, stir vigorously and pour onto Pammed foil.
Let it cool.
Do not try to flatten it out, it will be okay.
Break into pieces, serve and enjoy.

title: lemon squares
directions: Melt oleo in baking dish.
Mix in pan.
Pat out.
Bake 15 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: baked ham-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms. Drain. Remove stems; reserve caps. Chop stems to make 1 cup. Cook chopped stems and green onion in butter until tender. Stir in flour, savory and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Add wine and 2 tablespoons water. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Stir in ham and Parmesan.
Fill mushrooms with ham mixture. Place mushrooms in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender. Makes 24.

title: strawberries and creme
directions: Prepare Jell-O as directed on package but put in a shallow pan.
Cut into squares when set.
Add sugar to washed and stemmed berries; let set until sugar dissolves.
Combine cubed Jell-O, strawberries and Cool Whip.
Fold together in a large bowl.
Serve in dessert dishes.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Mix and cook until thick (between 1/2 to 1 hour).
Put into pint jars and seal while boiling hot.
This is good for pie and cookies.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hairdresser's friday night special
directions: Before you go to work, form loaf from ground beef.
Place on aluminum foil.
Finely dice onions and potatoes.
Put potatoes, onions, butter, salt and pepper on top of loaf.
Tightly close aluminum foil.
Bake on grill until done or bake 1 hour in oven at 300°.

title: quick and light marinara sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until onions are limp and transparent.
Using food processor or blender, puree tomatoes with liquid and add to onions.
Add herbs and sugar.
Cover and simmer for approximately 20 minutes or until sauce is cooked down to 2/3 of its original volume.
Remove parsley sprigs.
Leave other herbs in the sauce.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in half and roll in mixture of 1/3 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Scatter in greased Bundt pan (angel food
pan okay).
Combine and boil 1 1/2 sticks butter, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 cup brown sugar.
Pour over biscuits in pan.
Bake at
350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until biscuits are crusty.
Cool for
minutes in pan, then pour out onto platter.

title: chocolate snowballs
directions: Cream the margarine with vanilla until soft. Add sugar gradually and blend well. Add eggs, flour and salt. Stir in chocolate bits and nuts. Mix thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool slightly, then roll in confectioners sugar.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: tuna-mushroom casserole
directions: In casserole dish (greased with butter), put a layer of whole potato chips, then a layer of crumbled tuna, hard-boiled eggs (cut thin), then a layer of soup.
Top with crushed potato chips. Cover casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream together cream cheese and butter. Add honey to taste. Mix well. Add nuts and vanilla. Mix well.

title: chicken biscuit stew
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Melt margarine in iron skillet. Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Gradually add milk and broth, stirring until bubbly. Add chicken, onion, peas and carrots. Cook 1 minute. Remove from heat. Top with biscuits. Cook in oven until biscuits are done.

title: yeast rolls (quick)
directions: Dissolve yeast	in warm water;	mix in sugar, flour and margarine.	Sprinkle
more	flour
on
waxed
paper and knead. Pinch
off	dough;	make
into rolls and place in pans sprayed with
Pam.	Leave room in between for them to rise.
Let rise. If in a hurry, place rolls inside a warm oven (bake at lowest temperature)
for
approximately 30 minutes.
They then should be ready to
bake.
Bake
at 350° until golden brown.	Really delicious with melted butter brushed over top.

title: fruit salad
directions: Use fruit juices and add 1 1/2 cups to pudding and cook until thick.
Cool and
mix
with fruits.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Add bananas just before serving.

title: no bake chocolate and peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter on medium heat until it starts to boil.
Remove from heat and cool for 1 minute.
Add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oats.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: rice pudding
directions: Place rice in water with 1/2 teaspoon of salt, butter and grated lemon peel.
Stir well on low heat for about 1 minute. Cover and simmer for about 20 minutes.
When it's dry, add 1/2 gallon of milk and stir constantly.
When it begins to bubble, add egg yolks with sugar that have been beaten together separately. Pour into 1 large or several small dishes and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: cheesy-hominy casserole
directions: Combine 1 cup cheese, sour cream and chilies.
Stir in hominy. Pour into lightly greased square casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake 5 minutes, or until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: barbecued fish
directions: Place fish in greased shallow pan; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Lightly brown onions in fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 5 minutes, then pour over fish.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 35 to 40 minutes.
Baste fish with sauce while cooking. Serves 6.

title: mango ice-cream ii
directions: Whip the ice-cream, whipped topping and mango pulp until well combined.
Pour into a dish and freeze.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and pour into pie crust. Put in refrigerator until set. Serve cold.

title: blueberry kuchen
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, salt and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Work in margarine with fingers.
Mix in vinegar.
Use a 9-inch loose-bottom layer-cake pan 1 1/2-inches deep.
Spread crust mixture on bottom to depth of 1/4 inch and thinly around sides to height of 1 inch.
Combine 1 cup granulated sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and the cinnamon.
Add 2 cups blueberries and pour into crust.
Bake in 400° oven for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and put 1 cup raw blueberries on top.
Cool and remove rim of pan.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Serves 8.

title: orange punch
directions: Mix together sherbert, ice cream and juice in blender, blend well, then add ginger ale. Serve with ice.

title: country pate
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Insert metal blade into food processor. Drop garlic through feed tube.
When finely chopped scrape bowl and add the onion, veal or poultry and bacon.
Process until very smooth, about 3 1/2 minutes, stopping to scrape the bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
(Caution with salt since bacon and ham may be salty.)
Process until ham is finely chopped, approximately 45 seconds.
Pack mixture firmly into 5 1/2 cup loaf pan.
Bake until top is nicely browned and meat has pulled away from sides, 45 to 60 minutes.
If browning too fast, cover with aluminum foil.
Drain off liquid and let cool.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Better served day after made.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Chill until it thickens.
Fold in apples, celery and walnuts.
Spoon into 6 cup mold and chill about 4 hours.

title: phyllis' potato puffs
directions: Heat oil to 375°.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add leftover mashed potatoes.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls into hot oil.
Do about 5 or 6 at a time. Fry 3 to 4 minutes, turning or until golden brown.
Watch since they brown quickly.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes 1 to 2 dozen, depending on your size heaping teaspoonful!

title: tomato cheese spread
directions: In a pan, warm 1 can tomato soup and cream cheese until cheese is smooth.
Dissolve 1 envelope Knox gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water; add to soup while hot.
Cool and add mayonnaise, celery, green pepper and onion.
Refrigerate until set.
Serve with crackers.

title: beef pie
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Return to stove over low heat and add tomato soup.
Sprinkle top with seasonings and Parmesan cheese. Stir in and sprinkle again.
Unroll crescent rolls and line 9-inch pie pan.
Put in hamburger mixture and top with Velveeta cheese slices.
Bake for 25 minutes at 375° or until cheese melts.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan. Beat sugar, vanilla, cinnamon, milk, and eggs together. Blend in pumpkin. Pour into pan. Sprinkle cake mix on top; sprinkle nuts then drizzle margarine over. Bake about 45 minutes. If pecans begin to brown too fast, reduce heat or cover with a sheet of foil.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown seasoned hamburger with onion and green pepper, breaking meat up with a spoon.
Drain.
Dissolve bouillon or soup in the hot water.
Pour over meat.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in potatoes along with milk.
Add butter, coconut and nuts.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring once.

title: stuffed pork florentine
directions: Split pork tenderloin lengthwise and flatten out.
Spread pork sausage over meat.
Then put spinach down the middle.
Roll up and put bacon around meat.
Secure with toothpicks.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours until done.

title: chicken caldo(great low-fat recipe)
directions: *Vegetables may be any combination of chopped spinach, chopped cabbage, chopped tomatoes, kernel corn, shredded carrots, diced squash, or any other ideas you may have.

title: camp bread
directions: Cook in hot grease.

title: pink lemon fizz
directions: Combine punch and lemonade concentrate in a large pitcher; stir until lemonade melts.
Chill well.
Just before serving, stir in 7-Up.
Pour over ice.

title: cheater's chili con queso
directions: Combine all ingredients in one dish.
You can cook in the crock pot for two hours on high heat; heat on stove-top until cheese is melted; or, you can microwave until cheese is melted. Serve with chips.

title: low-fat apple bread
directions: Beat eggs, stir in other ingredients.
Add nuts and raisins if desired.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cucumber-tomato salad
directions: Slice cucumbers, tomatoes and onions in large bowl.
Add vinegar, water and sugar.
Chill.

title: jerry may's polish mistakes
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage and onion; drain well.
Add cubed cheese and seasonings.
Stir well until cheese is melted.
Cool and spread mixture on rye bread.
Makes enough topping for 1 1/2 loaves.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar.
Add water gradually.
Add vinegar. Add slightly beaten eggs.
Cook until thick.
Set off to cool. Put cheese and pimento through food chopper.
Add this to sauce and stir until cheese has softened and thickened the mixture.
Add pimento juice if needed.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix all ingredients, except mushroom soup and water.
Make into patties and brown in bacon drippings.
Place in baking dish. Mix the mushroom soup and water; pour over patties.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Serves 5 or 6, depending on size of patties.

title: rosemary chicken
directions: At medium-high heat in 12-inch skillet add oil and place chicken breast, skin side down.
Sprinkle with salt and rosemary. Cook about 5 minutes until brown.
Turn chicken over, reduce heat and cook about 5 minutes more, until juices run clear when pierced with a knife.

title: fantastic chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl. Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended. Mix egg into creamed mixture.

title: micro magic fudge
directions: Place all ingredients, except nuts, milk and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Remove from oven. Add rest of ingredients and stir well.
Pour into buttered dish. Chill 20 to 30 minutes.

title: everyday cookies
directions: Blend sugars, margarine, oil and egg.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients to flour; fold into creamed mixture and mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Fold in Rice Krispies and oats.
Chill for easier handling.
Form into balls and flatten with glass.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 90 cookies.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine first five ingredients until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: veal chops
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over moderate heat.
Coat chops with flour, shaking off excess.
Brown chops in skillet on both sides, about 5 minutes per side.
Remove to a plate.

title: spinach pie
directions: Cook the spinach and drain.
Add the cottage cheese, eggs and seasonings.
Spoon into an 8-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and dot with margarine.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Yields 4 servings.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup pecans and 2 cups bananas. Spoon batter into 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pans and frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: baked cheese grits
directions: Bring milk to a boil, add grits and cook until thickened, about 10 minutes, stirring often. Add butter, salt and both cheeses, stirring until blended. Spoon into a lightly greased, one quart casserole dish, bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Yield: 6-8 servings.

title: crock pot clam chowder
directions: Place bacon in bottom of crock pot.
Add margarine, onions and celery.
Cook on high until margarine melts and cook celery and onion about 15 minutes.
Combine other ingredients and cook on high one hour - turn to low and continue to cook for about four hours.

title: pink lemonade pops
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into dixie cups.
Freeze for one hour, until slushy.
Place a wooden stick in center of each and freeze overnight.
Peel the paper from the pops before serving.

title: chicken vegetable stir-fry
directions: Stir together cornstarch, ginger, broth and soy sauce until smooth.
Set aside.
In skillet, in 3 tablespoons oil. brown chicken.
Set aside.
In skillet in remaining 3 tablespoons oil, stir-fry vegetables with garlic until tender and crisp.
Stir in reserved chicken broth mixture.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens.
Serve over rice.

title: frozen yogurt with fruit
directions: Just combine fruit juice and yogurt in any proportion you like, about half and half works fine.
Pour in a popsicle maker and freeze.

title: caramel corn
directions: Have the corn popped.
Keep popped corn in warm oven until syrup is ready.

title: lemon bread
directions: Grease and lightly flour loaf pan.
Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs; blend.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (small pan) or 60 minutes (large pan).

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix the cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar until creamy. Mix milk, pudding and Cool Whip together.

Mix all together. Layer the mixture and cookies, starting and ending with cookies. As a center piece or conversation piece, put mixture in a flowerpot with gummy worms; top with a bunch of silk flowers.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix jello and milk; let stand 5 minutes.
Blend in Cool Whip. Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Put pudding on top of them, then cherry pie filling.
Top with leftover Cool Whip.
Can be layered.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle butterscotch, chocolate chips, coconut, pecans over graham cracker.
Pour the sweetened condensed milk over the ingredients.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Its a fast recipe to make and everyone loves these cookies.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Blend into sugar mixture. Stir in oats, Wheaties and chocolate chips. Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: crunch cherry dessert
directions: Mix the margarine, flour and pecans together to form a pie crust and press into a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Let cool.
Combine cream cheese, lemon juice and powdered sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread on baked crust.
Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate.
Can be made a day ahead.

title: marilyn's fruit salad
directions: Mix above ingredients together; thicken in microwave approximately 4 minutes. Check after 2 minutes and check every 30 seconds thereafter. Mixture should be pudding consistency. Stir to create smooth mixture. Cool, then add 9 ounces Cool Whip.

title: buffalo swiss steak
directions: Cut round steak in 3/4-inch slices.
Cut pieces into individual servings.
Dredge in flour.
Brown in cooking oil, which has been lightly flavored with garlic.
Place a layer of meat in bottom of flat oven pan.
Cover with a layer of onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Pour can of tomatoes over the top. Add salt/pepper to taste.
Bake at 250° until tender.
(If you are going to the trouble of finding buffalo steak, invite a large group; this recipe serves 40.)

title: the very best zucchini bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Mix all other ingredients in a separate bowl.
Combine the dry and wet ingredients.
Bake in 2 loaf pans for 45 - 60 minutes at 350 degrees.
For muffins decrease time to 20
- 25 minutes.

title: texas ice cream bars(diet)
directions: Soften ice cream.
(I use chocolate.)
Mix ingredients (I also use chocolate pudding) and freeze in an 8 x 8-inch glass dish. When frozen, cut into 8 equal bars.
Wrap individually in Saran Wrap.
Refreeze and eat as wanted.
Makes 8 servings.

title: ginger fizz
directions: Combine ginger, mint, lemon zest and honey in a heatproof pitcher.
Pour boiling water over mixture; stir well and let steep for 30 minutes.
Strain and discard solids.
Combine ginger liquid with pineapple and grapefruit juices and vanilla.
This mixture can be frozen or stored in the refrigerator up to 7 days.
To serve, fill a tall glass with ice, then half fill with sparkling water.
Fill the rest with ginger mixture and stir.
Makes approximately 9 cups.

title: poppy seed french bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except cheese.
Cut bread into slices.
Spread each slice with oleo mixture and put a slice of cheese on each.
Put back together as a loaf and put remaining oleo on top of bread.
Wrap in foil, leaving top open.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: walnut crescents (cookies)
directions: Cream butter and 1/4 cup confectioners sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Shape in rolls 1/2-inch in diameter and cut in 1 to 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Put on cookie sheet, no grease and pull ends to form crescent shape.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes (preheat oven).
Remove cookies while a little warm and roll in confectioners sugar.
Then when cool, sift some more confectioners sugar over the tops.

title: peppered rice
directions: Combine water and bouillon cube in a medium saucepan; bring water to a boil, stirring to dissolve cube.
Stir in rice, garlic powder and pepper.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is tender and water is absorbed.
Remove from heat. Add parsley and toss.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: scampi
directions: Rinse shrimp; remove shells, leaving tails, if desired.
Heat oil and butter in large skillet.
Add garlic; cook slowly until golden.
Add shrimp.
Sprinkle with parsley, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, for 3 or 4 minutes, until shrimp are pink.
Sprinkle with lemon juice; stir until hot.
Serve over pasta; sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Pass cheese when serving.
Serve with a green salad and good, crusty bread.
Good, fast company meal.

title: finger drumsticks
directions: Cut off tips of wings; divide each wing in half.
Place on broiler rack.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Mix the other ingredients in saucepan, stirring until thick, about 3 minutes. Turn chicken over, spread with sauce and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: yeast biscuit
directions: Mix water, sugar and yeast.
(I mix sugar and dry yeast and then add water.)
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Marinate carrots in tomato soup mixture for 8 hours.
Freeze if desired and just heat.
Mix together and heat after marinated. Can be served hot or cold.

title: spicy black beans
directions: Heat oil in
medium saucepan. Saute garlic until tender, about 2 minutes.
Add beans, salsa and lime juice.
Simmer until heated through, about 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in tomato and sprinkle with cilantro.

title: cheesy garlic biscuits
directions: Combine Bisquick and 1/4 teaspoon of the garlic powder; mix in cheese.
Add milk, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Roll dough on floured surface to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with a 1 1/2-inch cutter.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Combine melted butter and the remaining 1/8 teaspoon garlic powder; brush on top of biscuits.
Bake for 10 minutes. Makes 12 biscuits.
These taste just like the ones they serve at Red Lobster!

title: fruit dip
directions: In a bowl, mix all the ingredients until smooth and creamy. Refrigerate several hours or until chilled.
This dip is especially good with strawberries or any fruit.

title: teriyaki cod fillets
directions: In shallow microwave dish, combine sherry, water, soy sauce, oil, ginger root (or lemon rind), sugar and garlic; stir to mix. Add fish fillets in a single layer.
Marinate at room temperature for 20 minutes or prepare and refrigerate for 4 hours, turning once or twice.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Add half of hash browns. Mix soup, sour cream, milk and onions.
Pour half of this over hash browns plus 1 cup grated cheese.
Add rest of potatoes and pour remaining mixture over.
Add rest of cheese.
Sprinkle cornflakes over.
Pour the other 2 tablespoons oleo over all.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cookies, candy and cream(ice cream dessert)
directions: Mix ingredients all together and pour in 9 x 13-inch pan. Freeze for several hours before serving.
This is so simple and so good.
It will keep indefinitely in freezer if covered.
This can also be served with hot fudge sauce and an extra dollop of whipped topping to dress it up a bit.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease a loaf pan with cooking spray.
Mix sugar, bananas, oil and eggs in a large bowl with a wooden spoon. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake until toothpick inserted in center of bread comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes around 6 dozen.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Set aside 1 cup of cake mix. With a fork, blend remainder of dry cake mix, melted butter and egg until moist. Press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased and floured pan. In a large mixing bowl, combine pumpkin, eggs, brown sugar, milk, cinnamon and white sugar; beat on low speed until smooth. Pour over bottom layer or crust.

title: little red hen's bread recipe
directions: Mix well.
Spoon out onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften; add the remaining ingredients.
Mix until orange in color.
May add dried onion and horseradish (if you like a hot dip) in small amounts.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix with beater.
Serve as a dip with fruit (apple slices, grapes, peaches, etc.).

title: red potato and bacon salad(12 servings)
directions: In a 5 quart saucepan, combine the red potatoes with enough water to cover.
Add 2 teaspoons salt.
Heat to boiling over high heat.
Reduce the heat.
Cover and simmer until tender, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Cook the bacon in 2 tablespoons olive oil over medium heat until browned, about 5 minutes.
With a large slotted spoon, transfer to paper towels to drain.	Chop.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the cider vinegar, 1/4 cup olive oil, sugar mustard, remaining 1-1/2 teaspoons salt and ground black pepper.
Whisk until well combined.
Drain potatoes.
Add hot potatoes to mixture in bowl; with a rubber spatula, fold potatoes into dressing.
Let potatoes cool for about 30 minutes before stirring in the chopped green onion.
Cover and refrigerate.
Sprinkle with chopped bacon to serve.

title: broccoli cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well.

title: blue cheese coleslaw
directions: Mix cabbage and onions; chill.
Combine horseradish, mayonnaise and 1/4 cup of cheese.
Stir well.
Mix together. Garnish with Blue cheese.

title: chili and cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in microwave until completely melted.
Stir in chili.
Serve warm with tacos, Tostitos, Doritos chips or on hot dogs.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Mix water and yeast.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix until dough forms.
Let stand for an hour and drop in hot oil by teaspoons.
Roll in mixture of cinnamon and sugar.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Put meat in baking dish.
Cut up onion and put on top of chicken.
Place cheese on top of onion. Crumble 1/2 bag of Doritos on top of cheese.
Mix together soups and Ro-Tel; pour over Doritos.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli flowerets into small pieces; cut off tough outer layer of the stalks and chop the tender parts into small pieces. You need about 8 cups broccoli.
In a small skillet, saute the bacon until crisp; set aside.
Slice onion lengthwise, then cut into julienne strips.
In a large bowl, combine broccoli, onion, raisins and bacon.
In small bowl, whisk together mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and pepper.
Combine dressing with vegetables and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.
Top with sunflower seeds.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken and cheese roll
directions: Flatten chicken breasts.
Roll cheese up in chicken, place in small casserole dish.
Sprinkle parsley flakes and garlic powder. Cook for about 45 minutes.
Remove from oven, sprinkle a little cheese on top.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ground beef, evaporated milk and onion soup mix in large mixing bowl.
Place ground beef mixture in shallow baking pan.
Shape into a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yields 4 servings.

title: squash delight casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender.
Drain.
Add butter and mash with fork.
Mix sugar, egg, mayonnaise, nuts, salt and pepper and cheese.
Add squash.
Pour into casserole dish and top with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Turn
oven
on	to
Put	margarine
in bottom of casserole and melt.
After margarine has melted, stir in rice, soup, water and mushrooms.	Cook for 1 hour, stirring every 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Combine all of the above; mix well.
Put into greased casserole; cover.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: lemon baked chicken for 100(1 piece each)
directions: Wash chicken under running water.
Drain.
Combine paprika, pepper and salt.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Let stand 1/2 hour. Dredge chicken in flour.
Combine lemon juice, honey and oil.
Set aside.
Grease baking sheet pan(s) with melted margarine.
Place chicken on pan skin side down.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Turn chicken over and pour lemon juice mixture over it. Do not cover.
Return to oven and bake additional 20 to 30 minutes until tender.
To serve 50, use half recipe.
Cooking time is the same.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain grease off of beef.
Add beans; stir in sour cream, then add cheese and salsa sauce.
Let it cook for about 15 minutes and serve with nacho chips.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add liquids.
Mix well.
Makes 60 muffins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix will keep in a jar in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.

title: spinach rockafeller
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle some extra Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Two cups of cold mashed potatoes and stir into it six tablespoons melted butter, beating to a white cream before adding anything else.
Add two eggs, whipped very light and a teacup of cream, salt to taste.
Beat this thoroughly and pour into a baking dish, bake in a quick oven until browned.
If properly mixed it will be very light and good, better than any mashed potatoes.

title: cranberry apple crunch
directions: Mix sugar and water in a large pan. Boil for 5 minutes.
Add cranberries and cook for 5 more minutes. Remove from heat. Add apples and pour into buttered pan.

title: mexican stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Remove stems.
Chop pepperoni and red pepper.
Grate cheese.
Mix together.
Fill mushrooms.
Microwave for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on High.
Makes 4 servings.

title: white chocolate fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream and margarine in heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a full, rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling for 7 minutes, over medium heat, or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly, to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate until melted.
Add remaining ingredients; beat until well blended.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix together strawberries and glaze.
Mix together milk, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers, strawberry mixture and then Cool Whip mixture.
Garnish with whole strawberries.

title: nellou's fruit salad
directions: Drain 1 cup pineapple juice.
Mix the juice with the dry pudding.
Microwave on High for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes.
Let cool. Mix pineapple chunks, drained oranges, banana and halved cherries.
Fold the cooled pudding mix into the fruit. Refrigerate.

title: cheesy onion chicken
directions: Melt butter in dish.
Add seasoned salt.
Roll chicken in mixture.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave 5 to 6 minutes.
Turn chicken and add mushrooms.
Cover and cook another 5 to 6 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese, onion and more cheese.
Microwave for 3 minutes more.

title: congo bars
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Stir brown sugar and butter.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well.
Add flour and mix in nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla. Pour into a greased waxed pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 40 plus.

title: chocolate chip cookies(matthew thinks they are better than mrs. fields)
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla, beating well.

title: tuna souffle
directions: Cook bread crumbs in milk for 5 minutes.
Add seasonings and beaten egg yolks.
Flake tuna into crumb mixture, adding oil from can.
Fold in beaten egg whites and tuna into 1-quart casserole. Place casserole in pan of hot water and bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: orange jello dessert
directions: Mix together and chill.
May add nuts.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Place meat in large mixing bowl.
Mix in finely chopped onion; add sausage, parsley and cumin.
Cover and refrigerate while boiling 6 eggs.
Roll eggs in flour until very dry.
Divide meat by 6.
Flatten to ovals 2 times the size of an egg.
Mold meat mix around egg.
Beat 3 raw eggs.
Roll coated eggs in a little flour, then dip into beaten egg, then dip into bread crumbs.
Place eggs on plate; chill for at least 30 minutes. Heat oil in deep fryer to 375°.
Fry 2 or 3 eggs for 10 minutes or until meat is cooked and coating is golden brown.
Drain.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful 1-2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15-20 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: hedge-apple pie
directions: Boil hedge apples, green peppers and canned beets in root beer and 3 cups water.

title: pudding pie
directions: Pour cold milk in mixing bowl.
Add pudding mix and ice cream. Beat slowly until well blended (1 to 2 minutes).
Pour into ready made 9-inch crust.
Chill.
Topping can be used (Cool Whip or Wilderness fruit toppings).
Refrigerate for 3 hours before serving.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Remove any twigs and shrivelled berries.
Put all the ingredients in a saucepan and bring to boil over medium heat. Simmer for 12 to 15 minutes.
Chill.
Lasts for 1 month in the fridge, longer if frozen.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Dissolve sugar in water in saucepan over medium heat.
Add peanuts and continue to cook, stirring frequently.
Cook until peanuts are completely sugar coated and no syrup.
Pour on ungreased cookie sheet.
Separate peanuts with fork.
Bake at 300° for approximately 30 minutes, stirring at 10 minute intervals.

title: microwave mochi
directions: Oil 2-quart microwave Bundt pan.
Mix all ingredients, except for the an and the katakuri.
Pour mixture into the pan.
Cover pan with plastic wrap.
Bake for 16 minutes on High in the microwave oven.
Let stand in the oven for a few minutes.
Take the mochi out on a katakuri dusted cutting board.
Cool.
Cut into serving pieces or cut and fill with an.

title: buckwheat pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add milk and eggs, then shortening.
Fry on greased hot griddle.
Serve hot with syrup.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Add flour, soda, milk and vanilla.
Mash bananas.
Add pecans; stir.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: In large Pyrex dish, pour hash browns.
Melt 1 stick butter and pour over top.
Mix together all other ingredients and pour over hash browns.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into greased pan.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: beth's prune cake
directions: This is an old recipe from my mother, hence some of the directions are antiquated.
The cake keeps well and is very moist. By its taste, it is hard to realize that the main ingredient is prunes!

title: halupsie (german dish)
directions: Boil the rice and drain. Add the ground beef, eggs, milk, 1 cup mashed tomatoes, 1 medium onion, salt and pepper to taste. Place cabbage leaves in boiling water a few minutes. Put filling in cabbage leaves and roll together. Put in roaster. Pour 1 pint mashed tomatoes over the top and bake at 300° until cabbage is done.

title: party spread
directions: Grate cucumber and set aside. Squeeze all juice from the cucumber. Blend all ingredients together. Add additional mayonnaise, if needed. Serve with crackers or on bread as open-faced party sandwiches.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place sugar, butter and milk in pan and boil for 5 minutes. Take off stove and stir in marshmallows and peanut butter.
Stir well, pour into buttered 9-inch pan.
Cool.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake corn bread according to directions.
Cool and crumble in bowl.
Add the other ingredients.
Spread salad dressing or mayonnaise on top.
Stir carefully just before serving.
Cheese can also be added.
This makes a filling and colorful luncheon dish.

title: chilled beet salad
directions: Mix and boil for 10 minutes the sugar, vinegar and water. Drain beets, saving juice.
Soften Knox gelatine in beet juice. Mix with hot vinegar liquid.
Cool chopped beets.
Add to cooled liquid along with crushed pineapple and chopped pecans.
Pour into mold and chill in refrigerator.
Serves 6.

title: low-fat orange chocolate chip bread
directions: Combine milk, orange juice, sugar, egg and orange peel in a small bowl.
Place baking mix in medium mixing bowl.
Stir milk mixture into baking mix, beating until well combined, about 1 minute.
Stir in mini chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes. Remove from pan.
Cool. Slice and serve.
Makes 16 servings.

title: spanish delight
directions: Cut onion and green pepper and fry in salad oil.
Add ground beef and brown.
Mix onion, pepper and beef with catsup, corn, mushrooms, chili powder and noodles.
Put in greased casserole. Top with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift all dry ingredients together in large bowl.
Add shortening, buttermilk and yeast; mix well.
Turn out onto floured surface; knead well.
Cover; refrigerate. When ready to bake, pinch off as much dough as needed.
Keep remaining dough in refrigerator.
Roll out amount you are using to about 1/2 inch thickness.
Let sit in pan to rise for 15 to 20 minutes. Bake in 375° oven until brown, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel jello
directions: Mix strawberry jello, boiling water and frozen strawberries and juice together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until set.

title: whole wheat popovers
directions: Place a muffin pan with 12 three-inch cups in oven.
Heat to 450°.
In a small bowl, place flour and salt, slowly adding milk to flour while beating.
Add eggs and beat at medium speed 3 minutes.
Remove hot muffin pan and butter quickly.
Fill with batter.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 minutes longer.
Brush with melted butter and serve piping hot.

title: irish creme
directions: Blend or mix in blender all ingredients.
Keeps refrigerated for up to 3 weeks.

title: paella
directions: Saute shrimp and garlic in butter until shrimp are pink, about 2 minutes.
Stir in cornstarch and cook 1 minute.
Add broth, tomatoes, pepperoni, vegetables and cayenne pepper.
Bring to a full boil, stirring occasionally.
Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: orange bread
directions: Beat butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, orange peel, orange extract and milk to butter and sugar.
Mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and pecans.
Mix until all ingredients are combined. Grease and flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Best second day; freezes well.
I usually double the recipe.

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: Mix, play and eat!

title: fudge
directions: In a large saucepan melt cheese and butter.
Sift together cocoa and sugar; add to cheese and butter and mix well.
Add vanilla flavoring and optional nuts; mix well.
Mixture will be thick.
Press into dishes greased with butter.
Let cool and cut into squares.
This makes a very creamy fudge.
Your friends and family will be very surprised that you made it with cheese.

title: microwave pecan pralines
directions: Mix all ingredients except baking soda and vanilla; pour into a microwavable dish.
Cook for 16 minutes, hand stirring every 4 minutes.
Add baking soda until foamy.
Stir for 1 minute on High with mixer.
Add vanilla.
Hand stir until tacky, and let sit until hardened on waxed paper.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Melt butter.
Dip chicken in butter and dry ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry-orange glazed pumpkin bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix together flour, sugar, baking soda, pumpkin pie spices, salt and baking powder.
In second bowl, stir together remaining ingredients until well mixed.
Add pumpkin mixture to flour mixture and stir until all ingredients are well moistened.
Pour batter into two 9 1/4 x 5 1/4 x 2-inch greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes or until bread tests done with wooden picks.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then remove to cooling rack.
Completely cool bread then drizzle glaze over top and sides. Makes 2 loaves.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons to a cup of hot water.
Stores well if kept dry.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake quiche pastry for 5 minutes; set aside.
Reduce oven temperature to 375°.
Spread 3/4 of the cheese and spinach on the bottom of the pastry.
Beat the cream, eggs and salt together until frothy.
Pour over cheese and spinach. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and dot with butter.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until filling is set.

title: steamed fish
directions: Slice fish and lay in flat cooking pan.
Place all ingredients on top of dish.
Cover; steam for 20 minutes.
Serve with your favorite vegetables.

title: blackberry ice cream
directions: Reserve 2 cups blackberries; sprinkle sugar over the remaining 3 cups.
In a small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over water and set aside for 5 minutes to soften.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly, to dissolve gelatin.
Puree sugared blackberries in a blender.
Put through a strainer to remove most of the seeds.
Add dissolved gelatin to puree, then the reserved 2 cups blackberries, the lemon juice and the cream.
Process in an ice cream maker until soft. Add beaten egg whites to soft ice cream; process until ice cream is firm.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Prepare cake mix according to box instructions.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done. Prepare pudding by package directions.
Blend with cream cheese. Spread over cake.
Spoon pie filling over pudding-cream cheese. Top with Cool Whip.
Chill for several hours.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together; place in dish.
Cover with remaining ingredients.
Bake for 40 minutes at 325°.

title: guacamole salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve on crisp lettuce, if desired.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt together. Add milk.
Heat cocoa mixture and milk until warm.
Beat egg yolks a little.
Add a little of heated cocoa mixture.
Pour back into cocoa mixture. Cook until thick and add butter and vanilla.
Pour in baked pie shell and add margarine.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Cook raisins and water until 1/2 cup liquid remains.
Cream shortening and sugar, then add egg, flour and soda, baking powder and vanilla.
Then add the raisins.
Drop by spoonful onto a baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon oil 1 to 2 minutes. Add the eggs and stir-fry until eggs are set and moist. Remove eggs.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil 1 to 2 minutes and add rice.
Stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes. Remove rice.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil 1 minute.
Add celery. Stir-fry 1 minute. Add bean sprouts and mushrooms. Stir-fry 1 minute. Stir-fry green onions and soy sauce. Return rice and egg to pan. Stir-fry 30 seconds and serve.

title: mock ham dip
directions: Grind hot dogs, egg and pickle slices.
Mix with mayonnaise. Serve with corn chips or crackers.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar in large bowl.
Bring Coca-Cola to a boil with cocoa and margarine.
Pour the boiled mixture into the flour and sugar; stir well.
Add milk with the soda and add eggs.
Stir in marshmallows and pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter snack
directions: Mix peanut butter and honey; add dry milk and raisins, nuts and coconut.
Roll into balls and then in nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat until well blended.
Melt butter, then cool.
Blend in cooled butter.
Stir in chips and walnuts.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Good warm or cold, alone or with either whipped cream or ice cream.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Add last two ingredients after it starts to thicken.

title: hot turkey or chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Toss lightly.
Pile lightly into large dish or casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese, then chips.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Serves 4.

title: toffee bars
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend egg and vanilla.
Add flour; mix well.
Spread dough into 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Place chocolate bars over hot dough; sprinkle with nuts.
Cool; cut into bars.
Makes approximately 3 1/2 dozen.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in boiling water.
Break eggs into cup and fill up with milk to 1 cup.
Break cheese and oleo.
Add to grits.
Mix. Add egg mixture and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese and paprika on top.

title: snowy white fudge
directions: Let margarine begin to melt in a heavy 3-quart saucepan. Brush sides of pan with melted butter.
Add evaporated milk and sugar.
Cook over medium heat to boiling, about 8 minutes, whisking constantly to dissolve sugar.

title: spicy hopping john
directions: Rinse peas.
Combine peas and water; let stand overnight.
Do not drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice.
Cover and simmer until peas are tender, about 1 1/4 hours.
Lift out ham hock; remove meat from bone, dice and return to pea mixture.
Add rice; cover and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Add more water, if desired.
Remove bay leaf.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place slices of dried beef on bottom of 9 x 11 glass baking dish.
Then chicken breasts, and a slice of bacon on top of each piece of chicken.
(I like to cook the bacon partially first.) Make sauce by mixing sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken, spaced slightly apart, not layered.
Sprinkle parsley flakes and paprika over each breast.

title: fresh mushroom sauce
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt butter.
Add mushrooms and cook until tender.
Stir in flour.
Cook 1 minute.
Gradually add beef broth, meat drippings and pepper.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Makes 4 cups.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook washed rice in 4 cups water for 45 minutes.
Add salt. Drain liquid.
Brown meat.
Add celery and onion; cook slightly. Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients and the ground beef mixture to the cooked wild rice.
Bake in a casserole at 350° for 1 hour.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Add sliced onion and green pepper.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Put rack on third level. Bake at 350°. Grease cookie sheets. Whisk together thoroughly the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Beat on medium until very fluffy and well blended the oil, butter, peanut butter, powdered sugar and brown sugar. Add and beat until well combined the large egg, large egg yolk and vanilla. Stir flour mixture into peanut butter mixture until well blended and smooth. Let dough stand for 5 minutes.

title: vivian's blueberry salad
directions: Drain juice from blueberries and pineapple.
Add water to juice to make 3 1/2 cups.
Bring to a boil, then add Jell-O.
Pour in dish to cool.
When cool, add fruit and nuts.
Let gel.
Mix Cool Whip, sour cream and sugar.
Use as topping for Jell-O mixture.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour. Separate egg yolk from white. Mix yolk and water and mix with sugar and flour. Cook. When nearly cooked, add butter and vanilla. Pour in baked crust. Beat egg whites and about 2 teaspoons sugar. Place on top of pie and brown in oven. Cool.

title: strawberry buttermilk sherbet
directions: Mix the strawberries and sugar in a medium size bowl and let stand for 10 minutes.
Transfer to a food processor or an electric blender and puree about 30 seconds.
Add the buttermilk and lime juice; whirl briefly to combine.
Pour the mixture into an ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cover with plastic food wrap and freeze until firm, about 3 hours.

title: carrot ring
directions: Grease mold and cook in a pan of water at 375° for about 35 minutes.
Fill center with creamed peas or lima beans.

title: mushrooms supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan (except salt). Bring to a slow boil on medium heat.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cook 5 or 6 hours with pot covered; remove top and cook another 3 to 5 hours until the liquid reduces to where it barely covers the mushrooms.
Now taste to determine if salt is needed.
Allow to cool and then store in refrigerator until ready to use.
They can be frozen, if desired.
Should be served hot as a side dish or in a chafing dish as hors d'oeuvres.

title: marlene's fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit, reserving liquid. Mix pudding according to package directions, using reserved fruit juice instead of milk. Cook until it starts to thicken. Remove from heat and cool. Add drained fruits and mix lightly. Add bananas and grapes. Refrigerate.

title: dressed up cabbage
directions: Clean, wash and cut cabbage, bell pepper, celery, onion and carrots to suit yourself; put the oil and 1/2 cup of water in a pot.
Add vegetables and seasoning.
Sprinkle pickles and juice over the mixture.
Simmer until tender.

title: yummy chocolate cake
directions: Mix in saucepan water, cocoa and margarine.
Bring to boil. Have sifted together flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Pour hot butter mixture into dry ingredients all at once, stir well.
Beat eggs, add buttermilk and stir into batter.
Pour into greased pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°

title: perfect apple pie(a sugar-free dessert)
directions: Combine Splenda, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Mix with apples. Line a 9-inch pie plate with crust.
Fill with apple mixture.
Pat mixture with butter.
Adjust top crust and brush with egg white. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: senate bean soup
directions: Soak the beans if necessary and drain.
Cover with cold water. Bring to boil and boil uncovered for 2 minutes.
Skim off any foam that rises to surface.
Cover and let stand for one hour.
Drain the beans and put them in a large pot.
Add 2 quarts water and hambone.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Add potatoes, onion, garlic and celery; simmer for 1 hour.
Remove hambone and cut up meat.
Set aside.
Remove 1 cup of beans and some liquid and puree in blender.
Return pureed beans and the meat to the soup.
Season and salt and pepper.
Heat until piping hot and serve, garnish with chopped parsley.

title: mini-cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Line muffin baking pan with paper cupcake liners; place 1 wager on bottom of each liner.
In a medium bowl, beat cream cheese; add sugar and beat again.
Add eggs, lemon juice and vanilla and beat till light and fluffy.
Fill line to 2/3 full of cream cheese mixture.
Bake 15-20 minutes.
Remove from oven and pan; cool.
Top w/ desired pie filling.

title: molded tuna salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water; dissolve over hot water.
Cream the cream cheese and mayonnaise; add gelatin, tuna (albacore), carrots, pickles and celery.
Mix lightly.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Drain pickles well.
Slice in chunks.
Put in large bowl.
Mix sugar, spices and vinegar well.
Pour over dills.
Mix until sugar is dissolved.
Stir often.
Return to jar.

title: bob's rum raisin french toast
directions: Combine melted ice cream, eggs, rum, cinnamon and nuts in a bowl.
Beat with a wire whisk until well mixed.
Dip raisin bread into egg mixture, coating well on both sides.
Saute in butter over medium heat until toasted.
Serve with a scoop of rum raisin ice cream topped with maple syrup.
Makes 4 servings.

title: country fried steak
directions: Cut steak into pieces.
Salt and pepper the pieces.
Roll the pieces in flour.
Brown them in hot fat in a heavy frying pan. Add water and cover the pan.
Simmer the meat until it is tender.

title: endives au gratin
directions: In a small saucepan, combine chicken stock and 1/3 cup of the milk; bring to a simmer.
In a small bowl, blend flour and the remaining 1/3 cup milk into a paste.
Whisk the chicken stock mixture in the saucepan.
Cook, whisking constantly, for about 5 minutes, or until thickened.
Add nutmeg and season with salt and pepper.
(The sauce can be prepared ahead.
Place plastic wrap directly over surface to prevent a skin from forming.
Refrigerate for up to 2 days.
Reheat before continuing.)
Trim the outer leaves from the endives.
Using a small sharp knife, remove all the dark cone at the base of the endive.
Place endives in a single layer in a steamer basket over boiling water.
Cover and steam for about 20 minutes, or until the endives are very tender.

title: cheese and pasta in a pot
directions: Cook ground beef in a large, deep frying pan until brown, stirring often.
Drain fat.
Add onions, garlic, spaghetti sauce, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Mix well and simmer 20 minutes or until onions are soft.

title: banana pineapple punch
directions: Add sugar to water.
Boil.
Set aside to cool.
After cool, add orange juice concentrate plus 3 cans of water.

title: curried shrimp(serves 8)
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter in 3-quart saucepan; stir in curry powder. Add celery, green pepper and parsley.
Saute 2 or 3 minutes. Stir in flour and salt.
Remove from heat; gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thick.
Cook 2 additional minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese until melted.
Add shrimp and pimento.
Heat to serving temperature; do not boil.

title: easy lemon bars
directions: Mix cake mix and pie filling together with spoon.
Pour into an ungreased jelly roll pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
When cool, frost with lemon flavored frosting.

title: spicy spareribs
directions: Cut the slab into individual ribs, putting the pieces in a large pot.
Cover the ribs with water; simmer for 20 minutes. Drain off water and put ribs in a baking pan.
In a small saucepan, combine the brown sugar, vinegar, soy sauce, salt and ginger.
Bring to a boil.
Add the pineapple with juice and coconut, if desired.
Reduce heat; simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Tabasco sauce.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Beat egg until light.
Add sugar gradually, then stir in vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Sift together, then add boiling milk in which butter has been melted, stirring all the time with rotary beater.
Put in shallow greased and floured pan and bake in 350° oven.
When cake is cool, frost with following icing.

title: fruit bars
directions: Put 3/4 dough in large cookie sheet.
Spread pie filling over this.
Dot rest of dough over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Drizzle powdered sugar frosting on top.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Combine all ingredients, except fruit.
Pour into oblong pan. Pour fruit juices over batter, then add fruit.
Pour 1/4 cup sugar over fruit.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: fresh strawberry shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Yields 3 cups.

title: sweet nothings
directions: Melt peanut butter, chocolate chips and margarine.
Mix with Rice Chex.
Place powdered sugar in large paper sack.
Pour in coated Rice Chex and shake.
Pour into large airtight container.

title: calico beans
directions: Drain kidney beans and cooked limas.
Brown bacon, hamburger and onion in large skillet.
Combine all 3 beans and browned ingredients in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch dish.
Mix 1/2 cup brown sugar, ketchup, vinegar and salt.
Pour over beans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon pie(makes 2)
directions: Mix lemonade and milk in large bowl; add Cool Whip.
Pour into the 2 pie crusts.
Top with more Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated until eaten.
May be frozen.

title: sausage balls
directions: While all ingredients are at room temperature, combine them and shape them into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes in the oven.

title: sausage hamburger dip
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage and onion together. Add soup and cheese.
Cook until cheese is all melted.

title: kielbasa bake
directions: Boil elbows until tender.
Mix sauce and spices.
Put a little sauce in the bottom of a large, rectangular casserole.
Add a layer of elbows, kielbasa, then Mozzarella and sauce.
Continue until casserole is filled.
Top with sprinkled Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, tomato soup, bell pepper and onion; add to drained carrots.
Mix well.
Keep indefinately in refrigerator.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Combine tuna, bread crumbs, celery and onion.
Blend mayonnaise, chili and lemon juice.
Stir into the tuna mixture. Form into 4 patties.
Fry in lightly oiled skillet over medium heat for about 5 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put frozen hash browns in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Press down with hands.
Mix together soup, sour cream, cheese and onion; pour over potatoes.
Melt butter/margarine; mix with crushed cereal.
Spread cereal over casserole.
Once ingredients are in baking pan, do not mix them together.
They should be layered.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: 5-cup chinese salad
directions: Heat the sugar, oil, vinegar and garlic salt and pour over salad. Make ahead. It keeps well.

title: pie crust(2)
directions: Stir flour and salt with fork.
Add the oil and milk.
If dry, add 2 tablespoons of oil and 1 tablespoon of milk.
Bake according to pie recipe.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, spread chicken breasts flat. Cut cheese and ham slices to fit on top.
Fold breast over filling.
Fasten edges with toothpicks.
Mix flour and paprika to coat chicken.

title: baked scalloped pineapple
directions: Beat together sugar, eggs, butter and milk.
Stir in bread, pineapple and juice.
Pour into 2-quart casserole (buttered). Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: reception salad
directions: Prepare jello and add all ingredients except whipped cream and mayonnaise.
When jello is partially set add them.
Then chill firmly.

title: festive ham spread
directions: Combine ham, 4 ounces cream cheese, 1/2 cup mayonnaise, onion and relish in bowl.
Mix well.
Chill.
Combine remaining ingredients, 4 ounces cream cheese and 1/4 cup mayonnaise.
Spread with cream cheese mixture.

title: cheese ring
directions: Blend thoroughly all ingredients except preserves.
Pam a 3-cup ring mold.
Press ingredients into mold and refrigerate overnight or at least two hours.
Unmold by carefully dipping right below top into hot water for 20 seconds.
Place plate on top and invert.
You may have to dip in hot water several times.
When you invert plate leave it for several minutes and it will release. Put preserves in center when ready to serve.
Surround with crackers and a cheese spreader.

title: creamy baked pork chops
directions: In a skillet, brown chops on both sides.
Pour off drippings. Stir in the can of soup and water. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and let stand for 1 hour in refrigerator.

title: breakfast casserole to serve anytime
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Spray a 9 x 9-inch baking dish with Pam. Brown crumbled sausage well and drain. Line baking dish with crescent rolls. Spread sausage over rolls. Pour eggs evenly over sausage. Sprinkle cheese on top in heavy layer. Bake 10 to 15 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: broccoli, cauliflower cheese bake
