directions: Prepare broccoli and cauliflower as directed on package. Drain and place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
In saucepan combine soup and Cheez Whiz.
Heat until smooth and creamy, stirring often.
Pour over vegetables and mix lightly.
Cover with onion rings and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Mix dressing, soup mix and cranberry sauce together and pour over chicken.
Place in a 14 x 11-inch dish (do not stack or crowd pieces).
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste every 15 minutes.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Combine butter, shortening and sugar; cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each addition. Stir in vanilla and food coloring.
Combine flour and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Beat well.

title: hard rock candy
directions: Mix sugar, water and syrup.
Combine and cook to 300°.
Remove from heat and add flavoring and coloring.
Mix well.
Pour into well-greased jelly roll pan with sides.
Let cool until it can be scored with pizza cutter or knife.
Loosen sides and break into pieces when cool.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Dust off well.

title: hot stir-fried shrimp
directions: Clean and butterfly the shrimp.
In

a medium size bowl, combine 4 tablespoons each of the cornstarch, sherry and soy sauce. Add 1 teaspoon of the salt and 1 teaspoon powdered ginger. Put in the shrimp and marinate in the mixture for 20 minutes. Heat peanut oil in wok until very hot. Add crushed fresh ginger root and garlic and cook until brown. Discard ginger root and garlic but keep the oil in the wok. Drain shrimp and reserve marinade. To the reserved marinade, add the remaining 6 tablespoons each of the cornstarch, sherry and soy sauce, the remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1 1/2 teaspoons powder ginger.
In hot oil, stir-fry shrimp for 2 minutes until opaque.
Add green onions and dried peppers.
Cook 1 minute. Add marinade and water chestnuts. Cook 3 minutes until sauce thickens. Do not overcook shrimp. Serve over hot rice.
Serves 6.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer if possible.
Thin with milk if necessary.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix eggs and sugar in bowl; add oil and beat.
Add soda, cinnamon, flour and salt.
Add pumpkin and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Use a Bundt pan.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes on greased cookie sheets.
Let cookies stand a few minutes before removing.
Yields 24 dozen.
Frozen cookies taste great too!
Do not overbake!

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Add chopped celery, carrots, onions and green pepper (to your taste).
Assemble in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: cauliflower and broccoli bake
directions: Cook cauliflower and broccoli separately until tender; drain. Mix vegetables with soup, well beaten eggs, grated cheese and mayonnaise.
Place mixture in a 2 quart baking dish.
Cover with crumbs or bread and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole. Boil carrots until tender.
On top of stove, melt butter. Add flour and all ingredients except Velveeta. Stir until thick.
Cut Velveeta into strips.
Add 1/2 carrots to greased casserole. Top with cheese. Add rest of carrots.
Pour sauce on top. Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until hot and bubbly.

title: chocolate angel food cake
directions: Sift cake flour, cocoa and powdered sugar together. Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until foamy. Gradually add sugar until very stiff peaks form.
Fold in vanilla.
Add flour mixture gradually folding gently after each addition. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine with cracker crumbs.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Cream 2 sticks margarine with eggs and sugar.
Beat 10 minutes.
Pour over crust.
Add diced bananas and pineapple and cover with Cool Whip.
Top with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate and cut into squares when firm and serve.

title: string bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Dice boiled eggs and onion.
Add mayonnaise, salt, pepper and celery salt to taste.

title: easy vegetable salad
directions: Combine vegetables in large bowl.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake pizza crust on pizza pan or small cookie sheet.
Mix together Ranch dressing, cream cheese and mayo.
Spread on cooled crust.
Layer these ingredients in this order on crust and refrigerate: carrots, peppers, broccoli, cheese and tomatoes.
Cut into small slices.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix grated potatoes, onion, egg, flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well and fry in leftover bacon fat or oil.
Serve plain or with sour cream.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Start cooking the potato, carrots, celery, cabbage and onion in the beef broth and tomatoes and juice. When vegetables are done, crumble the hamburger on top (raw); salt. Cook about 10 minutes or until redness is out of meat.

title: sauerbraten
directions: In appropriate dish, combine all ingredients except beef and gingersnaps.
Place meat in marinade for at least 24 hours, turning occasionally.
Sprinkle crushed gingersnaps over all. Bake at 300° for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve sliced with juice or thicken juice as for gravy.

title: baked corn
directions: Make white sauce with milk, butter and flour.
Simmer until thick.
Add salt, sugar and eggs and mix well.
Mix in drained corn.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crunchy cinnamon french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except sauce in large bowl and mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Cover and refrigerate or freeze until ready to bake.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Set spinach balls on ungreased baking sheet and bake until golden brown, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with mustard sauce.
Can be served hot or at room temperature.

title: sopa (bread pudding)
directions: Place sugar in 3-quart heavy saucepan; cook over medium-high heat, no stirring, until sugar starts to melt.

Reduce heat to low; cook until sugar is golden brown, stirring frequently. Remove from heat. Carefully add water (it will splatter). Return to heat; bring to boiling, stirring to melt hardened lumps. Remove from heat. Stir in margarine, cinnamon and vanilla. In a 3-quart rectangular baking dish, layer half the bread cubes. Sprinkle half the cheese and all the raisins over bread cubes. Top with remaining cheese and nuts. Pour caramelized sugar mixture over all. Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until top is golden and syrup is absorbed. Serve Sopa with whipped cream and orange slices, if desired. Serves 16.

title: "old dutch" caramel corn
directions: Place corn curls in large roaster pan.
In 2-quart saucepan, cook together for 2 minutes the butter, brown sugar and corn syrup.
Add baking soda; mixture will foam.
Pour caramel mixture over corn curls and stir until mixed.
Place in 250° oven for 45 minutes.
Stir at least every 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from oven and pour on wax paper and break apart.

title: corned beef with sauerkraut in white wine
directions: Soak corned beef in cold water overnight in refrigerator. Drain and cover with fresh water.
Bring to a boil; reduce flame and simmer, covered, about 2 hours.
It will be about half done. Remove corned beef from pot, discarding cooking liquid.
Place juniper berries, bay leaf, thyme and parsley on a square of cheesecloth and tie to make a bouquet garni.
Put bacon, onion and garlic in the pot and saute until onion turns yellow, not brown. Return corned beef to pot.
Add sauerkraut and juice in the can (do not wash sauerkraut).
Add bouquet garni, wine and chicken broth. Stir well.
Simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally, until corned beef is almost done, about 1 1/2 hours.
Peel potatoes. Peel carrots and cut crosswise into 1-inch chunks.
Add potatoes and carrots to pot.
Continue to cook until corned beef and vegetables are tender.
Remove bouquet garni.
Serves six.

title: party fruit punch
directions: Combine first three ingredients, stirring well.
Chill.
To serve, combine chilled mixture and ginger ale in a punch bowl. Garnish with fruit slices and maraschino cherries if desired. Yields about 2 gallons.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Very good.

title: pilaf
directions: Saute noodles lightly in margarine.
Add broth; bring to a boil.
Add rice and simmer 20 minutes until tender and liquid is absorbed.
Add salt, cumin and Gravy Master to taste.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Arrange crescent rolls, with points to center, on pizza pan. Spread dough until bottom and sides are covered.
Sprinkle sausage on crust. Add potatoes and cheese.
Pour egg mixture over top. Finish with Parmesan cheese sprinkled on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mango chutney
directions: Cook ginger root and garlic in water for about 1 hour. Combine sugar and vinegar; simmer for 1 hour.
Add sliced mango and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until ready. Serve chutney with your favorite meat.

title: krumkake
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar and beat lightly; do not overbeat.
Add cooled, melted margarine and flavoring.
Sift flour and cornstarch; add to egg mixture.
Dough will be sticky enough to be dropped by a spoon.
Bake on krumkake iron.

title: rye bread
directions: Mix yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Add milk, oil, salt and sugar.
Add white and rye flour.
Put on floured board and knead for 5 to 10 minutes.
Put in greased bowl and let rise. Punch down once and let rise again.
Divide for four loaves and knead.
Put in greased bread pans.
Put oil on top of each loaf. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: john's fat-free white bread for breadmakers
directions: Mix ingredients in order as listed.
If you are going to use timer, make "well" on top of ingredients and put yeast there.
If crust appears harder then you like, use less sugar.
Makes 1 1/2 pound loaf.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients; pour into ice cream churn.
Freeze 10 minutes.
Add crushed Oreos.
Freeze until ice cream freezer cuts off.

title: curry dip
directions: Blend all ingredients, except vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 days.
Serve with vegetables.

title: apple pie
directions: Pour pie filling, most of the brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle cake mix over filling.
Cover; top lightly with remaining brown sugar.
Pour melted butter over all.
Sprinkle white sugar over top.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind pears, onions, and peppers.
Add sugar, vinegar, salt and spices.
Cook 30 minutes after mixture begins to boil.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal tightly.
If pears have lots of juice, drain off.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Beat egg with milk and add to the flour mixture, along with the melted butter.
Stir everything up well.
Spread batter in a greased 9-inch pie dish. Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes, or until lightly browned on edges.
Serve hot with butter.
tags: whole grain stone ground corn meal

title: sausage casserole
directions: Break up sausage in skillet; brown with chopped onion.
Don't pour off grease.
While sausage and onion are cooking, cook macaroni and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in baking dish and bake in a 350° oven until hot and bubbly.
An option is to sprinkle grated cheese on top and put in oven just long enough for cheese to melt.
Makes 1 large or 2 small casseroles.
Serve hot.

title: chili beans
directions: Saute onions in shortening until tender.
Add hamburger and cook until hamburger turns gray.
Add all the other ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook noodles; drain and rinse in cold water.
Fry sausage until done (you can add diced onion to this if you want).
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Layer noodles, spaghetti mixture and cheese in large cake pan or lasagna pan.
Keep layering until all used.
You can also add mushrooms to sauce if you want.
Cover with foil; bake 30 to 45 minutes, until hot and cheese is melted.

title: seven layer salad
directions: The night before salad is to be served:
layer the ingredients in the order given in a clear serving bowl, making sure each layer covers the previous layer and shows through the sides of the bowl.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 4 hours.

title: carrot and parsnip soup
directions: Heat oleo, add in this order:
(stirring after each addition) onion, leek, parsnip, carrots, celery, rice, parsley and dill.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Melt or soften butter.
Cream with sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour and salt with chopped nuts, dates and candy.
Add to creamed mixture.
Bake in large tube pan prepared as for other cakes.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: blondies
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and blend.
Stir in egg, then sifted dry ingredients.
Last stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread in well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into bars while still warm.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: Brown ground beef; dip off grease.
Chop medium-sized onion. Chop medium (1/2) cabbage head.
Dice potatoes.
Combine all with stewed tomatoes.
Simmer mixture for 20 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add chili powder.

title: italian chicken
directions: Mix in a bowl the bread crumbs, seed and cheese.
Set aside. In a bowl, place melted butter and oregano.
Sprinkle chicken with garlic salt.
Dip in butter mixture, then bread crumbs.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 450° for 1 hour.

Spread milk over top and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: potato crisp
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes.
Place potatoes in greased 9 x 12-inch dish.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese, corn flakes and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Combine chicken soup, mushroom soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Layer Doritos, meat mixture, soup mixture and shredded Velveeta.
Bake at 375° until cheese bubbles.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 2 baking sheets.
In medium bowl, beat butter or margarine and 1 cup sugar 5 to 8 minutes or until light and fluffy.
Beat in molasses and egg until blended. Sift flour, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon, cloves and salt over sugar mixture.
Stir with a wooden spoon to make a stiff dough. Shape dough into walnut sized balls; roll in sugar to coat.
Place about 2 1/2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated oven 12 to 14 minutes.
Remove from baking sheets; cool on wire racks.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients in large skillet.
Cover and cook over medium heat until tender.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all dry ingredients well, then add liquids.
If you want raisins, add in with dry ingredients.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes for a chewy cookie.
Bake 10 to 11 minutes for crispy cookies.
Cool 3 to 4 minutes on cookie sheet.
Store tightly covered.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen cookies or something around that.

title: judy's potatoes
directions: Make mashed potatoes with butter and milk or follow instructions on instant potato package.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Beat with mixer 4 minutes.
Pour mixture into greased and floured loaf pans (2 large or 3 small loaf pans).
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: curried chicken casserole
directions: Layer cooked broccoli and chicken in 13 x 9-inch dish.	Mix soup, milk, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour on top of layered chicken and broccoli.
Top with grated cheese.	Mix bread crumbs and melted margarine; sprinkle on top of cheese.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: duck breast in herb sauce
directions: Combine chicken broth and shallots.
In shallow dish, arrange duck breasts in single layer.
Pour broth over duck breasts; cover tightly.
Microwave on 60% (bake) for 15 to 17 minutes.
Turn once during cooking.
(Duck breasts should be cooked to medium rare at this point.)
Remove from oven and cover tightly with aluminum foil, shiny-side down.

title: pat-in-pan crust
directions: Combine flour, salt and sugar.
Stir well.
Mix oil and milk and pour in flour mixture.
Stir well.
Pat in 9-inch pie plate. Can pour in pie mixture or bake for pie shell at 425° for about 10 minutes (prick crust with fork before baking).

title: fried dill pickles
directions: Stir flour, cornstarch, baking powder, and salt into a large bowl.
Make a well in center, add water, egg yolk and dill pickle juice at the same time.
Stir until smooth.
Cover bowl and refrigerate 30 minutes.
Heat at least 2 inches of oil in deep fryer.
Dip pickles in batter to coat evenly and fry.

title: italian marinade salad
directions: The night before, cook noodles according to package instructions.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Add bottle of McCormick Salad Supreme, Italian dressing and onion.
Toss and refrigerate overnight.
Add other ingredients a few hours before serving, then chill.
The longer it sets, the better it tastes. May also add chopped broccoli, cauliflower and black olives.

title: best white sugar cookies
directions: Cream the butter and shortening; add sugar and cream well. Add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour, soda and cream of tartar; add gradually, creaming well.
Add vanilla; cream well.
Chill dough 3 to 4 hours or overnight.
Roll out 1/4 inch on floured board. Bake at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet 7 to 9 minutes.

title: italian butter bean bake
directions: Saute onion, chicken broth and garlic until transparent.
Add remaining ingredients to saute mixture.
Bring to boil; transfer to casserole.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours until thickened.

title: shirley's chicken casserole
directions: In a large pot, cover chicken with water; if desired, add onion, carrots, celery and bay leaf for more flavor.
Boil until tender.
Skin chicken; discard skin.
Pick meat from bones and place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread vegetables over chicken.
Heat soup, butter and broth together and pour over chicken.
Mix Bisquick and milk together.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Bake in 375° oven for 40 to 60 minutes or until top is brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: stir 'n' spoon fudge drops
directions: Combine margarine, evaporated milk, sugar and salt in a saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Start timing when mixture starts to bubble around edges of pan.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, chocolate, vanilla, walnuts and raisins.
Stir vigorously 1 minute or until marshmallows melt and blend.
Working quickly, drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Cool.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: heath bar trifle(also called death by chocolate)
directions: Bake ahead of time chocolate cake mix in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Poke holes in cake 2 to 3 inches apart by using the end of a wooden spoon.
Drizzle a small amount of Kahlua into the holes and cover and let set overnight.
Mix the chocolate pudding up and set aside.
Crush the Skor bars and set aside.
Get a trifle dish and break up the chocolate cake all up into pieces.
Layer cake, pudding, Cool Whip and sprinkle with Skor bars.
Keep layering until all is used up.
Cool Whip with the candy will be on top.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt; put aside. Cream together sugar and oil and add to flour mixture. Add eggs to mixture one at a time. Add carrots and nuts. Bake in angel food pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: ham-n-cheese rolls
directions: Break crescent rolls into 4 rectangles, pressing together perforated lines that connect 2 triangles.
Spread desired amount of mustard over crescent rolls.
Next add layer of ham, then add layer of shredded cheese.
Roll up on long sides.
Using sharp knife, slice roll in approximately 1/2-inch slices.
After sliced, should look like pinwheels.
Lay on cookie sheet and bake according to crescent roll directions.

title: sue's pecan cookies
directions: Place one layer of Keebler graham crackers on a foil-covered 10 x 13-inch (or 15-inch) cookie sheet with sides.
Bring to rolling boil 2 sticks margarine and 1 cup light brown sugar (packed). Remove from heat and stir for two minutes.
Add vanilla, nuts and salt.
Pour over crackers and spread evenly.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool 5 minutes and remove from pan to waxed paper.

title: p-t-a bars
directions: Combine oatmeal, brown sugar and oleo in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.
Melt chips and peanut butter.
Spread over bars.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: beverage
directions: To thaw strawberries, fill the mixing bowl with warm tap water.
Place the unwrapped package of strawberries in the water. Let stand 10 minutes or until the strawberries are thawed.
Put strawberries and their juice into the blender container.
Cover with lid and blend until smooth.
Add the milk.
Cover and blend until smooth again.
Scoop or spoon half of the ice cream or yogurt into the strawberry mixture in the blender container. Cover and blend until smooth.
Turn off the blender and scrape the sides with a rubber scraper, as needed.
Add the rest of the ice cream or yogurt.
Cover and blend just until smooth, stopping the blender and scraping as needed.
Pour into glasses.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: doris' real cornbread
directions: Use a 9-inch cast-iron skillet.
Preheat oven to 475°.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk and egg.
Beat well.
Add 3 tablespoons of the corn oil and mix.
Heat the remaining oil, or a little bacon grease, in the skillet.
Heat the skillet until quite hot.
Pour mixture into hot skillet.
Bake at 475° for 15 minutes.

title: a. j. chocolate cake
directions: Pour 1/2 cup boiling water over baking chocolate in mixing bowl; stir until melted.
Measure other ingredients while the chocolate cools.

title: favorite custard pie
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add sugar, flour and salt.
Boil the milk and then add to the egg mixture.
Put into unbaked pie shell and bake at 400° for 15 minutes and then at 325° for another 15 minutes or until knife comes out clear.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix well in baking dish.
Put 1 pack Ritz cracker crumbs on top.
Dot with butter.
Put in oven at about 400° and let get good and hot.

title: special drink
directions: Put in 2-quart container and finish filling with water.

title: refried bean taco salad
directions: In bottom a long Pyrex dish, spread refried beans.
Next spread sour cream, salsa, green onions, cheese, black olives, tomatoes and lettuce.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour. Eat on chips.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Top with butter, flour, brown sugar and pecans mixed together. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: ojarascus-mexican shortbread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Add hot cinnamon tea until you are able to form balls.
Flatten the balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until brown.
Sprinkle tops of cookies with a mixture of cinnamon and sugar.

title: bavarian sauerkraut
directions: Brown pork chops in oil and remove.
Toss together brown sugar, onion, caraway seed and sauerkraut.
Place back into the skillet and place pork chops on the top.
Cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes until tender.
Serves 4.

title: apricot tea loaf
directions: Cover apricots with warm water for 30 minutes.
Drain and cut into small pieces.
Sift together next four ingredients and set aside.
Mix next five ingredients together well.
Add sifted ingredients to sugar mixture with apricot pieces and walnuts.
Mix until flour is just dampened.
Pour into greased and floured pan (8 1/4 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan).
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes until lightly browned.
Turn out on wire rack.

title: new england scrod
directions: Scrod is not a fish at all.
It is a classic way of preparing common fish filets in New England.
Fish should be served with potatoes.
With this dish, I prefer small red potatoes, halved and sauteed in butter in parsley and pepper.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Cook zucchini in very little water over medium heat for 6 minutes.
Bring to a boil and turn heat down to simmer.
Add sugar, lemon
juice, pineapple flavoring and pineapple.
Bring to boil and cook 6 minutes.
Add dry jello and mix well.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: swiss steak and vegetables
directions: Trim steak and rub with garlic.
Pound into steak as much seasoned flour as both sides will hold.
Brown meat in fat on one side.
When turned over, place in casserole; add chopped vegetables and seasoning.
Cover with tomato juice.
Bake in covered casserole for 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: angel food cake dessert
directions: Place slices of cake in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Spread pie filling over cake slices.
Mix milk, cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over pie filling.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: potatoes candy
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Roll out flat and spread with a thin layer of peanut butter.
Roll up and chill in refrigerator for about 1 hour, then cut into inch pieces.

title: 90 minute dinner rolls
directions: Mix 3/4 cup flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Heat milk, water and margarine to 120° to 130°.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed of mixer.
Add 1/4 cup flour.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in enough additional flour to make soft dough.
On floured board, knead 2 to 3 minutes.
Divide into 10 or 12 equal pieces.
Shape into balls. Place in greased 8-inch round pan.
Set pan in warm place.
Cover with damp cloth and let rise 30 minutes.
Bake in oven at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: If using fresh broccoli, finely chop or put through food processor; if using frozen broccoli, thaw and drain.
Melt butter and saute onion.
Add chopped broccoli and cook one minute.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in broth.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes, until broccoli is tender.
Stir in cream.
Heat short time until hot.
Serve.

title: biscotti di regina(italian sesame seed cookies)
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together (flour, oats, nuts, coconut, sugar and salt).
In small bowl, mix baking soda and water.
Then melt butter with Karo syrup over low heat; remove pan from heat. Stir in baking soda mixture.
Then stir butter mixture into flour mixture, combining well.
Round 1 tablespoon of batter and press into disks on cookie sheet, 2 inches in diameter.
Bake in middle of oven for 14 minutes at 325°.
Cool on cookie sheet.
Makes 30 cookies.
Keep in airtight container.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Cream sugar, butter and shortening together until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time and mix well after each.	Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Combine milk, food coloring, lemon and vanilla flavoring and cocoa together; add to batter.
Beat at high speed until mixed well. Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Fill to 2/3 full. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes until done.	Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: quick twist
directions: Mix 1 cup flour, salt and undissolved yeast.
Heat 1 cup water and margarine to 120° to 130°.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed of mixer.
Add 1/2 cup flour. Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in enough additional flour to make soft dough.
On floured board, knead 5 minutes.
Set in greased bowl; turn to grease top.
Cover; let rise in warm, draft- free place 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Add salad oil, lemon juice and Accent; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
After refrigeration, add remaining ingredients and chill.
Serve.
Will keep up to 3 weeks refrigerated.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Cut in shortening until mixture is like coarse cornmeal.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Slice crust off white bread.
Mix all ingredients (except asparagus) together.
Spread mixture over slice of bread.
Layer asparagus pieces.
Roll; cut in half.
Brush with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: hershey pie
directions: Whip chocolate bars and Cool Whip together.
Place in graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: green bean salad(lo-cal)
directions: Bring ingredients in saucepan to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Add beans and pimento.
Return to boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and chill before serving.
Tastes best if done a day ahead and chilled overnight.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat well.
Pour filling into pastry shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lucy's cream cheese pound cake
directions: *I use 2 cups plain flour and 1 cup self-rising.

title: quick and easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Add sugar, oil, salt and egg.
Stir to dissolve sugar and salt.
Stir in one cup of flour until smooth.
Cover with cloth, place on rack over a bowl of hot water; let rise 15 minutes.
Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Stir down batter and add 1 1/2 cups flour.
Stir until mixed and turn out onto floured board or countertop.
Knead 3 minutes. If still sticky, knead in 1/4 cup more flour.
Divide into 16 pieces and shape quickly into balls; arrange in pan and brush tops with butter.
Cover with cloth.
Place on rack over bowl of hot water.
Let rise 25 minutes.
Heat oven to 425°.
Bake rolls 12 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Remove from pan onto wire rack. Brush tops with butter.
Makes 16 servings.
Recipe could be doubled.

title: peanut butter hershey kisses cookies
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix on low speed until dough forms.
Shape into balls, using a rounded teaspoon for each.
Roll balls in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.
Press Hershey Kiss into each cookie while hot.

title: corn bread
directions: Blend together the sugar, butter, eggs and salt.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 365° to 375° for 35 minutes.

title: hen and dressing
directions: Clean hen and put in large pot.
Add water until almost covered.
Salt and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Prepare Marie's Cornbread for Dressing.
In large bowl, crumble cornbread and cover with broth.
Mix well.
Take meat off bony pieces of chicken, cut up fine and put in mixture.
Add eggs, onions and poultry seasoning.
Add more broth until dressing is not quite soupy.
Mix dressing well.
Grease roasting pan.
Pour dressing in pan.
Place hen on top of dressing.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour and baking powder.
Stir in creamed mixture with zucchini.
Add nuts and coconut.
Bake in greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1 1/2-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: This is better if made and let set in the refrigerator a day...

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash and sterilize 10 pint jars.
Wash okra and leave stems on. Pack in jar, stems up.
Place 1 pepper pod and 1 garlic clove in each hot jar.
Bring vinegar, water and salt to boil, remove from fire immediately and add 1 teaspoon celery salt or mustard seed, if desired.
Pour boiling hot mixture over okra and seal jar.
Let stand 2 months before using.

title: chocolate thumbprint cookies
directions: In a small bowl, cream butter, sugar, egg yolk, milk and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt; blend into creamed mixture.
Chill dough at least 1 hour or until firm enough to handle.
Heat oven to 350°.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls.
Beat egg white slightly.
Dip each ball into egg white; roll in nuts. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press thumb gently in center of each cookie.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
As soon as cookies are removed from oven, spoon about 1/4 teaspoon filling in thumbprint.
Gently press kiss in center of each cookie. Carefully remove from cookie sheet.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix milk, eggs, flour and salt well and cook on low heat for 5 minutes.
Pour through strainer.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add more milk to fill line of freezer.
Freeze until firm.

title: tasty potatoes
directions: Roll potatoes in mix of cheese and flour.
Put in baking pan. Pour over 1 stick margarine.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mint juleps
directions: Crush fresh sprigs of mint in a 3 to 4-quart pan.
Fill with water; boil and boil and boil until it turns green.
Remove mint leaves.
Stir in sugar to taste until it is dissolved.
Store liquid in jars until ready to use.

title: schmeyer bacardi rum cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, lemon jello, eggs, water, oil and dark rum.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Put 1/2 of nuts in pan and add 1/2 of mixed cake mixture.
Add other half of nuts and rest of cake mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: creole cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage into 6 wedges.
Remove core.
Cover and cook 10 minutes in small amount of lightly salted boiling water.
Drain well and carefully place wedges in greased 2 quart shallow baking pan.
Saute pepper and onion in butter until tender; add tomatoes, salt, pepper, and sugar to mixture.
Simmer for 3 minutes.
Pour over cabbage.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake until cheese is bubbly.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs in a large bowl until fluffy. Add other ingredients, using a wooden spoon.
Mix until even or around 50 strokes.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350° (325° if glass pan).
Cool, then serve or frost.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes and bacon and celery until tender.
Remove bacon.
Add salt and pepper.
Thicken with cornstarch or oil and flour mixture.
Serve with cornbread.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: In large skillet, combine sugar, grated rind, orange juice and butter.
Heat, stirring occasionally, over moderate heat until blended and smooth.
Add potatoes and simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Baste and turn potatoes occasionally to glaze evenly.

title: easy casserole
directions: Place ground beef in bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle on onion soup mix and spread undiluted mushroom soup on top.
Top with desired amount of cheese.
Line Tater Tots in a single layer over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 300° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes more.

title: freezer dinner rolls
directions: In large bowl mix 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
In saucepan, put water, milk and margarine.
Heat over low heat until liquids are very warm (125°).
Margarine doesn't need to melt.
Gradually add to flour mixture.
Beat in electric mixer for 3 minutes, then add eggs and 1 cup flour.
Beat at high speed for 3 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make soft dough.
Turn out on floured board.
Knead dough until smooth (about 10 minutes).
Cover with plastic wrap and then a towel.
Let rest for 20 minutes.

title: crusty pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add flour and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan almost immediately.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook wild rice in chicken broth. Combine with all ingredients. Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pineapple cream salad
directions: Boil pineapple and sugar mixture for 5 minutes in a saucepan. Remove from stove and add cream cheese.
Stir until it is dissolved.
Add the gelatin, which has been dissolved in cold water, to the mixture.
Refrigerate until the mixture is partially set.
Then fold in a small container of Cool whip.
Refrigerate overnight in a 12 x 8-inch Pyrex covered dish.
Cut in squares and place on lettuce.
Enjoy!

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and lemon rind; add boiling water. Cook on high heat until mixture begins to thicken.
Turn off and cook, stirring constantly for 5 minutes.
Add egg yolks, lemon juice and butter.
Cook on low for 5 minutes.
Turn into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil chicken; save broth.
Layer in dish:
Doritos, onion and bell pepper.
Pull chicken from bones; cut up and add to dish.
In saucepan, mix Ro-Tel, chicken soup, celery soup and 1 1/2 cups broth.
Pour into dish.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes. Then top with cheese.

title: lime buffet salad
directions: Mix ingredients and place in flat oblong casserole dish.
Cut into rectangular squares and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: caribbean pork chops with apple island sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients except meat. Place meat in a shallow dish or plastic bag. Pour marinade over meat to cover. Marinate in the refrigerator 4 hours or overnight. Remove meat from marinade; heat marinade. Grill or broil meat as desired, basting frequently with marinade.

title: easy brunswick stew
directions: Prepare cooked meats ahead of time or use leftovers. Heat tomatoes, corn, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
If cooking fresh ground beef, cut up onion and simmer. Add meat to tomato mixture. Cook in large broiler on low heat for 45 minutes. Save leftover stew; it's even better the next day.

title: zucchini bread
directions: You will need 2 greased and floured loaf pans.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening.
Add water and egg, making soft dough.
Roll out into thin sheets.
Dry 15 or more minutes.
Cut into strips and drop into boiling broth.
Don't cover.

title: caramel pie
directions: Caramelize sugar with butter and add to hot milk.
Mix remaining sugar with flour and add to hot mixture.
Beat egg yolks and cook until thick.
Cool.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into cooked crust.

title: golden puffed broccoli
directions: Arrange cooked broccoli in shallow 1 1/2 quart pan or broiler-proof serving dish.
In small bowl with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites and salt until stiff peaks form.
Fold in cheese and real mayonnaise and spoon evenly over broccoli.
Broil 6-inches from source of heat 4 minutes or until golden brown. Serve immediately; 15 mg cholesterol per serving.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix soup, green beans and milk.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Top with bread crumbs and dried onions.
Bake 5 minutes with bread crumbs and onions until crispy.
Serves 6.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix apples, cinnamon and 5 tablespoons sugar; let stand.
In a separate bowl mix flour, baking powder, vanilla, 2 1/2 cups sugar, salt, orange juice, oil and eggs.
Beat well.
In a greased tube pan put a layer of dough, then apples, alternating, ending with apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve warm or cold.

title: polish mushrooms
directions: Sprinkle mushrooms with lemon juice.
Simmer, lightly covered, with onion and 3 tablespoons of the butter.
Season with salt and pepper, stir in flour and cheese.
Cook for about 3 minutes. Place in buttered baking dish.
Beat together cream and egg yolks.
Pour over mushrooms.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with remaining butter.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for about 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach pie *
directions: Line an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with 1/2 of the dough (4 rolls). Thaw and drain spinach.
Mix egg, garlic and spinach and layer on top of dough in pan.
Cover mixture with a layer of the cheese and another layer of the remaining dough.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour, until cheese is melted and dough is golden brown.
Let cool for about 5 to 10 minutes before cutting into small squares.
Can be frozen.

title: krazy kake
directions: Take a square 9-inch pan, ungreased, and set sifter in pan. Put the flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and soda in sifter.
Sift ingredients into baking pan.
Make 3 little hollows in flour mixture.
In
the first, put the vanilla. In the second put the vinegar and in the third, put the oil.
Pour the cold water over all and mix thoroughly in the pan. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef and Italian sausage in frying pan until brown.
Drain fat.
Boil water in a deep 5 qt. saucepan; add noodles to boiling water and cook until just softened (will cook more during final baking).
Add tomato puree to meat mixture in a large saucepan.
Add water, garlic salt, onion salt, celery salt, basil, parsley and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil and turn down heat to simmer.
Grate cheese into a large bowl.
In a 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan, spread a small amount of meat mixture. Layer 4 large noodles to cover sauce.
Spread noodles with more meat sauce. Cover meat sauce with cottage cheese.
Cover cottage cheese with layer of pepperoni.
Sprinkle grated cheese over pepperoni and cover with a layer of noodles.
Spread noodles with more meat sauce.
Sprinkle grated cheese over meat sauce.
Cover cheese with top layer of noodles and meat sauce.
Spread generous amount of grated cheese on the top.
Bake in pre-heated 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Let cool about 20 minutes before cutting and serving.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir together the flour, salt, cinnamon, baking soda and nutmeg.
In a large bowl, beat the margarine and sugar with electric mixer until fluffy.
By hand, stir in the egg, bananas and oatmeal.
Add the dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in the walnuts or raisins. Drop batter by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until edges begin to brown.

title: turkey and black bean chili
directions: Cook turkey in a large nonstick skillet until browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain.
May wish to microwave turkey, drain well on paper towels.
Heat oil in skillet.
Saute onion, garlic about 5 minutes.
Add chili powder, oregano, cumin.
You may want to use half amounts of these spices to start.
Return turkey to skillet; stir in water, prunes and beans.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Adjust seasonings to taste. Serve chili over rice.
Yield: 5 servings.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 12 x 12-inch pan.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add 1/2 of the butter and milk.
Pour dough mixture in pan.
Pour fruit (include juice) over dough.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: gelatin dessert
directions: Dissolve the
first
3	ingredients over heat.	Add the evaporated milk and red food coloring.

title: chocolate-walnut cookies
directions: Blend margarine, walnuts and chocolate bits together.
Beat in egg, milk and cake mix.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: apricot jello dessert
directions: Cook egg, sugar, pineapple juice, flour and butter until thick.
Then add cream cheese.
Whip until smooth.
Let cool, then fold in Cool Whip.
Spread mixture over Jell-O.
Cool.
Serve when ready.

title: coconut fruit bowl
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in whipped cream and salt. Chill and serve.
(You can use sour cream.)

title: cherry-orange punch
directions: Combine Kool-Aid, sugar, orange juice, water and ice cubes. Stir until dissolved.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: peanut sauce
directions: Heat oil in a saucepan; add onion and garlic.
Fry for 2 minutes.
Over medium heat, add remaining ingredients and mix well.
If sauce is too thick, add extra lemon juice or plain water.
If it is too thin, simmer gently until it becomes the right consistency to your taste.
Makes 4 servings.

title: quick salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.
This is good made ahead.
This contains no sugar.

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: Cook rhubarb, water and sugar for 5 minutes or until tender. Add pudding mix and strawberries.
Stir until mixture boils. Remove from heat and pour into serving dishes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: ophelia's corn pudding
directions: Mix flour with water and baking powder.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake at 350°. Check after 40 minutes.
Remove when set.
